title: sand tart cookies
directions: Add flour,
enough
to roll.
Roll and cut into shapes. Optional:
add
food
coloring to liquid mixture to give dough color or add colored sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Wash and dry chicken well on paper towels.
Combine flour, paprika, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken with flour mixture.
In shallow baking pan in oven, melt butter. Remove from oven.
Arrange chicken in pan in single layer, skin side down.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes.
With tongs, turn the chicken and bake 15 minutes longer, or until brown and fork-tender. Nice served with Cumberland Sauce.
Makes 3 servings.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions and drain.
Put in shallow, 2-quart baking dish; top with chicken.
Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, cream of chicken soup and herb seasoning; pour over ingredients in baking dish.
Prepare stuffing according to directions, using chicken broth instead of water.
Spread over the chicken and top with grated cheese.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: coconut balls
directions: Put eggs (well beaten), dates, sugar and salt in a frying pan. Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until thick enough to hold together. Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies, vanilla and nuts. Cool. Roll into balls and roll in finely grated coconut.

title: spice cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar. Add milk, oil, flavoring and eggs. Add spice and mix well. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, until done.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Place the sliced cucumber and onion in a bowl and sprinkle with the salt, pepper and sugar.
Allow to sit for a few minutes. Pour the vinegar over the cucumber and onion.
Place several ice cubes on the cucumbers to crisp them.
Refrigerate for 1 hour. Remove the ice cubes and serve.

title: best ever cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the pecans, until well blended. Use hands for best results.
Chill.
Form into a ball, or any desired shape, and roll in pecans.	Serve with assorted crackers and watch it get gobbled up.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Mix together brown sugar, nuts, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and nutmeg (set aside).
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and salt.
Cream together butter, white sugar, 1/2 cup brown sugar and add 2 eggs, beating well.
Add dry ingredients with cream mixture, alternating with 1 cup buttermilk, beating well after each addition.
Spread batter into 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar mixture over batter.
Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: orange carrot cake
directions: Blend all ingredients; beat 2 minutes at highest speed.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes or until done in a 350° oven.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers, onions and peppers with 2 trays of ice for 6 hours.
Cover with lid.
Boil remaining ingredients 5 minutes. Put pickles in mixture until they change colors.
Seal in jars.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Take Hershey candy bar and shred.
Put oatmeal in blender and shred, then mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.

title: irish bread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour in black frying pan (greased).
Spread on butter while warm (optional).

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Pour into greased baking dish (13 x 9-inch) and sprinkle with Parmesan and crushed cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Freezes and reheats well.

title: tortoni squares
directions: Warm the preserves slightly and stir so it will spread over ice cream.

title: "fruit cocktail"
directions: Place ingredients in blender and serve in champagne glasses or brandy snifter and garnish with cherry and orange slices.
To serve as a before dinner drink, frappe with a little crushed ice. To serve as an after dinner drink, add the vanilla ice cream if desired.
Serves 2.

title: fresh rhubarb pie
directions: Combine in mixing bowl the sugar, flour and rhubarb; mix well. Pour into 9-inch pastry-lined pan.
Dot with butter.
Roll out remaining dough.
Cut slits for escape of steam.
Moisten rim of bottom crust.
Place top crust over filling.
Fold edge under bottom crust, pressing to seal.
Flute edge to make high standing rim.
Brush with milk and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until golden brown and rhubarb is tender.

title: microwaved mashed potatoes
directions: Place potatoes, milk and butter in a 3-quart casserole dish. Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook on High until the potatoes are very tender, about 15 minutes.
With a mixer set on lowest speed, mash the potatoes right in the cooking liquid.
When the lumps are gone, season with salt and pepper.
Then, on high speed, whip until light, adding more milk if potatoes are thick.
Serves 4.

title: tortilla bread
directions: Mix flour and yeast.
Mix water, sugar and salt.
Add to flour; stir well, then beat vigorously for 3 minutes.
Stir in cornmeal and enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead 3 to 5 minutes.
Form into ball; let rise in covered greased bowl for 1 hour.
Punch down; let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into two round loaves and put into two greased round pans.
Let rise 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes; remove from pans and cool on racks.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and cream cheese.
Add milk, soup mix, garlic and spinach.
Mix well.
Top with onion rings. Bake in casserole approximately 45 minutes.

title: favorite beef loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Shape mixture in a loaf in a shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Cook frozen broccoli.
Saute garlic with all the vegetables in butter.
Add lemon juice.
Mix in soup and cheese until melted. Drain broccoli; add to mixture until everything is mixed together. Serve in chafing dish on low heat.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 1 quart.

title: mexican dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and press into bottom of glass pie plate. Pour chili on top of cream cheese and top with Cheddar.
Microwave mixture until cheese melts.
Serve with taco chips.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Put mixture of all ingredients (except cherries) in a greased 8-inch square pan. Pour over it 1 pint of red cherries, drained. Add 1 cup of the drained juice.
If there is not a full cup, add water to make 1 cup of cherry juice liquid. Sprinkle with 3/4 cup of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Turn to 325° for 24 minutes or until set.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Cook sugar, milk and margarine until it is at soft ball stage. Take off heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until it starts getting stiff. Put on buttered pan.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Set aside.
Cook grits in boiling water for 3 minutes.
Add cheese and margarine to grits; mix until cheese and margarine are melted.
Add egg mixture and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Place cooked, drained noodles in a 2-quart casserole dish. Add tuna over noodles. Pour soup over tuna. Add black pepper and top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef brisket
directions: Cover brisket with the ingredients in the order given.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: eggs bondurant
directions: Turn heat on; put water in pan that will hold water.
Drop in eggs.
Boil for 6 minutes.
Take eggs out of water.
Run cold water over eggs for 2 minutes.
Take off outer shells.
Cut in half; eat.

title: fried cabbage and ham
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add chopped cabbage, carrots, salt and pepper.
Cook on medium heat; stir frequently to keep from burning.
Let cabbage begin to brown.
Add 1 cup water and ham.
Cover and simmer for about 20 minutes.

title: eck's jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes or until done.

title: glazed ham with sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat broiler.
Position oven rack about 4 inches from heat source.
Place ham in shallow pan.
Surround with peaches and sweet potatoes; drizzle peaches and sweet potatoes with 1 tablespoon maple syrup.
Broil 5 minutes or until lightly browned. Meanwhile, heat combined jam and mustard in microwave until jam is melted; stir until well-blended.
Turn ham, peaches and sweet potatoes over; brush ham with jam mixture.
Drizzle peaches and sweet potatoes with remaining 1 tablespoon maple syrup.
Continue broiling 5 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serves 4.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening, sugar and salt.
Add eggs 1 at a time, mixing well.
Add soda to flour.
Sift and stir into shortening mixture, gradually add buttermilk 1/3 cup at a time.
Pour into tube pan and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, potatoes and onion until done.
Drain fat. Mix both soups and add to meat and potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: beaumont inn corn pudding
directions: Combine flour, salt and sugar.
Mix it and butter into corn. Beat eggs well.
Pour into milk, then stir into corn mixture. Pour into a 3-quart greased casserole.
At this point, it may be refrigerated overnight or frozen for several weeks.
(If you freeze, use a dish that is freezer and oven safe.)

To serve, thaw and bake in 400° oven for 40 to 50 minutes, stirring vigorously with a long-tined cooking fork 3 times, about 10 minutes apart. Pudding should be soft, but set in center when done and top should be golden.
Makes 12 servings.

title: summer jello salad
directions: Following directions, prepare the jello in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add the cottage cheese and pineapple to the jello and stir well. Float the marshmallows on top.
Chill until set.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage, cool and crumble in mixing bowl.
Beat eggs. Add milk, salt, mustard and bread.
Stir and add cheese and sausage.
Pour in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Put in cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Soak chicken in buttermilk for 15 minutes.
Coat chicken well in dry ingredients.
Put Crisco in skillet.
Heat on medium-high heat.
Add floured chicken and brown on one side with cover on skillet, then turn and brown on other side.
Replace cover.
Cook until tender and brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Ready to serve.

title: squash dressing
directions: Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: bavarian sausage and sauerkraut
directions: Drain cans of kraut and place in crock-pot. Slice sausage and place on top of kraut.
Drain potatoes and place on top of sausage.
Cover and simmer in crock-pot until heated through.

title: ginger ale pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating after each.
Add flavoring.
Add flour and ginger ale alternately.

title: cheese bars
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Unroll and put a layer of crescent rolls on bottom.
Mix together rest of ingredients.
Pour onto dough.
Unroll other package of rolls and place on top.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 24 hour vegetable salad
directions: Place lettuce or spinach in bottom of a large salad bowl; sprinkle with a little salt, pepper and sugar.
Spoon desired vegetable evenly atop.
Arrange egg slices and bacon over vegetable.
Top with desired shredded cheese.
Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, paprika and red pepper.
Spread mayonnaise mixture over top of salad, sealing to edge of bowl.
Cover and chill salad in the refrigerator up to 24 hours.
Garnish top of salad with sliced green onion.
Before serving, toss to coat the vegetables. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: pepperollies
directions: Separate the 8 crescent roll triangles.
With rolling pin, roll out each crescent roll triangle slightly on floured board.
Cut triangle lengthwise into two triangles.
At widest end of triangle, place 2 slices of pepperoni.
Top with 1 tablespoon cheese and roll from wide to narrow end.
Place on baking sheet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with your favorite marinara sauce as a warm dip.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Bring to boil, stirring constantly cranberries and sugar. Boil until cranberries pop and are done only a few minutes. Dissolve one box of lemon jello in 1/4 cup boiling water.
Add this to the mixture as you take from stove, then add celery, crushed pineapple and nuts.
Put in small oblong size dish to set. Can be made several days ahead.

title: squash balls
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Form into small balls or patties.
Roll in cornflakes.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown. Serve hot.

title: mexican macaroni casserole
directions: Brown sausage, onion and green pepper in a large skillet. Stir in tomatoes, sour cream, sugar, chili powder and salt.
Add macaroni.
Cover skillet and simmer about 30 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: roasted pecans
directions: Melt oil and butter on large broiler tray or cookie sheet with sides to prevent oil and butter from running off.
Sprinkle with salt.
In single thickness, spread pecans over tray and stir to coat them with the mixture in the tray.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring frequently.
If necessary, more salt may be added to taste.

title: hearty wild rice soup
directions: Rinse wild rice and soak in cold water 1 hour. Drain.
Cover with boiling water and cook over low heat 40 minutes.
Melt butter in 4-quart pan and saute onion. Blend in flour.
Gradually add the broth and cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened. Stir in rice, salt, carrots, celery and mushrooms. Simmer 5 minutes. Add cream and sherry.
Heat to serve. Garnish with parsley.
Yields 12 cups.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar with wire whisk. Combine this with remaining ingredients making sure broccoli is thoroughly coated.
Refrigerate for two hours before serving.

title: plum pudding rum sauce
directions: Pour brown sugar in pot; stir with spoon.
Add water; heat until sugar starts to crystallize.
When clear, add butter, then rum.
Thicken with flour or corn starch.
Serve over plum pudding.

title: dang good pie
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, vanilla, pineapple and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until center is solid.

title: cranberry salad mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and allow to cool until partially thickened.
Gently fold in sour cream, cranberry sauce and salt. Spoon into individual salad molds or l large mold. Chill until firm.
Unmold onto lettuce. Serve with any salad dressing.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pizza loaf
directions: Let dough rise according to directions.
Combine in skillet the meat, onion, tomato sauce, mushrooms and pepper flakes.
Add paprika, oregano, celery salt, garlic salt and pepper.

Cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes. Stir in olives. Cool to lukewarm. Press dough out onto 2 greased 10 x 15-inch cookie sheets (one loaf on each sheet). Place half of meat mixture on each loaf. Spread to within 2-inches of outside.
Sprinkle with cheese. Fold ends over filling. Brush with milk.
Let rise in warm place for 15 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco.
Add buttermilk and yeast (dissolved in 1/2 cup warm water).
Mix with spoon (I usually use my hands).
Cover and put in refrigerator.
Pat out 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Will keep several weeks in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together peanut butter, confectioners sugar, graham cracker crumbs and margarine.
Shape into balls the size of walnuts.
In a double boiler, melt chocolate chips.
When chocolate is melted, dip balls in chocolate (can use tongs to do this) and place on waxed paper on a cookie sheet.
(Balls can be rolled in coconut or chopped nuts if desired.)
Let cool thoroughly in refrigerator.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: oven brown rice
directions: Mix together in glass dish.
Slice butter on top.
Cover and bake at 350° to 400° for 1 hour.

title: salsa
directions: Chop onion, peppers (be careful with the peppers, wash your hands afterwards), and cilantro.
Put them in a food processor and process until they are to the consistency you want - should be fairly fine.
Heat tomatoes in a sauce pot over medium-high heat to a slow boil.
Add hot tomatoes to the processor.
Add a dash of salt (to taste).
Process all ingredients until mixed and the tomatoes are in a juice-like consistency.
Cool and serve.

title: crispy broiled zucchini
directions: Wash zucchini and slice into half-inch rounds.
Boil in salted water just until tender.
Drain and spread zucchini in a shallow baking pan.
Melt butter.
Peel and grate onion.
Stir onion and green chile into the butter.
Spread this mixture over the zucchini.
Shake salt and pepper over slices.
Sprinkle cheese over it.
Broil about three inches from heat for five minutes or until cheese is a light brown.
Serves 4.

title: layered salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise and sour cream.
Refrigerate.
Rinse peas and drain, set aside.
Wash and cut lettuce in small pieces. Divide 1/2.
Place 1/2 lettuce in large bowl.
Slice boiled eggs and arrange around sides of bowl.
Place remaining eggs on lettuce.
Layer ham, cheese, Bac*Os, cucumbers and carrots. Arrange remaining lettuce on top.
Spread peas.
Spoon mayonnaise/sour cream sealing the salad.
Top with potato/salad topping mix and arrange tomato wedges.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Can be made 24 hours in advance.

title: chicken marsala
directions: In electric frypan at 350°, cook chicken in 2 tablespoons butter and 1 tablespoon oil until browned.
Remove from pan.
Add 2 tablespoons butter.
Saute mushrooms until tender.
Add soup and Marsala wine.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Return chicken to pan. Simmer 5 to 7 minutes more.
Serve with noodles.

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine, sugars, peanut butter, vanilla and egg in a medium bowl vigorously until creamy and well blended.
Mix in flour and oats.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 1 minute.
Remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.
Yields about 2 dozen cookies.

title: peanut butter chicken
directions: Mix peanut butter and milk until creamy.
Add chicken and let set overnight or a few hours.
Put dry ingredients into a shaker bag; add chicken and coat well.
Melt 1 stick margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add coated chicken.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°.
Turn chicken and bake 20 minutes more.
Serves 4.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Melt butter in large pan.
Add flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg. Stir until smooth.
Add broth and cream.
Cook until thickens. Remove from heat.
Combine with spaghetti, mushrooms and turkey. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10.

title: one-minute drop candy
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a rolling boil and boil for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: jennifer chicken salad
directions: Mix the ingredients in blender or mixer.

title: quick caramel topping
directions: In a 4-cup measure, cook caramels and water, uncovered, on 100% power (High) for 2 to 3 minutes or until soft enough to stir smooth, stirring once.
Top ice cream.
Makes 3/4 cup (6 servings).

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix together flour, 1 stick butter (softened) and cream cheese.
Chill, then put in small tart pans.
Make filling.
Add together beaten egg, 2 tablespoons butter, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into tart pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour; measure.
Add baking powder, salt and soda.
Sift again.
Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Continue beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and mix until smooth.
Add dry ingredients alternately with mashed bananas, stirring enough to combine thoroughly.
Add nuts.
Turn into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: alaskan wild blueberry nugget cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, beat both sugars until light and fluffy.
Add water, black walnut extract and eggs. Blend well.
(Mixture will look curdled.)
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup.
Stir in flour, rolled oats, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Roll into inch and a half ball by hand and put hole in center.
Add fruit to hole.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 6 to 9 minutes.
Yields 4 1/2 to 5 dozen.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix; spoon over chicken and bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: cinnamon apple salad
directions: Dissolve jello and candies in boiling water.
Stir in applesauce, lemon juice and salt.
Chill until partially set.
Add walnuts.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: oatmeal cookies(they stay soft)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream together the shortening and sugar. Add eggs.
Mix together flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves. Add flour mixture alternately with applesauce. Add raisins, nuts, oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet 2-inches apart to allow for spreading.
Bake 15 minutes or until done at 375°.
Serves 4 dozen.

title: wendy's chili
directions: In large skillet, put oil, and ground round; brown.
In a blender, add onion soup and blend only 1 second.
Add to the ground round.
Then add cumin, pepper, Tabasco, kidney beans, tomato paste and tomato sauce and cook until ready to eat.

title: sausage egg bake
directions: Brown sausage.
Sprinkle cubed bread on bottom of an 8 x 11-inch casserole.
Top with sausage.
Combine other ingredients; pour over sausage.
Top with cheese.
Let sit overnight.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and warm chicken, soup, chilies and water or broth.
Layer in casserole: tortillas, onion, grated cheese and warmed mixture.
Bake at 350° until thoroughly warmed.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together chicken broth, water and chicken soup.
Add rice and chicken breasts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: crab appetizer
directions: Split cream cheese and lay on dish, end to end.
Top with rinsed crab meat.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over crab meat just before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Spread the pineapple over the bottom, over that the cherry pie mix.
Over that spread the dry cake mix.
Scatter nuts.
Cut oleo into small squares and place all over the top until cake is completely covered.
Do not stir or mix.
Bake as is at 350° for 1 hour.
Cut into squares and serve with whipped cream.

title: party chicken
directions: Skin, split and bone the chicken, making 16 halves.
Wrap each half with 1/2 piece bacon and skewer with toothpicks.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange the dried beef in greased pan.
Place chicken on dried beef.
Combine soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 3 hours.

title: indian corn casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, stirring once after the dish has baked for 30 minutes.
Garnish with additional pimientos, if desired.
Yields 8 servings.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: In a large frying pan, brown bacon.
Add chopped lettuce and onion.
When lettuce and onion are cooked, add tomatoes and seasonings.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: alexander icicle
directions: Blend until creamy and smooth.
Serve in stem glass.
Add sweetened whipped cream for garnish.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls in pizza pan and bake at 350° to 375° for 10 minutes; let cool.
Mix sour cream, cream cheese and dressing mix.
Spread over crust.
Cut up vegetables and arrange on top.
Spread Mozzarella cheese on top of vegetables.

title: cracker snacks
directions: Blend ingredients. Pour over cheese oyster crackers. Coat and turn frequently to blend. Should let blend for 2 hours before serving.

title: grits souffle
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add grits; cook until thick.
Add cheese, beaten egg yolks and seasonings.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Fold in beaten egg whites and turn into a well-greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer if dish is deep. Good served with fried chicken and pork entrees.

title: macaroni cheese deluxe
directions: Cook and drain macaroni according to box directions.
Don't overcook.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, egg, salt and pepper.
Add grated cheese and mix.
Stir in macaroni.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: In pastry shell arrange sliced and peeled apples in a circular fashion.
Mix together sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle some of the mixture over each layer of apples.
Sprinkle nutmeg over top layer and dot with butter.
Top with a slashed pie crust and crimp edges. Brush top crust with a little beaten egg and sprinkle sugar over top.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes more.

title: best sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugars, margarine and oil.
Add eggs and mix.
Add flour, cream of tartar and baking soda; mix.
Add vanilla and mix.
Chill dough.

title: divine turkey divan
directions: Make white sauce with butter, flour, bouillon and milk.
Stir in cheese and mayonnaise.
Arrange broccoli in 8 x 12-inch dish, cover with turkey.
Pour white sauce over.
Combine bread crumbs and melted butter; sprinkle over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Slivered almonds may be added on top.

title: zesty meat loaf
directions: Mix together beef, onion, green pepper, bread crumbs, salt, egg, ketchup, horseradish, mustard and milk; blend well.
Pack firmly into 9 1/2 x 5 1/4 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pan.
Spread ketchup over top of loaf.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: "shrimply delicious quiche"
directions: Chop shrimp (hold).
Saute mushrooms and onions in butter until tender, but not brown.
Beat eggs, half and half, salt and mustard in bowl until smooth.
Layer 1/2 shrimp, 1/2 mushroom mixture, and 1/2 of the Mozzarella into each pie shell.
Pour 1/2 of the egg mixture into each pie shell.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce to 300° and continue 30 minutes.
Let set for 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken. Remove from bones and cut into bite size pieces. Place in baking dish.
In saucepan, mix broth and soup. Bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken.
Mix margarine, flour, buttermilk and salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon over top of chicken.
Bake at 375° until crust is done.

title: dee's texas barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer all ingredients in a covered saucepan for 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Refrigerate after cool. Can be hot packed in sanitized hot canning jars or refrigerate up t 6 months. Excellent on chicken, venison or leftover beef or pork roast. Best the second day.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain the pineapple and mandarin oranges, reserving the juice from both.
In a large bowl, combine the juice with the pudding mix, stirring until smooth.
Add the canned fruit and the fresh fruit of your choice.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugars, shortening and eggs until light.
Add applesauce, mixing well.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder, salt and spices.
Stir well to blend; add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Alternately add water.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into well greased 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
If using glass pan, bake at 325°.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper. Combine sour cream, mayo and taco seasoning.
Assemble:
Spread bean dip on large shallow platter.
Top with avocado mixture; layer with sour cream, sprinkle with onions, olives and tomatoes.
Cover with cheese.
Serve chilled with a bowl of Tostitos chips.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix.
Chill at least 2 to 3 hours.

title: plain pound cake
directions: Blend margarine, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add Crisco, flavor and milk.
Add flour slowly.
Bake at 325°.

title: nut gingerbread
directions: Measure together flour, baking soda, salt and ginger.
Combine 1 1/2 cups brown sugar, molasses, butter and egg.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk to sugar and molasses mixture. Beat until well blended.
Pour into well-greased 8 or 9-inch baking pan.
Put remaining 1 1/2 cups of brown sugar and nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until crispy.
I usually bake mine 8 to 10 minutes.

title: remi's ambrosia
directions: Combine oranges, coconut, pineapple, cherries and sugar in a medium bowl.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: corn bread
directions: Blend all dry ingredients.
Add egg, Miracle Whip and milk. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cornmeal dumplings
directions: Cook in chicken or pork broth.

title: pop cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add pop alternately with flour. Fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites; add nuts.
Bake in 3 (8-inch) layer pans or loaf pan (10 x 14-inch) at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: 22 minute chocolate cake
directions: Don't use mixer!
Combine flour and sugar in a large bowl. In saucepan, combine and bring to a boil the next 4 ingredients (margarine, water, shortening and cocoa).
Pour over sugar/flour mixture.
Mix by hand.

title: ground venison casserole
directions: Brown ground venison, onion and garlic in oil.
Add salt and pepper.
Boil potatoes until tender.
Drain.

title: noodles
directions: Saute mushrooms and peppers until done.
Add seasonings.
Cook elbow noodles.
Add your favorite sauce and mix all together.

title: broiled chicken livers
directions: Drain and rinse livers.
Drain chestnuts; set aside.
Cut onion.
Take 1 strip of bacon and at one end place 1 liver, 1 water chestnut and wedge of onion.
Roll up and secure with a wooden toothpick.
Place on deep baking sheet and broil.
Turn at intervals for even cooking.
When bacon is done on the outside, livers will be done on the inside.
Place on paper towel, then onto serving plate.

title: harlequin mousse
directions: Dissolve each flavor of Jell-O in separate bowls with 1 1/2 cups of boiling water each.
Set until firm.
Cut in squares. Dissolve lemon gelatin.
Set until syrupy.
Whip until foamy. Fold in different flavor Jell-O squares.
Pour into angel cake pan.
Set in fridge overnight.
Unmold.
Frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.

title: coke roast
directions: In blue galvanized roaster, brown your roast on top and bottom.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top.
Add cream of mushroom soup and drained mushrooms.
Pour in the Classic Coke.
Bake 3 1/2 hours at 350°.
Remove roast from pan.
Add Wonder flour to make the gravy.

title: peanut crisp bars
directions: Heat sugar, margarine and corn syrup in saucepan until all are melted.
Add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Press into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan, then frost with chocolate chips, melted. Cut into squares.

title: flippo caesar salad
directions: Toss and head to refrigerator.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pepsi cake
directions: Mix together and set aside sugar and flour. Mix and bring to a boil the butter, cocoa and Pepsi.
Pour this over the flour and sugar mixture.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, vanilla and marshmallows.
Bake in a greased sheet cake pan at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Add a favorite icing.

title: quick baked beans
directions: Brown the bacon, onion and bell pepper in a skillet.
Add catsup, sugar, syrup and barbecue sauce; stir until well blended. Add pork and beans.
Stir and simmer over low heat for about 30 minutes.
Stir often to keep from burning.

title: crab spread
directions: Green onions and celery need to be chopped very fine. Crab can be chopped in a little larger piece.

title: langostino dip
directions: Melt butter and cheese in double boiler.
Then mix other ingredients and cover.
Stir frequently.
Pour into chafing dish. Serve with crackers or bread.

title: overnight chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in large casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove and mix well.
Top with Ritz crackers.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: anasazi beans and squaw bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Cut in shortening. Add milk and beat well. Makes soft dough. Roll out on floured surface, cut in slices and fry.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Blend at high speed for 3 minutes.
Pour in a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cheese blintzes
directions: Separate bread slices while still frozen.
Trim off outside edges of the bread (the bread will be thawing).
Roll each slice flat with rolling pin and cut in half, making 2 strips.
Spread each strip with the softened cream cheese.
Roll up jelly roll style.
(It will stick to itself.)
Dip into melted margarine. Then roll in the sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Good!

title: steak butter
directions: Soften butter and margarine.
Combine all ingredients in mixer or blender.
Keep refrigerated.
Yields 1 cup.

title: choklit chip brownies
directions: Get a meteum size boll and put all the ingretients in the boll. Ster it up and put them in the oven.
Set it for 6 minitse at 3 degrees.

title: tomato pie
directions: Flour tomatoes; season with salt and pepper and fry until brown.
Drain and set aside.
Bake pie shells as directed for 5 minutes.
Layer tomatoes, onions, Provolone and mushrooms. Combine eggs, Cheddar cheese and milk.
Pour into pie shells over tomatoes.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hot and spicy cider
directions: Pour into a two-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil and then let simmer on medium heat for about 20 minutes.
Strain and serve steaming hot in mugs.
Use cinnamon sticks as stirrers.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch dish with graham crackers.
Mix pudding, milk and vanilla until almost thick.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour over graham crackers and cover top with graham crackers.
Refrigerate while making icing.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch; add water, vinegar and salt. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add beets and butter and cook over low heat 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: easy apple crisp
directions: Place apples in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
With a fork, mix brown sugar, flour, oats, soft butter and cinnamon together.
Drop little clumps over apples until covered.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: never fail caramel corn(makes 2 shallow pans)
directions: Mix and boil brown sugar and white syrup.
Boil 8 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add soda and vanilla. Stir very good and then pour over popped corn and stir very good until all is coated. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn pans end for end and stir every 15 minutes.
Cool.
(Will not get sticky.)

title: coffee cake
directions: Defrost rolls.
Grease a tube pan and place nuts and raisins in bottom of pan.
Place rolls in large Ziploc bag with 1 to 2 tablespoons cinnamon.
Shake to cover each roll.
Arrange rolls over nuts and raisins in pan.
Sprinkle pudding mix (1/2 package) over rolls.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top of pudding mix and rolls. Pour melted butter over rolls.
Cover with towel and let sit overnight.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Grate or blend corn and add sugar, salt, pepper, flour, onion powder and melted butter.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Pour in greased baking dish and sprinkle with beef flavor granules, paprika and parsley flakes.
Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions, omitting any salt if desired.
Drain well.
Cool to room temperature.
Put in large bowl.
Add chicken, grapes, chestnuts or celery and mayonnaise. Toss gently.
Cover and chill.
Just before serving, add nuts and serve on lettuce.
Yields 6 servings.

title: he-man potatoes
directions: Melt in a pot over medium heat the cheeses, margarine and half and half.
Add salt and pepper.
Put frozen potatoes in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour cheese sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 8.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells according to directions.
Combine cheeses, crumbs, egg, parsley and salt; mix well.
Stuff shells generously.
Put in baking dish; cover with sauce.
Cook, uncovered, for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: nut cups
directions: Mix cream cheese, margarine, flour and salt.
Chill several hours.
Shape into balls and press into mini cupcake pan, like a pie crust.
Take beaten egg, melted margarine, brown sugar and nuts, mixing together.
Fill crusts with 1 teaspoon each of filling.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes before taking out of pan.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Saute onions, green pepper and garlic in oil until tender. Add tomatoes, water, salt, chili powder, thyme and bay leaves. Simmer about 1 1/2 hours.
While sauce is cooking, dredge chicken in the flour which has been seasoned with salt and pepper.
Brown chicken in deep fat (350°) approximately 10 to 15 minutes. Arrange in roasting pans and cover with sauce.
Place cover over pans and bake at 325°
for about 1 hour or until tender.
Yields 100 portions.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix items 2 through 5.
Add crackers.
Mix well.
Stir every few minutes until crackers are dry.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.
(Frozen strawberries may be added.)

title: caramel dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and brown sugar to taste.
Add nutmeg.
Add enough marshmallow cream to thicken to desired consistency.

title: five hour stew
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Put all ingredients, raw, into a large Dutch oven or casserole with tight fitting lid.
Bake, covered, 4 1/2 to 5 hours.
You can add a cup of frozen peas 5 minutes before serving.

title: polynesian sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients lightly, but well.
Form into 30 meatballs, using a rounded teaspoon.
Drain pineapple; reserve liquid; refrigerate pineapple.
Add water to reserved liquid to measure 3/4 cup.
Combine liquid with vinegar and next 3 ingredients in large skillet.
Heat to boil; add meatballs. Cover; simmer 15 to 20 minutes, or until meatballs are cooked. Stir occasionally.
Stir in drained pineapple.
Combine cornstarch and water; stir into meatballs.
Cook until sauce is thickened, stirring constantly.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix together in large bowl flour, sugar, oil, eggs, salt, orange juice, vanilla and baking powder.
Beat until smooth.
Mix apples, cinnamon and sugar.
Pour into a greased 10-inch tube pan as follows:
1 layer batter, 1 layer apples, batter, apples and repeat until all gone.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes or until golden brown on top and not gooey when checked with toothpick (oven 340°).

title: ramen noodle salad(serve lots)
directions: Shred cabbage, chop green onions and store together in Ziploc bags.
Will keep fresh for a couple of days.

title: creamy raspberry sipper
directions: Combine raspberries and grape juice in container of electric blender.
Cover and process until smooth.
Strain mixture through several layers of dampened cheesecloth, reserving liquid.

title: turkey rolls
directions: Cream the cheese and stir in the turkey and mushrooms.
Unroll the crescent dough and separate into 8 pieces.
Spread each with heaping teaspoonful of turkey mixture and roll into long rolls. Mix rosemary, onion and crumbs.
Seal edges of the rolls and dip in melted margarine and roll in crumbs.
Put on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot with cream sauce made by heating soup and water.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and cocoa.
Blend in eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Spread in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Be careful not to overbake.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Mix well the shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs.
Sift together the flour, tartar, soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture. Chill dough in refrigerator.
Bake dough into small balls.
Dip in sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Cut into 2-inch pieces then layer broccoli, soup, water chestnuts and onion until all used up.
End with broccoli.
Cook covered about 30 minutes at 350°.
You can use cheese on top of soup, if desired.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix water and sugar for syrup; boil 3 minutes and cool.
Put juice from lemons over mashed bananas.
Mix juices and bananas. Add cool syrup.
Freeze overnight until crunchy.
At serving time, add ginger ale.
Serves 30.

title: apple butter pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine filling ingredients in order given; pour into pie shell.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted two inches from center comes out clean.
Top with Streusel Topping.
Bake for additional 15 minutes.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Saute okra in shortening for 10 minutes or until okra appears dry, stirring constantly.
Add onion, garlic, salt, pepper and shrimp.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add water, tomatoes and bay leaves. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove bay leaves and add liquid hot pepper sauce.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mustard beans
directions: Cut the beans about 1-inch long; boil for 1/2 hour in salted water, then drain water.
To the vinegar, add sugar and other ingredients, except the flour.
Mix everything well; put on beans. Mix water and flour; put on beans.
Cook slowly.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Roll in small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while hot.
Repeat when cool.
Makes about 3 dozen.
Really good and easy.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Broil chicken; let cook and cut into pieces.
Combine chicken broth and soups.
Pour over chicken in baking dish.
Mix butter, milk and Bisquick mix and pour over chicken.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: old fashioned egg noodles
directions: Combine ingredients to make a stiff dough.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Roll dough very thin on a floured surface.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Roll up loosely; slice 1/4-inch wide and unroll.
Spread out.
Let dry 2 hours.
Store in covered container until needed.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Cook hamburger and drain fat; add barbecue sauce and stir to mix.
Grease muffin tins well.
Put biscuits in bottom and push up against the sides of the pan.
Top with 1/2 cup ground beef mixture.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: sausage and noodle dish
directions: Cook noodles until done.
Grease and flour baking dish.
Line dish or pan with sausage.
Put in noodles, pimento, onion and peppers.
Add cheese, salt and pepper, eggs, butter, milk and baking powder.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old fashion chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla in large mixing bowl. Beat until fluffy.
Add water, flour, cocoa, soda and salt; beat until smooth.
Bake 28 to 33 minutes at 350°.

title: pina colada party cake
directions: In saucepan, bring to a boil the sugar and pineapple juice. Using a fork, prick cake at 1/2-inch intervals and pour hot syrup over cake.
Let cake cool, and frost with frosting (add rum extract and rum).
Spread over cake and sprinkle with 1/2 cup toasted coconut.
Refrigerate.
Serve chilled.

title: therapeutic fruit juice
directions: Cut apple and place in blender bowl.
Cut pineapple and place in blender bowl.
Place banana in blender bowl.
Add almonds to blender bowl.
Add pumpkin seeds to blender bowl.
Add lemon juice.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients.
Add flour, coconut, apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: individual meat logs
directions: Combine all ingredients and form into logs 3-inches long by 1 1/2-inches thick.
Wrap each log in bacon and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add in all other ingredients.

title: cinnamon roll-ups
directions: Roll bread slices flat with a rolling pin. Mix cream cheese, egg yolk and 1/4 cup sugar. Spread about 1 tablespoon on each slice; roll up tightly. Mix remaining sugar and cinnamon in a shallow bowl. Brush roll-ups, including ends, with butter. Roll in sugar mixture to coat. Place on cookie sheet. Refrigerate or freeze at least 2 hours. (To store in freezer up to 2 months.)

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Beat egg; add sugar with 3 tablespoons flour to beaten egg. Gradually add milk, melted butter and vanilla.
Put coconut in the bottom of the unbaked pie shell.
Pour liquid ingredients over coconut.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; lower heat to 350° and bake 30 to 40 minutes, until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: hamburger goulash
directions: Brown meat in large skillet.
Drain.
Add celery and onions. Cook until soft.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, beans and corn.
Add spices.
Cook until blended.
Add macaroni.
Before serving, sprinkle with cheese.

title: baked eggplant slices
directions: In a bowl, combine mayonnaise, milk, lemon juice and salt. Season eggplant slices with additional salt; dip into mayonnaise mixture, then coat with crumbs.
Place eggplant slices on a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 or 30 minutes or until slices are crisp and hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: southwestern spoon bread
directions: Stir all ingredients, except last two, in mixing bowl.
Pour half batter in 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle green chillies and Cheddar cheese over batter.
Pour remaining batter over all.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes or until set.
Serve warm.

title: pumpkin 'n' spice tea bread
directions: Blend sugar and oil well with electric mixer.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, and continue beating until light.
Add pumpkin and blend.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and salt into creamed mixture.
Beat at low speed until blended.
Pour batter into greased pans and bake until lightly browned.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 15 minutes on wire rack. Remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: meat loaf with sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Pack lightly in 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in oven (350°) about 1 hour.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Slice the tops off the tomatoes and discard.
Using a spoon, remove the pulp and reserve.
Sprinkle the inside of each tomato shell with salt and pepper. Invert the shells onto paper towels and let drain for 20 minutes.

title: dog shampoo(non-edible)
directions: Mix all ingredients in a gallon jug and fill with water.
Shake well.
May leave concentrated if desired.
Use 1 to 2 tablespoons per dog shampoo.
More for lareger dogs may be necessary.

title: imperial salad freeze
directions: Mash bananas with fork.
Blend in other ingredients.
Pour into ice cube tray or salad mold.
Freeze until firm.
Cut in wedges and serve on salad greenery.
Serves 6.

title: "gorp"
directions: Add all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
Makes a great snack.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix well.
Put in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cover with wax paper. Place pan in larger pan with 1 to 2 inches of water.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 300°.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Cut in shortening. Dissolve yeast in warm water and add milk to dry ingredients. Mix well. Roll out in 1/4-inch dough and fold in half. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all together well.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes, covered. Mix the saved 1/2 of the cheese crackers with 4 ounces grated cheese.
Pour over casserole and bake, uncovered, 10 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Mix together all ingredients and chill.
When ready to eat, make a serving bowl out of the Hawaiian bread by cutting out the soft middle portion and filling crust with dip.
Cut the bread which has been scooped out into bite-sized cubes to dip in the spinach mixture.

title: taco burgers
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Shape into 12 oblong burgers.
Grill until done.
Serve, if desired, in taco shells or frankfurter rolls and top with shredded lettuce, grated Cheddar cheese and chopped tomatoes.

title: chicken dip
directions: Mix all together (except almonds) and put in microwave to melt cream cheese.
After it has melted add almonds.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichoke hearts and green chilies.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl and stir until mixed.
Place dip in an ovenproof serving dish and bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips or your favorite cracker.

title: gold-n-honey nut crunch bars
directions: Spray pan with vegetable spray.
Heat honey, margarine, brown sugar and cinnamon to boiling in a 3-quart saucepan.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Gradually fold in cereal until completely coated.
Fold in nuts.
Press mixture in pan with piece of waxed paper (it's sticky).
Let stand at least 1 hour.
Cut into bars.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat together margarine and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in 325° oven for 60 minutes.
Turn oven down to 300° and bake for 30 more minutes.

title: souperburgers
directions: In skillet, brown beef and cook onion until tender (use shortening if necessary); stir to separate meat.
Add soup and seasonings; simmer 5 to 10 minutes to blend flavors.
Stir often. Serve on buns.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: russian rye and dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill overnight.
When ready to serve, core out a large round loaf of Russian rye sourdough or pumpernickel bread.
Tear the cored bread in pieces to use for dipping.
Place bread with dip on platter and place extra bread around the outside.
Should serve 25 to 30 people.

title: lemon glaze cake
directions: Beat 2 to 3 minutes until smooth.
Pour into a 10-inch tube pan lined with waxed paper.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool and pour glaze over cake.

title: shortribs of beef(microwave)
directions: Arrange shortribs in 3-quart microproof casserole.
Add just enough hot broth to cover ribs.
Add onion and cover with casserole lid.
Cook on High 10 minutes.
Rearrange ribs.
Cook on 50% for 35 to 45 minutes or until meat is tender.
Let stand 5 minutes. "Precious things are without value to those who cannot prize them".

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together sugar and eggs.
Add oil, nuts and apples.
Stir until blended.
Sift dry ingredients and add a little at a time. Mix well.
Pour into a greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: miniature pizzas(kid recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Open biscuit can and flatten biscuits onto waxed paper and flour.
Flour hands also.
Allow children to place 1 tablespoon sauce on flattened biscuit.
Cover with cheese. Add desired toppings.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Pick up mini pizza with spatula and place on baking sheet (slightly greased). Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 450°.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix; let come to a boil.
Boil six minutes.
Add three packages of chocolate bits.
Add butter and stir in nuts.
Pour in greased pan.
Let set.

title: punch for a crowd
directions: Mix ingredients together and enjoy.

title: hurry up yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve dry yeast in warm water; mix in the Bisquick.
Add the melted butter and sugar.
Knead until smooth, about 20 times. Turn dough on well dusted surface and knead until smooth.
Shape into 12 pan rolls or crescent rolls.
Place pan of rolls on wire rack over a bowl of hot water and cover with a towel.
Let rise about an hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Brush with butter after baking.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Peel, slice and core zucchini.
Slice into 1/4 inch pieces. Cover with water and boil 5 minutes.
Drain well and mix in remaining ingredients.
Put in double pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Then bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: orange dump salad
directions: Place cottage cheese into a large bowl.
Dump dry jello over cheese and mix well.
Add fruits and mix.
Dump in Cool Whip and fold in well.
Place in container of choice.
Chill 1 hour or overnight.
This will keep well 3 to 4 days.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Cut up marshmallows and mix with pineapple.
Let mixture stand until it becomes soft.
Add finely chopped pecans, then whipped cream.
Chill before serving.
Serves 6.

title: veggie bar snack
directions: Spread crescent rolls into an 8 x 13 pan. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: four layer delight
directions: Mix flour and nuts together; melt oleo and pour into flour and nut mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Press into long pan and bake at 350° until brown, approximately 15 minutes; let cool. Blend cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip; spread on top crust.
Mix pudding and spread.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.
Let cool.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat eggs and combine with creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add half of dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Add milk and vanilla. Add rest of dry ingredients.
Cookies may be dropped or rolled 1/4-inch thick and cut.
Bake at 350° until delicately browned, approximately 10 minutes.

title: food for gods
directions: Blend butter and 1 cup of flour.
Pat into an 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 325°.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over partially baked bottom layer.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes more.
Cut into small bars.
Rich!!

title: brown butter sauce
directions: Brown butter in pan, stirring well.
Add seasoning.
Add about 1/2 pound cleaned shrimp.
Good on any fish.

title: chicken supreme
directions: The day before you want to serve, mix all ingredients together and place in a casserole dish.
Cover with foil; refrigerate overnight.
Remove 1 hour before baking.
Preheat oven for 10 minutes.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove foil the last 10 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes prior to serving.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: In large mixing bowl stir together all dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs, carrot, pineapple and vanilla.
Mix until all ingredients are moistened.
Beat with electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Note:
Large glass trifle bowl works well.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Grease and sugar Bundt or tube pan.
Mix together sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour 1/2 batter in pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 of sugar mixture.
Cut with knife.
Pour rest of batter in pan and sprinkle rest of sugar mix and cut again.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Boil noodles.
Add beef and spaghetti sauce.
Layer beef and sauce, cottage cheese, noodles, Mozzarella cheese, beef and sauce, cottage cheese, noodles and Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add garlic powder, hot sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: carrot-bran muffins
directions: In bowl, combine bran and buttermilk; let stand about 3 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
In mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Combine cereal-milk mixture, egg, carrot and oil.
Add all at once to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened (batter will be thick). Fill greased muffin pans 1/2 full.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 to 14 muffins.

title: "don't peek in pot" stew
directions: Place meat in heavy roaster with lid.
Pour soups and wine over meat and bake, covered, for 2 hours in 350° oven.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Water can be added before serving if it is too thick (1/2 cup).

title: mississippi caviar
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with corn chips that are made for scooping (example: Tostitos, Scoops).

title: earthquake cake
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put coconut and pecans in bottom of pan.
Make cake by directions on cake mix.
Pour cake batter over coconut and pecans in pan.
Beat the cream cheese and margarine well.
Drop cream cheese mixture by spoonfuls over cake batter and lightly spread over cake batter.
You can swirl it in batter with spoon or knife.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: banana-nut muffins
directions: Mix egg with bananas, oil, molasses and yogurt.
In another bowl, mix flour, wheat germ, pecans, baking soda, powder and cinnamon.
Mix two bowls of ingredients together.
Pour in liners of muffin pan.
Bake about 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: homemade vanilla flavoring
directions: Put whole beans into bottle and replace top.
Vanilla is ready to use in about 6 to 8 weeks.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar; set aside.
Combine butter, water, shortening, and cocoa.
Bring to a boil, remove from heat and add to flour/sugar:
Beat, add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla. Beat well.
Bake in oblong (13 x 9-1/2) baking pan at 325° until done.

title: potato soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook over medium heat for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Heat pineapple and sugar to boiling.
Dissolve jello in 1 1/2 cups cold water; add to hot mixture.
When cool and begins to thicken slightly, fold in cheese and whipped cream.
Turn into mold.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish.
Combine and put ingredients in casserole.
Bake at 350°.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco together.
Add sugar and mix well. Add eggs, one at a time, blending after each addition.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix as listed.
Drop by teaspoonful about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.
Yields about 5 dozen.

title: jello punch
directions: Bring sugar and water to boil.
Add jello, pineapple juice and extract.
Measure this amount and add 1 1/2 times of water.
Mix well and freeze.
Thaw from 4 to 6 hours before serving.
Makes about 2 gallons and serves 40.

title: individual pizza treats
directions: Power Level: Medium-High.
Cook Time: 2 to 3 minutes.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Melt margarine.
Crush 3/4 of Ritz crackers.
Form into crust in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole.
Mix broccoli and onion.
Place in crust.
Place 6 tablespoons margarine over broccoli.
Slice cheese and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Crush remaining crackers over casserole.
Bake additional 10 to 15 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Melt shortening in skillet.
Brown meat in shortening using salt and black pepper.
Combine all other ingredients; put on top of meat.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix well and roll into rounds about 2 inches in diameter. Refrigerate overnight.
Slice.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Heat 7-Up and dissolve red hots and Jell-O in 7-Up.
Let cool slightly and add applesauce.
Refrigerate overnight.
You may add nuts and marshmallows on top if desired.

title: punch
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and then add the orange sherbet.

title: basic cheese ball
directions: Blend all cheeses.
Add everything, except pecans.
Cover and refrigerate until firm.
Shape into large ball.
Roll in pecans.

title: chalupa casserole
directions: Brown onion and hamburger, then add seasoning mix and tomatoes, then beans.
Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer tortillas in pan.
Add 1/2 of the sauce and cheese.
Then layer more tortillas, sauce and cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Can be served with sour cream.

title: hamburger over rice
directions: Brown chop meat; break up in small pieces.
Drain any excess fat.
Add 1 can cream of mushroom soup (undiluted); stir.
Let simmer slowly while Minute rice is being prepared.
Serve over rice.

title: layered 24-hour salad
directions: In large salad bowl, place 3 cups lettuce.
Sprinkle about 4 tablespoons sugar and the salt over eggs.
Next layer in order peas, remaining lettuce, crumbled bacon and shredded cheese.
Spread mayonnaise over top and spread the chopped onions on top.
Be sure to seal by spreading the mayonnaise to the edge of bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap for 24 hours.
Toss and serve.

title: sour cream potato casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 400° for 1 hour. If desired, top with additional cheese.

title: mexican casserole bake
directions: In medium skillet, brown meat and stir until crumbly.
Drain fat.
Add taco spices and seasonings; blend well.
In small bowl, combine the broth and flour.
Add to meat mixture.
Bring to a boil to slightly thicken mixture.
Stir in sour cream and chilies. Blend well.
In 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish, place 1/2 of beef mixture, 1/2 of cheese and 1/2 of onions.
Layer again with remaining ingredients, ending with green onions.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix the first 6 items and spread on a jelly roll pan; chill well.
Cut in large serving squares.
Roll in flour and brown. These may be frozen until needed.
Use desired amount of pieces and bake 1 hour in diluted cream of mushroom soup with the Kitchen Bouquet.
Bake in a 350° oven.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in 9-inch square cake pan.
Beat with fork until smooth and creamy, about two minutes.
Scrape bottom and sides of pan with rubber spatula after one minute of beating. Spread batter evenly in pan; sprinkle with 1/2 cup semi-sweet chocolate pieces.
Arrange 9 to 12 walnut halves over top.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes or until done.

title: lempesis beef stew(for 6 servings)
directions: Saute onions; let brown. Add beef and saute. Add all ingredients to pot. Simmer on low for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: frozen peach salad
directions: For strawberry, substitute 2 cartons strawberries instead of peach.
Mix together and freeze.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until tender.
Cool, peel and mash until smooth.
Add sugar, butter, egg and spices.
Mix well until smooth.
Add cream, fold in well.
Place in prepared pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until middle test comes out clean.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix together and let set overnight.

title: pecos pasta
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Melt butter; add green pepper and onion.
Cook until tender (not brown).
Add chili, corn, seasoned salt and pepper.
Simmer on low heat for 5 minutes.
Stir in macaroni.
Top with shredded cheese.
Cover and cook on low for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Put frozen blackberries into the unbaked crust.
Pour some water over them.
Mix sugar and flour and distribute over the blackberries.
Dot with oleo.
Place crust over the top and perforate with paring knife.
Bake 45 minutes at 425° or until crust is golden brown.

title: sincere promus
directions: Stir together.
Put in hurricane glass.
Garnish with orange and cherry.

title: zucchini bisquick bake
directions: Mix all ingredients in order as listed in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: braunschweiger spread
directions: Blend all together the day before and serve on rye rounds.

title: celery casserole
directions: Preboil celery until tender in salted water; drain well.
Layer chestnuts, celery and celery soup in casserole dish.
Melt butter in pan; add almonds and brown.
Stir in cracker crumbs.
Spread over celery mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lunch meat sandwich spread
directions: Grind all the lunch meats together and mix with Miracle Whip; serve.
May use 1/4 cup shredded cheese.
Garnish with toast, lettuce and sliced tomatoes.

title: chicken chili
directions: Remove skin and bones from chicken breasts.

Dice chicken. In 5 quart Dutch oven or saucepot over high heat, in 2 tablespoons hot salad oil, cook chicken just until tender and it loses its pink color throughout, stirring quickly and frequently, about 2 to 3 minutes.
With slotted spoon, remove chicken to bowl.

title: hot mozzy
directions: Put everything in 1-quart greased casserole dish.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven until melted, up to 35 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: fried egg sandwich
directions: Place cooked egg on slice of toast.
Add onion and tomato slices.
Add Worcestershire Sauce.
Top with other slice of toast.

title: company vegetable casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well; pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: macadamia brittle
directions: Butter large baking sheet; set aside.
Cut nuts in half; set aside.
In 10-inch nonstick skillet, combine sugar with water and the corn syrup.
Over medium-high heat, cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown.
Stir in nuts; cook, stirring constantly until medium brown (do not burn mixture).
Remove from heat; quickly stir in butter and baking soda.
Pour onto prepared baking sheet.
Cool on pan or wire rack.
Break into pieces. Makes 4 1/2 cups.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar and cream until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time blending each until smooth.
Sift flour then add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla. Pour into a 12-inch tube pan and bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Allow to cool 10 minutes, then remove from pan to continue cooling.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, salt and vanilla.
Add soda and flour which has been sifted together.
Add bananas and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Combine rice and 2 cups milk in top of double boiler; cover and cook over hot water until rice is tender.
Add butter.
Beat eggs; mix in sugar, vanilla, salt and remaining milk.
Add hot rice mixture, mixing well.
Pour into buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes or until silver knife comes out clean when inserted.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: Grind all ingredients together.
Mix very well.
Add the sugar and mix again.
Store in tightly sealed container until ready to use.
Refrigerate or can be frozen.

title: pearl brown's chess cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together; press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix eggs, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and salt. Mix well.
Pour over first mixture in cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 12 to 16.
Tastes great!

title: macaroni with chickpeas and tomatoes
directions: Heat olive oil in heavy saucepan for 30 seconds.
Add garlic and cook 30 seconds.
Mix in tomatoes, parsley, basil and oregano. Bring to a boil and lower heat gently.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes until slightly thickened.
Stir in chickpeas.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine 1 stick melted margarine with hash browns, sour cream, soup, salt, pepper and cheese.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and cover with a mixture of corn flakes and 1/2 stick margarine.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: tiramisu
directions: In a large bowl whip cream to form soft peaks.
Gradually beat in sugar to form stiff peaks.
Fold in sour cream just to blend and set aside.

title: hot cocoa from scratch
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and salt together.
Blend to a smooth paste with the boiling water.
Bring to a boil and cook rapidly for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add rest of the liquid and heat over boiling water until scalding.
Whip with an egg beater for 1 minute.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: impossible mexican pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Brown beef and onion; put in pie plate.
Top with chilies and cheese.
Beat other ingredients until smooth.
Pour over meat.
Bake until brown 25 to 30 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: black cherry jello salad
directions: Mix 2 cups hot water in jello until dissolved, then pour juices into 2-cup container and add water to make 2 cups.
Add this to jello mixture; stir until well mixed.
Add pineapple, cherries and nuts.
Put in refrigerator and let jell until thick but not set.
Usually about 45 to 50 minutes depending on your refrigerator.
When it is thick, fold whipped cream or the thinned Cool Whip into the jello.
Be sure and get jello out of corners of bowl.
Can be made a beautiful dish with purple and white stripes on top, or maybe "swirls."
May add whole pecans on top. Cut in squares and serve on lettuce.
Makes 8 or 10 squares depending on size you cut them.
Great for company.

title: country style steak and gravy
directions: Coat steak in flour.
Brown the steak.
Put in crock-pot. Cover crock-pot with a piece of foil between lid.
Cook on low for 2 hours.
Prepare gravy and serve over steak.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine sugar, 1/2 cup light cream, salt and flour.
Add well beaten eggs; mix thoroughly.
Add water or milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook over hot water until thick and smooth, then add butter and beat well.
Remove from fire and add vanilla.
Let cool.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
This makes 2 small or 1 large pie.

title: all american meat loaf
directions: Combine meat and oats; mix all other ingredients and pour over meat and mix well.
Bake at 375°.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Marinate the chicken for 6 hours.
Put chicken on a cookie sheet and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour; add eggs.
Beat well.
Add milk and stir.
Cook in a double boiler, stirring often, until thickened. Add vanilla and butter; stir.
While pudding is hot, spread a layer of wafers and a layer of sliced bananas until pudding mixture is used.
Garnish with wafers.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix well and keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: potato candy
directions: Cook potato until it can be mashed fine.
Add vanilla until stiff enough to roll on board.
Sprinkle board with confectioners sugar and roll to thickness of pie dough.
Spread with peanut butter; roll up and cut in half-inch slices.
Place on greased plate to harden.

title: artichoke salad
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni and cool.
Drain artichokes, reserving the liquid.
Chop artichokes, green pepper and onion into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serves 6 to 8. Easy and elegant!

title: walnut drops
directions: Crush cornflakes to make 1 cup.
Beat egg whites, adding sugar gradually, until stiff and glossy.
Fold in salt, cocoa, vanilla, cornflakes and walnuts.
Drop tablespoons 2 inches apart on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: pasta con broccoli
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter.
Boil and drain noodles according to package directions.
Boil and drain broccoli according to package directions.
Combine all ingredients in mushroom mixture; heat to warm but do not boil.
Add garlic powder, salt and pepper as desired.
Serves 4.
Great to serve as leftovers.

title: sausage bread
directions: Flatten dough.
Grease a cookie sheet; brush on egg.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Spread sausage, pepper and Mozzarella on dough.
Roll and seal top and edge tight.
Brush remaining egg on loaf.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken la de da
directions: Put chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place cheese on each piece of chicken.
Mix soup with water and heat thoroughly; pour over cheese and chicken.
Melt oleo and mix with stuffing crumbs. Place on top of soup.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
This tastes better when made the day before and reheated before serving.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift
flour, baking powder and salt together.
Beat egg yolks and stir in the corn and flour mixture and pepper.	Fold in
salad oil.
Beat
egg
whites
until
stiff and fold into mixture. Heat shortening (1 inch deep) in skillet.
Drop corn batter
by tablespoon into hot shortening and fry until golden brown, turning once.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Combine
all
cheeses
with salad dressing, mixing well. Then add
remaining
ingredients,
mixing well, then roll into rolls. On
wax paper put paprika.
Then roll cheese rolls over paprika and roll up on same paper.
Keep in refrigerator until cold,
then slice.
It
is
better to leave it in refrigerator overnight.

title: spiced tea
directions: Blend together and store in a jar.
Use 3 heaping teaspoons in a cup of hot water.
Makes you feel warm! Best to double this recipe to make enough.

title: hashed brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, onions, butter, green pepper, cheese, celery and sour cream, salt and pepper to taste in bowl.
Mix well. Spoon into baking dish.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: summer pasta salad
directions: Combine Miracle Whip, cheese and milk.
Mix well.
Add all remaining ingredients except macaroni.
Cook macaroni as package directs, then drain and add to other mixture.
Chill.

title: quick garden cheese soup
directions: In a large kettle, cook celery and onions in butter until tender.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add water, then bouillon, pepper and vegetables.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add milk and cheese.
Cook and stir until cheese melts and soup is hot.
Do not boil!
Makes 2 quarts.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time to the mixture.
Mix
well.
Add
flour
alternately with Seven-Up soda, then add flavor.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: grilled chicken salad
directions: Grill, broil or pan-fry chicken until cooked through.
Slice crosswise.
Combine chicken and vegetables in large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in small bowl; mix well.
Pour over salad; mix gently.
Chill, occasionally stirring gently.
Stir gently and serve on lettuce-lined platter with additional picante sauce. Makes 4 servings.

title: patsy cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and put half of batter in bottom of pan and bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Melt package of caramels and 1/3 cup milk in double boiler.
Pour caramels, pecans and small package chocolate chips over cake.
Crumble rest of batter on top and bake 12 to 15 minutes more.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Mix remaining ingredients into sausage.
Pour into greased 9 x 11-inch dish. Cover and refrigerate 6 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: moroccan bean stew
directions: Soak beans overnight in 2 quarts of water or boil 2 minutes and allow to stand 1 hour; drain beans and place in Dutch oven or large, heavy pan.
Cover with orange juice and water.
Add bouillon cubes, onion, herbes, cinnamon and sausage.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 45 minutes or until beans are tender.
Remove from heat; stir in peas and cheese.
Serve with white, yellow or saffron rice.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Stir together stuffing mix and milk in large mixing bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes or until stuffing is softened.
Add egg, Worcestershire sauce, onion and salt.
Beat well.
Add ground beef.
Mix until combined.
Shape into loaf.
Place in greased or foil lined shallow baking pan.
Score loaf by making several diagonal grooves across top.
Fill with catsup.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until well browned.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion until beef is brown.
Stir in dry seasoning mix. Spread in pie plate; sprinkle with chilies.
Beat milk, eggs and Bisquick until smooth.
Pour over chilies.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package. Brown ground beef and drain. Add seasoning, onions, peppers, mushrooms and tomato sauce. Simmer 30 minutes. In a long casserole dish, put a layer of sauce, layer of noodles, then both cheeses (lightly). Keep layering to top of dish. The last layer should be sauce and then heavy cheese layer. Bake at 350° until cheese melts and is lightly brown (approximately 30 minutes).

title: beef spread
directions: Grind roast beef and nuts together.
Add pickle relish and enough mayonnaise to moisten and hold ingredients together.
Mix well.
Keeps well.
May be frozen.
Great with crackers or on finger sandwiches.

title: funfetti cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, oil and eggs.
Stir by hand until thoroughly moistened.
Stir in candy bits from cake mix.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Flatten to about 1/4-inch using bottom of glass dipped in flour.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes until light golden brown.
Cool 1 minute.
Spread frosting over warm cookies. Immediately sprinkle with sprinkles.
Store tightly.

title: gingerbread
directions: Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and cut into wedges 1/8-inch. Arrange wedges in a single layer in a 13 x 9-inch dish. Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well. Brush mix on potatoes. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes. Baste with mix occasionally while baking.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Then sprinkle on top 1/2 cup of each:
carrots, celery, broccoli, cauliflower, or any kind of your favorite vegetables.

title: raspberry cooler
directions: Cook raspberries for about 12 minutes in saucepan.
Strain through a sieve with wooden spoon.
Cool.
Add lemonade.
Stir, then add 2 quarts cold ginger ale.
Serve in glasses with crushed ice.

title: french dressing(for diabetics)
directions: Mix together and store in refrigerator.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Many ingredients may be substituted for ham.
Check your refrigerator for leftovers.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all together and chill to let flavors blend.
Serve with your favorite crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: granola
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Heat oil and honey (I do this in the microwave).
