Pour over dry mixture and stir until evenly mixed.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir two or three times while cooling to prevent sticking together.
When cool, add 1/2 cup raisins.
Store at room temperature.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Add amount of oats to make stiff.

title: cheesy french bread
directions: Combine cheese, mayonnaise, parsley and garlic powder, stirring well. Spread mixture on the cut sides of the bread. Put bread on a baking sheet; bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until the topping is melted and lightly browned.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Boil noodles 10
minutes or until done.
Flake tuna in a pot. Put cream of
mushroom soup and 1/2 can of water to tuna. Season as desired.
Let simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour sauce over noodles. Blend in
casserole
dish.
Slice bread and layer top of casserole.
Then layer
with
cheese and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: turkey soup
directions: Place turkey frame in a large cooking vessel.
Add leftovers and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a rolling boil; lower heat. Cover.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add 1 cup instant rice just before cutting off heat (for a thicker soup).
Yields 8 servings.

title: dip for raw vegetables
directions: Combine in blender; chill.

title: best ever banana bread
directions: In a large bowl, stir together the flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
In another mixing bowl, combine eggs, bananas, oil, buttermilk and vanilla; add to flour mixture, stirring until well combined.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: snow salad
directions: Combine cream cheese, pineapple, cherries, nuts and marshmallows. Mix well. Add Cool Whip. Mix well. Chill.

title: chicken or veal cordon bleu
directions: Have butcher bone breasts.
Flatten.
Cut in half if large or fold over.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place on each piece of chicken or veal 1 slice of cheese and ham a bit smaller than the chicken.
Now place the other 1/2 of meat on top and flatten to seal.
Dip in flour, then in egg and crumbs.
Saute in margarine. Turn when brown.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes on low heat each side. Handle carefully.
Serves 6.

title: italian meatballs and sauce
directions: Mix well; form into balls.
Prepare sauce.

title: creamy peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese at high speed until fluffy. Add thawed Cool Whip, peanut butter, sugar and milk. Beat well. Spoon into graham cracker crust.
Chill at least 5 hours before serving. Garnish with peanuts.

title: o's cole slaw
directions: Mix all the ingredients, adding salt according to taste.
You can garnish it with raisins and/or
apple slices.
Serve chilled.

title: lemon chicken with mushrooms
directions: Dredge chicken in flour.
In a 10-inch skillet, combine margarine and oil.
Heat until margarine is melted.
Add chicken; cook over medium high heat, turning once, until lightly browned, 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Place chicken on plate; set aside.
In same pan, mix mushrooms and garlic; saute until mushrooms are soft.
Sprinkle with rest of flour; stir to combine.
Stir in rest of ingredients and boil.
Simmer.
Return chicken to skillet and cook until heated through.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop popcorn and remove unpopped corn.
Mix brown sugar, syrup, salt and oleo.
Boil 5 minutes, then remove from heat.
Add vanilla and soda and stir quickly.
Pour over popcorn and mix well.
Put in cake pans and bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir 2 or 3 times.
When cool, store in airtight container.
May add raw Spanish peanuts before baking, if desired.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put sugar, butter, milk and vanilla in a large saucepan.
Stir and bring to a boil over medium heat; simmer for 10 minutes, stirring constantly to avoid sticking.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter until melted and marshmallow cream and stir.
Add nuts; pour into a large buttered baking dish.
Let cool.
Makes three pounds.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Making layers of broccoli, then chicken. Then another layer of broccoli and then chicken in a 9x13 baking pan.
In a seperate bowl mix remaining ingredients, then pour over chicken and broccoli. Sprinkle with bread crumbs (optional).
Bake at 350° for 30 min.

title: bell peppers stuffed with ham
directions: Wash and scoop out insides of peppers.
Drop in boiling water for approximately 5 to 10 minutes; then drain.
Mix together ground ham, tomatoes, onions, bread crumbs, as many eggs as needed, salt and pepper, potatoes and Worcestershire sauce.
Stuff peppers with this mixture.
Put mound of grated cheese on top of each pepper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or freeze for future use.
When heating frozen peppers, bake for approximately 15 minutes longer.

title: raspberry-orange slush
directions: Combine raspberries and orange juice. Combine until smooth. Strain mixture and discard seeds.
Combine raspberry mixture and 1/2 cup carbonated soda in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Cover and freeze 3 hours.
Remove from freezer and let stand 30 minutes. Add remaining 2 cups carbonated beverage.
Stir gently until slushy, breaking up frozen pieces with a spoon.
Serve!!
Makes 5 cups.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Press uncooked ground beef in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex casserole.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Slice potatoes (very thin) on meat, then slice onions over potatoes. Sprinkle grated cheese over onions and cover everything with mushroom soup. Cover with foil.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until potatoes are done.

title: grandmother's old-fashioned light bread or hot rolls
directions: In a big mixing bowl, put all ingredients except flour.
Stir in flour a little at a time until you have a stiff dough.
Rub a little grease or oil on top of dough.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until double in size (or about 2 hours).
Stir down and pour out on floured dough board.
Knead dough by working back and forth with hands.
Squeeze off dough to make rolls or loaves. Place in greased pan and let rise again (about 1 hour).
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Cream together butter and crisco; add sugar, cream, eggs one at a time.
Combine dry ingredients; add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for one hour and ten minutes.

title: mom's apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. In a saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar melts.
Cut shortening into flour until particles are like fine crumbs.
Add milk and stir with fork only until dough leaves the side of bowl. Turn onto lightly floured board on pastry cloth.
Knead just until smooth.
Roll dough into a large rectangle about 1/4-inch thick. Sprinkle cinnamon over fruit, then sprinkle apples evenly, over dough.
Roll up dough like a jelly roll.
Dampen the edge of the dough with a little water and seal.
Slice dough into about 16 slices, 1/2-inch thick.
Place in pan with melted butter.
Pour sugar syrup carefully around rolls (this looks like too much liquid, but crust will absorb it).
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes. Makes 8 servings.
This may be made with other fruit, frozen or canned.
If packed in liquid, drain and substitute for part of the sugar syrup.
Always use 2 cups of liquid.

title: banana split cake
directions: Vanilla wafers may be substituted for grahams, pineapple chunks or slices, well drained and put in blender for crushed pineapple and 1 large carton Cool Whip for Dream Whip.

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine squash, onions and salt in layers.
Top with ice cubes; let stand for 3 hours.
Drain and rinse in cold water. Combine squash mixture with other ingredients; heat to boiling point.
Reduce heat and simmer for 2 minutes.
Fill jars and seal. Process in hot water bath for 5 minutes.

title: sinful chocolate cake
directions: Rave reviews from my taste testers at work.
Chocolate drizzled over a caramel-pecan filling on a shortbread base.

title: chocolate revel bars
directions: Cream together oleo, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture with oatmeal.
In pan over low heat, cook sweetened condensed milk, chocolate chips and oleo until melted.
Add nuts, vanilla and salt.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Combine tomatoes, water and oregano; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in potatoes and sauce packet.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover top with pepperoni, then cheese and bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon pineapple pie
directions: Prick pie crust and bake about 15 minutes in 400° oven until brown.
Cool.
Stir together pineapple with juice, yogurt, pudding mix, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Stir in Cool Whip, just until blended.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour. Garnish with additional topping and canned pineapple slices if desired.

title: betty's chocolate almond pie
directions: Put chocolate bars, almonds, marshmallows, milk and salt in top of double boiler and melt over hot water.
Cool thoroughly. Whip cream until stiff and fold in.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Place croutons evenly in bottom of dish; sprinkle cheese over croutons.
In medium bowl, combine eggs, milk and seasonings; pour over croutons.
Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble. Sprinkle crumbled bacon over egg mixture.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until eggs are set.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: gumdrop cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add well beaten eggs, 2 cups flour, spices, soda and applesauce.
Sift remaining 2 cups flour over gumdrops, fruit and nut meats.
Mix this well and add to other mixture.
Bake for 2 hours at 300°.
For best results use a large tube pan.

title: bobbing apple punch bowl
directions: Heat cider, cloves, allspice, cinnamon and sugar to boiling. Cover and simmer 20 minutes (spices can be tied in cloth).
Stud oranges with whole cloves.
Strain punch and pour into punch bowl. Float oranges and apples in punch bowl.

title: stuffed flounder
directions: Cut a pocket on each side of backbone of fish.
Mix together the stuffing, crab and lemon juice.
Stuff the pockets with stuffing mixture.
Lay bacon strips on the stuffed pockets.
Bake at 350° in a well greased dish.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix butter and cheese.
Blend flour, salt, Rice Krispies and pepper.
Make in small balls and press out with fork.
(Makes 75 wafers.)
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: pork chop-scallop potato bake
directions: Salt and pepper the pork chops to taste; brown.
Mix potatoes and sauce mix.
Stir in pimento and liquid for water and milk. Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Place pork chops on top of potatoes in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Cook corn meal and water, stirring until begins to roll up. Remove from heat.
Add milk, oil and onion.
Stir until smooth. Add beaten eggs.
Blend dry ingredients.
Add to corn meal batter. Drop batter by teaspoons into hot fat.
Makes 24 to 30.

title: lime salad
directions: Boil all the water.
Stir in jello.
Put in cream cheese. Chill a little.
Put in pineapple and nuts. Stir together. Chill.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix and pour into large baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until light brown.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: In pot on low heat, mix orange juice, margarine and marshmallows. Stir until smooth.
Add cracker crumbs, chopped candied fruit and nuts.
Pour into a greased pan and chill.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Add onion and celery; saute until tender (5 to 8 minutes). Add the potatoes, water and salt. Cook until potatoes are tender; add chicken soup and milk. Bring to a boil and stir until broth is smooth. Ready to serve.

title: rice pizza
directions: Grease	a
12-inch
pizza
pan.
Mix cooked rice, sharp cheese and eggs real good.
Press mixture in pizza pan, making a
high ridge all way around pan. Cook sausage until brown and crumbly. Mix soup and oregano. Spread over crust. Arrange rest of ingredients
on
top, adding Parmesan on top. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: easy chili beans
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain excess fat.
Add beans, chili powder and enough ketchup to completely cover mixture.
Turn down to simmer and cook 30 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Shred lettuce into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle green pepper, celery and onion over lettuce.
Pour frozen peas on top of first 4 ingredients.
Mix the salad dressing and sugar together; pour over salad.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over the whole salad.
Let sit in refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: sweet noodle pudding *
directions: Boil and drain noodles.
Combine eggs, sugar (reserve 3 tablespoons), raisins and applesauce and mix into noodles.
Pour melted butter into casserole, reserving some for top.
Pour in noodle mixture.
Put apple slices on top and sprinkle with cinnamon, 3 tablespoons sugar and the remaining melted butter. Bake for 50 minutes, uncovered, at 375°.
Enjoy hot or cold.

title: fudgy chocolate torte
directions: Melt butter over low haet; stir in cocoa and 3/4 c. sugar. Blend until smooth.
Remove from heat and cool 5 minutes.
Blend in almonds and flour; beat in egg yolks one at a time.
Stir in water.

title: marvelous mustard ribs(makes 8 servings)
directions: In a small bowl, combine the sugar, pepper, paprika, curry powder and salt.
Rub over ribs, coating well.
Place ribs in shallow pan.
Cover and chill for 2 to 6 hours.
In a covered grill, arrange medium coals around drip pan.
Test for medium-low heat above pan.
Place ribs, fat side up, on grill rack over drip pan, but not over coals.
Lower grill hood.
Grill about 1 1/4 hours or until tender, turning once, and adding more coals as needed.

title: best barbecue sauce
directions: In saucepan, stir together corn syrup, ketchup, onion, vinegar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and boil gently 15 minutes to thicken.
Brush on meats or poultry, turning frequently, during last 20 minutes of cooking. Makes 2 cups.

title: chopped vegetable salad
directions: Chop broccoli, cauliflower, onions and celery.
Mix together with frozen peas.

title: crackers vegetable lasagna
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, add peppers, onion, zucchini and oregano.
Cook in butter until tender.
Spray 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Layer half of each crackers, vegetable mixture and cheese; repeat layers, ending with cheese.
In bowl, beat milk and Egg Beaters slightly.
Pour over cheese layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until knife comes out clean.

title: snowball salad
directions: Start with mashed bananas and lemon juice.
Add remaining ingredients, folding Cool Whip in last.
Freeze.
Can be frozen in individual muffin pan.

title: ma's molasses cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Last, add enough flour to roll out.
Cut in shapes and bake.

title: valentine days hidden hugs cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Remove wrappers from Hugs.
In large mixer bowl, beat butter, powdered sugar and vanilla until well blended. Add nuts and blend well.
Mold scant tablespoons dough around each Hug covering completely; shape into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set.
Cool slightly; roll into powdered sugar.
Cool completely before serving and roll into powdered sugar again, if desired.

title: harvard beets
directions: Blend sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Heat.
Add vinegar.
Mix. Cook on low heat until smooth; stir constantly.
Add butter, onion and beets.
Let heat for 20 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown peppers and onions in oil until tender.
Add ground beef.
Brown and drain off grease.
Add seasoning and mix well. Add tomato sauce, water, beans, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, Ro-Tel and chili powder.
Boil 10 minutes and stir.
Simmer several hours and let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: banana pralines sundaes
directions: Remove ice cream from freezer; let stand at room temperature to soften slightly (10 minutes).
In a 10-inch skillet over low heat, heat sugar and butter until melted, stirring frequently. Add raisins and bananas; cook 5 minutes or until fruit is heated through, gently turning fruit.
Spoon ice cream into four dessert dishes; top with banana mixture, sprinkle with pecans and serve immediately.

title: tilapia francaise
directions: Combine eggs, Parmesan cheese, 2 tablespoons cream and scallions; mix well. Heat 4 tablespoons oil and/or butter in saute pan. Coat fillets lightly in flour. Dip in egg mixture, back in flour and again in egg. Place in hot oil and cook until golden brown over medium heat, approximately 3 to 4 minutes per side. Keep fillets warm in oven.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Beat for 4 minutes. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: veal hot dish
directions: Cut up and brown the veal steak.
Chop up the onion and brown.
Add the celery, mushroom soup, chicken rice soup, water, mushroom pieces and rice.
Stir to mix.
Pour into 2-quart casserole and bake for 2 hours at 325°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Put sugar, milk, cocoa and butter in a large pan.
Heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on waxed paper.
Leave until cool.

title: orange stuff
directions: Mix jello with hot water.
Add pineapple and juice and mandarin orange juice.
Let set in refrigerator until hard.
Beat softened cream cheese.
Add jello mixture and beat.
Add Cool Whip and beat.
Fold in mandarin oranges; set until firm.

title: bell pepper relish
directions: Grind bell peppers, tomatoes and onions.
Let drain 30 minutes.
Add all ingredients together and add 1 pint of Miracle Whip salad dressing. Boil 10 minutes.
Put in jar and seal.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and meal. Add to beaten eggs. Add milk, margarine, lemon juice and rind. Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: potato corn bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 11 x 7-inch or 9-inch square pan. Cook bacon and crumble.
Reserve 1 tablespoon drippings and put in large saucepan; add green onion and green pepper, cook until tender.
Stir in corn, milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Cook until hot; remove.
Stir in potato flakes and sour cream until well blended.
Spoon into greased pan.
Top with bacon, cheese and green onions.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and set aside.
Cream shortening or butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, flour, salt, vanilla, buttermilk and soda.
Fold egg whites into mixture and bake at 350°
for about an hour.

title: pineapple pecan pie
directions: Cream butter, flour, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Blend in eggs and syrup.
Add pecans, pineapple and juice.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken confetti
directions: Cook spaghetti and set aside.
Cook chicken breast until it almost falls off the bone.
Cool and cut in small pieces.
Add soup and broth.
Using 4-quart casserole, combine chicken, spaghetti, soup broth and 1 cup of cheese.
Put 1/2 cup of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is completely melted.
Serves 4 very generous servings.

title: quick coconut cake
directions: Bake cake in 2 layer pans following directions on box.
Split each layer in half.
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut. Chill.
Reserve 1 cup sour cream mixture for frosting.
Spread remainder between layers.
Combine reserved sour cream mixture with Cool Whip.
Blend until smooth.
Spread on top and sides of cake.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator for 3 days before serving.

title: fruit delight
directions: Prepare Dream Whip as package directs.
Cream the cream cheese with sugar and vanilla.
Fold cream cheese into Dream Whip. Spread half of mixture in crust.
Place a layer of peaches, then remaining mixture.
Top with rest of peaches.
Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.
Chill at least 12 hours before serving.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a 9 x 11-inch dish, layer ingredients as given.
(The amount of celery and onions may be varied, but use 1 cup of mayonnaise and plenty of cheese and bacon.)

title: green bean rice casserole
directions: Cook green beans and season to taste with salt and butter. Drain beans (use liquid); add enough water to make 3/4 cup.
Add Minute rice.
Cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand several minutes.
Combine hot beans, rice and cheese.
Toss all together.

title: blueberry pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 12-inch pizza pan.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, 1 cup oats and 6 tablespoons butter at low speed until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup crumbs for topping.
To remaining crumbs, blend in egg.
Press in prepared pan.
Bake for 12 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach five minutes; drain.
Put a layer of spinach into a quart casserole dish.
Cover with sour cream that has been mixed with dry onion soup.
Put rest of spinach on this mixture. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until bubbles and cheese melts.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix Jell-O, pudding, water and 2 packages of Equal.
Cook until thickened, about 3 minutes.
Cool.
Then add the sliced berries and 2 packages of Equal.
Mix sliced berries with the jello mixture.
Pour in a graham cracker crust and chill several hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: diabetic's cake
directions: Mix eggs, sweetener and oil together. Add milk and vanilla. Beat well.
Add flour and beat well.
Add raisins and nuts.
Pour into rectangular pan. Bake for about 30 minutes at 350° until cake tests done.
Keep refrigerated.

title: corn spoon bread casserole
directions: Combine eggs, corn, cream and butter.
Blend in muffin mix. Spread in 9 x 13-inch glass or ceramic baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Makes 16 to 20 servings.

title: play dough
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Gradually add water and food coloring.
Knead well.

title: stained glass church windows
directions: Melt chocolate chips in butter or margarine (1/4 pound).
Cool thoroughly.
When cold, add marshmallows and chopped walnuts, blending gently.
Sprinkle flaked coconut lengthwise down middle of each of 3 pieces of wax paper.
Drop marshmallow mixture onto coconut; form into rolls.
Sprinkle coconut on top and sides. Wrap in wax paper, shaping into rolls.
Also wrap each roll in aluminum foil to hold shape.
Refrigerate for at least 24 hours. Remove wax paper; wrap in foil.
Store in refrigerator and cut slices as desired.

title: lime pineapple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pineapple and nuts, using a hand mixer.
Blend well.
Chill until fairly thick.
Mix in crushed pineapple and nuts.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks; gradually add sugar and beat until stiff peaks form and sugar is dissolved. Add drop of red or green food coloring if desired.
Spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Turn oven off.
Place cookies on center rack and forget them at least 2 hours or until oven is cold.
Do not open door.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen.

title: meat mixture for sandwiches
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in skillet, then add remaining ingredients.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes until cooked thoroughly and serve on buns.

title: tender pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops. Combine catsup and brown sugar. Add water and mix to make at least 1 1/2 cups liquid. Pour over the browned chops. Simmer in a covered skillet for about 2 hours or until liquid is thickened and pork chops are tender.

title: blizzard party mix
directions: In a large bowl, combine cereal, pretzels, peanuts and caramels. Microwave morsels in a medium microwave-safe bowl on Medium-high power for 1 minute. Stir. Microwave at additional 10 to 20 second intervals, stirring until smooth. Pour over cereal mixture. Stir to coat evenly. Spread mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan coated with nonstick cooking spray. Let stand for 20 to 30 minutes or until firm. Break into bite size pieces.

title: wiener and bean pot casserole
directions: Combine oleo, onions and garlic. Cook until onions are soft. Combine all ingredients in 3-quart casserole. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Stir once.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except 7-Up.
Add 7-Up just before serving.

title: microwave stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from caps.
Wash both.
Place caps on paper towel lined plate.
Microwave at 70% (Medium High) for 2 minutes. Drain.
Chop stems.
Microwave bacon at 100% (High) for 2 minutes. Drain.
Add chopped stems, salt and pepper.
Microwave for 2 minutes.
Blend in flour and milk.
Microwave at 70% until thickened, about 2 minutes.
Stir once during cooking.
Stir in cheese.
Fill caps with mixture.
Place mushrooms on plate. Microwave for 2 minutes or until bubbly.
Top with crisp bacon tidbit for garnish.
Serve warm.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter. Cook over medium-high heat until it boils. Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add Marshmallow Creme, pecans and peanut butter chips. Stir until melted. Add vanilla. Pour into buttered dish. Let cool; cut into squares.

title: quickie beef stew
directions: Drain vegetables, reserving liquid.
Combine flour and soup. Mix in large skillet.
Add water and reserved liquid to make 3 cups.
Stir into mixture in skillet.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in vegetables and beef. Cover over low heat, about 10 minutes or until done.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Reserve 2 teaspoons pimientos.
Mix all ingredients in medium bowl.
Spoon into a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese and reserved pimientos.
If making ahead, cover and refrigerate.

title: broccoli-chicken roll-ups
directions: Combine soups and milk and set aside.
Combine chicken, broccoli, 1 c. cheese, 1/2 can of onions, and 1/2 of soup mixture. Divide chicken mixture evenly over tortillas and roll up.
Place seam side down in a lightly greased rectangle baking dish.
Pour remaining soup mixture over tortillas.
Bake covered at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.
Top tortillas with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered for 5 minutes more.

title: mexican joes
directions: In small nonstick skillet, heat oil.
Add onion, pepper and garlic.
Saute until softened.
Stir in ground beef, tomato sauce and seasoning mix and cook over low heat until heated through, about 5 minutes.
To serve, place bottom half of each bun on individual plates.
Top each with half of the meat mixture. Sprinkle each portion with half of cheese, lettuce, tomato, sour cream and olive slices and top half of bun.
Makes 2 servings (1 each).

title: low calorie russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put 2 or 3 teaspoons mix in cup.
Add hot water and stir.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until done.
Mix all ingredients.
Place crumbled crackers on top for crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vidalia onion bake
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Boil rice in salted water 5 minutes. Drain.
Mix well with onions, cheese and cream.
Bake in greased casserole at 300° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: orange julius
directions: Simply syrup:
Equal parts sugar and water boiled until clear, then chilled.

title: smothered chicken(this dish is so easy and so good.)
directions: Rinse the chicken well, pat dry, then season the chicken with the soy sauce, salt and hot sauce and set aside.

In a large, high-walled skillet, heat the oil, then saute the onion, bell pepper and parsley over medium-high heat until the onion is clear. Add the wine and stir; add garlic and stir, then add the chicken. Mix everything together, then lower the heat to medium, cover and cook for at least 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
The chicken should be so tender that it falls apart.
Serve over cooked rice. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook large shells; rinse and drain.
Brown hamburg and onions; drain fat, then add seasonings, spinach, 1 cup of cheese and 1 cup of spaghetti sauce.
Mix well.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, soup, onion and cheese.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cut butter into pats and distribute evenly over potato mixture.
Crumble potato chips over top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: blueberry peach truffle
directions: In large bowl combine sweetened condensed milk, water and lemon juice; mix well.
Add pudding mix; beat until well blended. Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.

Spoon 2 cups pudding mixture into 4-quart glass serving bowl; top with half the cake cubes, the peaches, half the remaining pudding mixture, the remaining cake cubes, then the blueberries and remaining pudding mixture.
Spread to 1 inch of edge of bowl.
Chill at least 4 hours.

title: chicken dijon
directions: In a skillet, melt 1 tablespoon oleo.
Brown chicken breast halves.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Remove from skillet.
Add 1 tablespoon oleo.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Stir often.
Add soup, milk, mustard and parsley flakes.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover; cook over low heat for 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Serve with noodles.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: superb popping
directions: Measure corn and oil into a heavy-bottomed pan.
Cover and turn heat to medium.
Leave lid slightly ajar to allow steam to escape.
When popping has stopped, remove from heat.
Add salt and melted butter.

title: stir-fried oriental vegetables with chicken
directions: Combine soy sauce, sherry (or vinegar), cornstarch, sugar and salt in bowl.
Add chicken and marinate 10 to 15 minutes.
In 2 tablespoons oil, stir-fry vegetables 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove. Add 2 tablespoons oil and chicken, discarding marinade.
Stir-fry 3 to 5 minutes.
Add vegetables and stir-fry an additional 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Melt butter in skillet. Saut onion, celery and parsley until soft. Add oysters and cook until they begin to curl. Mix in thyme, crumbs, broth and beaten eggs.

title: blueberry surprise
directions: Crush graham crackers. Blend into soft margarine and 1/3 cup sugar.
Press into 2-quart baking dish.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Over medium heat, add refried beans and taco mix (add water according to directions on package). Stir well and simmer over low heat for 10 minutes with lid on skillet.
Pour meat mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer other ingredients as follows: sour cream, peppers, olives, onion, tomato and cheese.
Serve warm over nacho chips.

title: trisha's best sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and all wet ingredients.
Add dry ingredients. Blend.
Chill 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Make little balls of dough and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Press dough balls with bottom of glass (dip glass in flour so it won't stick).
Sprinkle with colored sugar.

title: an apple a day
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place apples in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Mix Bisquick, sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
Dot with butter.
Bake about 30 minutes or until apples are done. Serve with either milk or cream.
Also good topped with vanilla ice cream.

title: mom's oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Cream sugars and margarine until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, raisins and coconut.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cherry pie
directions: Drain cherries, reserving 1/2 cup juice.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and pinch of salt in saucepan.
Stir in reserved juice and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil; boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Stir in cherries and vanilla.
Cool.
Heat oven to 425°.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and top with unbaked pastry. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375°.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Mix together in balls the size of a dime.
Mash down flat. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Pour
half mixture into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex cake plate. Let set.
Leave
other half out.
Spread the mixture that has jelled with 1 cup sour cream.
Pour remaining mixture over and set again. Serve with whipped cream (not necessary).

title: sugarless brownies
directions: Sift flour before measuring; resift twice with baking powder and salt.
Melt chocolate and butter over hot water.
When cool, beat in eggs 1 at a time.
Beat in honey and rum or vanilla.
Stir in sifted ingredients.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until tested done.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cornmeal well with fork.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until smooth.
Beat by hand for 5 minutes. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: christmas cranberry waldorf salad
directions: Grind cranberries and combine with sugar and marshmallows. Cover and chill overnight.
Add apples, grapes and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream.

title: exotic chicken salad
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients, then combine the last 5 ingredients.
Toss both combinations together.
Season with salt and pepper, then chill.
Serves 8.

title: belgian endives au gratin(4 servings)
directions: Boil endives in salted water with a little lemon juice for 20 to 25 minutes.
Drain, forcing out all liquid.
Saute endives in butter, not browning them, just coloring them slightly.
Roll each endive in a slice of ham.
Put rolls in buttered baking dish. Cover with Bechamel sauce, in which the cheese has been melted and the white wine added.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and add dots of butter.
Brown under broiler.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Place chopped apples into pastry shell.
Combine flour, sugar and salt in a bowl.
Add sour cream, egg and vanilla.
Beat until smooth, then pour over apples.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.
Remove from oven and add topping.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Combine
flour,
baking powder, salt, cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add milk, stirring until well blended.
Turn dough out into a lightly floured surface; knead lightly
3 or 4 times, roll dough into an 18 x 12-inch pan, spread sausage at room temperature over dough leaving 1/2 inch
margin on	all
sides;
carefully roll dough lengthwise (jelly
roll fashion).
Pinch
seams
ends to seal, cover and refrigerate
at least 1 hour.
Slice dough in 1/4-inch slices. Bake 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: bark candy(diabetic recipe)
directions: Melt coating in microwave; stir until smooth.
Add cereal; blend until thoroughly coated.
Pour onto waxed paper and spread thinly.
Let stand until hardened.
Break into pieces and enjoy.

title: homemade chalk
directions: You will need a clean, smooth rock, 2 small dishes, a spoon and a strip of paper towel.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar gradually. Add eggs one at a time beating well after each. Add crushed wafers, milk, pecans and coconut. Mix well. Bake in a well greased angel food cake mold pan. Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thoroughly drain thawed spinach.
Squeeze to remove any excess moisture.
Chop with sharp knife through a few times.
Set aside in strainer.

title: cranberry centerpiece
directions: Fill snifter with the bag of whole cranberries.
Place green taper candle in the center of the cranberries.
The berries will hold the candle in place.
Tie a Christmas plaid ribbon around the stem of the brandy snifter.
Place a wreath of fresh evergreen sprigs around the base of the snifter.
Quick and pretty!

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion; season to taste.
Drain grease.
Spread meat in bottom of casserole dish.
Spread beans on top of meat.
Cover beans with cheese.
Mix corn bread according to directions.
Spread corn bread over casserole.
Bake until done at 350°.
Cut in squares.

title: baked pork chops & stuffing
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown chops in skillet over medium heat. (Add oil, if necessary to prevent sticking).
Meanwhile prepare stuffing mix.
Place chops in single layer in 2 to 2-1/2 quart casserole.	Top each chop with 1/6 of stuffing.
Combine 1/3 cup water and soup in skillet used for browning chops.	Pour over stuffing and chops.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour or until chops are tender.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Break lettuce in small pieces in large bowl.
Next break cauliflower in pieces and put atop of lettuce.
Cut onion in small pieces, put over cauliflower.
Cook bacon until crisp, cool and break into pieces.
Put over onion.
Sprinkle cheese (as much as you prefer).
Next, spread salad dressing in layer, sprinkle with sugar.
Cover and leave in refrigerator until ready to serve. Shake or stir salad before serving.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Fry onion in butter; add all ingredients except 1 cup of cheese and Fritos.
Alternate layers of chicken mix and Fritos; top with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese vegetable soup
directions: Saute in butter the carrots, celery, onion, cabbage and potatoes.
Add 5 cups of water.
Add boiled chicken and 3 chicken bouillon cubes or 1 pound cooked ground beef and 3 beef bouillon cubes.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add Velveeta and season to taste.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Prepare vegetables cheese and place in a large salad bowl with the beans.
Add beef.
Just before serving, pour on Catalina dressing and toss.
Serve with corn chips.

title: acini de pepe dessert
directions: Add macaroni, fruit and 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Chill overnight.

title: hungarian potato pepper stew
directions: You will need a 4-quart Dutch oven.

title: fugace (potato bread)
directions: Mix mashed potatoes and oil together.
Add yeast (mixed with warm water).
Add water as needed to make a nice soft dough.
Knead with knuckles dipped in oil.
Cover and let rise about one hour. Put dough in greased pan and let rise again about one hour.
Make finger holes on top of bread and spread oil over the top just to coat.
Place in a hot (350°) oven.
Cooks in one hour.
Bread must be well browned.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together. Shape into a ball. Spread on crackers.

title: orange cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix pineapple, cottage cheese and Jell-O in mixing bowl.
Add whipped topping and mix well, then fold in Mandarin oranges and refrigerate.

title: orange julius drink
directions: Blend in a heavy duty blender until the mixture thickens.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix sugar and margarine together until smooth.
Add egg and milk slowly.
Add flour and baking powder, mixing slowly.
Add blueberries and mix with spoon.
Put into 9 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut the elephant into bite-sized pieces.
This should take about two months.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over kerosene fire for about four weeks at 465°.
This will serve 3,802 people.
If more are expected, the two rabbits may be added, but do this only if necessary as most people do not like hare in their stew.

title: stuffed jalapeno peppers
directions: Mix tuna as usual.
Cut jalapeno peppers in half. Take out seeds.
Stuff peppers with tuna.
Lay baby shrimp on top.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours.

title: broccoli-cheddar cheese soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan over medium heat.
Add flour: cook and stir 30 seconds or until bubbly.
Add milk, salt, mustard, and cayenne pepper; bring to a simmer over high heat, stirring frequently.
Add broccoli and red pepper; return to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; simmer uncovered five minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter and vanilla.
Blend in sugar.
Form into small balls.
Melt chocolate and butter or Crisco in a double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture and place on wax paper. Top each ball with a pecan half.
Chill until set.
Makes about 125 balls.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in buttered casserole dish. Cook for 2 hours in a 325° oven. Since casserole ingredients are cold, start in a cold oven. To fill a 9 x 13 casserole dish, double the recipe.

title: pale pink wedding punch
directions: Mix first five	ingredients in large pitcher; cover and chill well.
When ready to serve, pour over ice in punch bowl. Pour ginger ale down side of bowl slowly so as not to lose the sparkle. Makes about 3 quarts.
Can be doubled.

title: oreo pie
directions: In a giant mixing bowl, allow ice cream to soften.
Add whipped topping and nuts.
Crumble 1 stack of Oreos into ice cream and set aside.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Beat the egg whites until stiff.
Combine the oil, sugar, egg yolks, milk, salt, baking powder and cracker crumbs; mix well. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift flour in mixing bowl.
Add to this 1/2 cup whip cream and 1 teaspoon Mazola oil.
Mix thoroughly.
Roll out onto floured board and cut into desired size.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.
Makes about 10 biscuits.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish. Add rice and soups. Cover. Bake 1
to 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.

title: coffee liqueur
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar and coffee.
Add boiling water, stirring to dissolve.
Cool completely.
Stir in pure grain alcohol and vanilla.
Pour mixture into bottles and close tightly.
Let stand in a dark place for at least 2 weeks before serving.
Yields about 16 cups of liqueur.

title: cauliflower and broccoli casserole
directions: Place cauliflower and broccoli in baking dish (I use the package that has carrots).
Stir in 1/4 cup sour cream, 1 can mushroom soup, 1 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Bake at
350° (preheated) for 20 to 25 minutes.
Take out and add 1/2 cup cheese and rest of the onions.
Bake for 10 more minutes.

title: creamy corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, salt, sugar and flour. Add beaten eggs and mix well. Add milk and butter and mix well. Pour into greased casserole dish. Place the dish in a pan of hot water and bake at 375° for 1 hour or until a knife comes out clean.

title: elegant scalloped corn
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in eggs, milk and butter, mixing well.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Garnish with parsley and pepper rings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour, milk, vanilla and butter. Cook until warm, then add eggs. Cook until it is thick. Add sliced bananas and mix.

title: fresh mushroom salad
directions: Combine mushrooms and onions.
Blend vinegar, oil and seasonings in blender.
Add cheese to mushroom/onion mixture. Pour dressing over salad.
Mix well.
Serve immediately. Delicious but does not keep well.

title: r t blue devil
directions: Blend with crushed ice.
Pour into cocktail glass.
Garnish with lemon twist.

title: cheese ball
directions: Shape into ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Spread on crackers.

title: awesome roast beef
directions: Place rump roast in a slow cooker.
Pour in condensed cream of mushroom soup and condensed beef broth.
Cook on low for about 8 hours.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix all together; work with hands until oil comes out of peanut butter.
Shape and refrigerate.

title: baked chicken sandwich
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and spread between slices of bread.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Beat eggs.
Add milk and salt.
Pour over sandwiches.
Let stand overnight.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Keep covered the first 35 minutes, then remove cover.
Sprinkle almonds over top and continue cooking, uncovered, the remaining 15 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice dish
directions: Saute onion and broccoli in margarine until real tender.
Heat soup, milk and Cheez Whiz in saucepan until cheese melts.
Pour over onions and broccoli.
Add dry rice to the entire mixture in a covered casserole dish.
Let stand until rice softens, about 20 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 10-inch pie plate.
Brown together 1 pound ground beef, chopped onion, salt and pepper. Spread beef mixture in pie plate.
Sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Mix together Bisquick mix, eggs and milk until smooth. Pour over meat mixture.
Bake about 35 minutes.
Done if knife inserted comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: b.b.q. beef brisket
directions: In small bowl combine liquid smoke, brown sugar, garlic powder, season salt, salt and pepper, mix well.

title: a unique cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese and thoroughly work it with your hands.
Shred one package of beef and work into cheese.
Shake Worcestershire sauce into cheese and mix.
Add garlic powder and mix; then onion powder and mix.
Shape into a large ball and wrap it with the other package of beef.
Chill and serve with small pieces of your favorite bread or crackers.

title: tuna-swiss pie
directions: Pierce pastry thoroughly with fork.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°, then remove.
In large bowl, stir together tuna, cheese and onions.
Spoon into pastry shell.
In a bowl, stir together remaining items and slowly pour over tuna mixture.
Bake for 60 minutes, or until knife in center comes out clean.

title: memory book cookies
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in pecans.
Shape dough into two 16-inch rolls; wrap in waxed paper and chill at least 4 hours.
Unwrap and cut into 1/3-inch slices; place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Yields 8 dozen.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put in casserole.

title: surprise
directions: Cut the first 3 ingredients together.
Put in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake until light brown.
Cool.
Mix the next 3 ingredients together; spread over crust.
Mix the pudding and milk; put over cheese layer.
Top with softened Cool Whip.

title: green rice
directions: Boil the 2 1/2 cups water.
Put rice in casserole dish.
Pour the water over rice and bake in the oven at 350° for 45 minutes. Saute onion in olive oil.
Add frozen spinach and minced garlic to pan and steam.
Add this to the rice, then add remaining ingredients.
Stir and bake an additional 45 minutes.

title: easy one-dish casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off grease.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Pour in casserole dish.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: crab quiche
directions: Mix mayonnaise, flour, eggs and milk.
Stir in crab, onion, parsley and cheese.
Spoon into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli-raisin salad
directions: Combine ingredients and refrigerate 2 hours in a serving bowl. Serves 4 to 6.

title: mommy's pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar together. Add one egg at a time and continue mixing. Add milk and flour a little at a time, alternating while continuing to mix. Add vanilla and lemon flavoring and mix well. Bake in tube pan 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Crumble up six slices of bread in a bowl; add water, egg, flavoring and butter.
Mix together until all ingredients are mixed finely.
Pour into a buttered pie pan; bake for 10 or 15 minutes.
Eat hot.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in their skins until done.
Chill overnight. Peel potatoes and grate into a large bowl.
In medium saucepan over low heat, combine butter and cheese.
Stir until melted. Remove from heat; blend in sour cream, onion, salt and pepper. Pour over the potatoes.
Mix and pour into 2-quart greased casserole.
Spread with remaining 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 45 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, apples, cornstarch and cinnamon; put in pie shell, then top with slices of butter.
Put top crust on and bake at 375° for 10 minutes, then at 325° until done.

title: grandma shirley's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter well.
Gradually add sugar and continue creaming. Add eggs and beat well.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients and vanilla.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: raisin and carrot salad
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil in a medium pan.
Add carrots and cook until tender, but still a little firm.
Drain and set aside.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Stir in sugar.
Add raisins and boil for 1 minute.
Return carrots to pan and cook for 2 minutes.
Stir often until carrots are tender.
Garnish with mint leaves.
Serves 4.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, raisins, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter.
Mix together the egg, buttermilk and baking soda.
Add second mixture to first and mix well.
Batter will be thick.
Put in greased loaf pan or 8-inch round cake pan. Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel pound cake
directions: Cream together the butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift the flour and baking powder together.
Add alternately with milk.
Add flavoring and nuts.
Put into a greased and floured tube pan; bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix the powdered sugar, orange juice, margarine and nuts with the vanilla wafers. Mix well. Form into small balls. Roll in coconut. Can be frozen.

title: baked fudge
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat sugar and eggs until mixture forms slowly dissolving ribbon when beaters are lifted.
Sift flour and cocoa into mixture and blend well.
Stir in melted butter, nuts and vanilla; do not overmix.
Spread batter evenly in an 8 x 10-inch baking pan.
Set into a larger pan; add enough boiling water to larger pan to come halfway up sides.
Bake until fudge is firm and knife inserted in center comes out moist but clean, about 1 hour.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.
Serve with whipped cream. Serves 8 to 10.

title: special chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts, debone and cut into pieces.
Place chicken in 7 x 11-inch buttered casserole dish.
Mix cream of chicken soup with sour cream and pour over chicken.
Crush 1 package of Ritz crackers and combine with poppy seed.
Sprinkle over soup mixture.
Melt margarine and pour over top.
Cook approximately 30 to 40 minutes until bubbly at 350°.

title: mom's butterscotch pie
directions: In medium saucepan, stir together the dry ingredients.
Add the milk, egg yolks and butter.
Combine well.
Cook and stir on medium heat until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir for 2 more minutes.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover surface with clear plastic wrap and cool on wire rack for 1/2 hour.
Keep covered until ready to serve.
Top with whipped cream.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix eggs and
shortening;
add
salt and soda together; set aside.
Mix flour and
spices.
Add
1/2 cup milk to flour mixture, then add flour mixture to the egg and shortening mix. Add molasses last.
Cook in iron skillet at 325° until done.

title: irish cream
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients.
Blend until smooth. Store in tightly covered container in refrigerator up to 1 month. Stir before serving.

title: grandma's irish soda bread(yield: 2 loaves)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 375°.

title: coconut joys
directions: Add powdered sugar and coconut to melted butter.
Mix.
Form into balls and make a small indentation on top of each.
Fill with melted chocolate.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Melt butter and saute onions and garlic.
In a large bowl, combine the 2 cheeses, sour cream and artichoke hearts.
Add butter mixture.
Scoop out bread (can toast part scooped out). Pour mixture into middle of bread.
Top with almonds.
Wrap foil around bread edges so it won't burn.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until bubbly.
Serve with bagel chips.

title: rice and spinach salad
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Cool in bowl slightly. Combine dressing, soy sauce and sugar.
Stir into warm rice and chill.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Top with walnuts.

title: honey french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Chill.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix together all ingredients and serve with tortilla chips.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain well.
Add all ingredients and mix with beater.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.
Can be cut into squares to serve.
Especially pretty for a lucheon.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in large container. Use 1/3 to 1/2 cup mixture and add hot water.

title: quick butterscotch cream cheese pie
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy; gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.

title: date roll candy
directions: Bring to boil sugar, corn syrup and milk.
Add chopped dates and cherries (whole).
Boil slowly to soft ball stage.
Add nuts and margarine.
Remove from heat and let thicken.
Set in cold water until cool.
Beat until thick.

title: wild turkey
directions: Brush bird with lemon butter and season with dry spices inside and out.
Place bird in roasting bag.
Pour juice into cavities and tie bag loosely.
Insert thermometer into meatiest part of thigh.
Bake at 225° until temperature reaches 180°.
The sweetness of the juices will affect the sweetness of gravy.

title: party pies
directions: Mix milk, pecans, lemon juice, Cool Whip and crushed pineapple together; pour into the pie crusts.
Refrigerate.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: peanut butter tandy cake
directions: Bake cake on cookie sheet for about 20 minutes or until done. Cool cake.
Soften peanut butter in microwave and spread over cake.
Set cake in refrigerator until cold, then melt chocolate in microwave and add teaspoon of Crisco to chocolate.
Stir well. Spread chocolate over cold cake.

title: peanut brittle(for an electric skillet only!)
directions: Place sugar in	cold
skillet.	Set temperature control at 400°.
Stir until sugar
melts.
As soon as sugar melts add peanuts.
Stir until
nuts	are
covered
with
candy mixture. Pour out into greased jelly roll pan.

title: reuben quiche
directions: Mix egg, milk, bread crumbs, onion, salt, pepper and mustard well.
Add sauerkraut, ground beef and corned beef.
Fill pie shells with first layer of meat mixture.
Then a layer of cheese, another layer of meat and final layer of cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: mock frosting
directions: Bring to boil to paste.
Let cool.
Add Crisco and sugar.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat 5 minutes.
Makes 2 cups.
Double for layer cake.

title: martha's chicken rolls
directions: Boil chicken until done and debone.
Reserve 1 cup broth.
Tear chicken into small bite size portions.
Flatten crescent rolls and put meat on wide end and roll up folding loose sides inward.
Place in baking dish.
Mix in bowl, both cans of soup, broth, cheese and milk.
Pour mixture over rolls.
Bake at 350° uncovered.

title: laggots or liver dumplings
directions: Grind liver and onion together.
Mix rest of ingredients and add to liver mixture.
Form into balls.
Place into a pan or kettle.
Add a small amount of water, some use beer.
Do not cover pan.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 1 hour, depending on size of meat balls.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Take meat off bones.
Cook rice as directed on package.
Boil eggs.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crush Town House crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Add 1/2 cup water and stir until meat crumbles.
Add 3 cups water and fresh vegetables.
Cook on low heat until carrots are tender.
Add tomatoes.
Cook 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in margarine in skillet.
Add oregano, salt, pepper and parsley.
Beat eggs and add to grated Mozzarella cheese (8 ounces).
Add to skillet and mix well.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground round.
Put into large pot.
Then saute green peppers, onions, parsley and garlic.
Brown in butter.
Place all into large pot with ground round, tomato soup, kidney beans, tomatoes, tomato juice, Chili-O mix, chili powder, olive oil, vinegar and salt and pepper to suit you.

title: beaten biscuits
directions: Sift sugar and salt with flour.
Blend in shortening and add just enough milk to make a very stiff dough.
Knead on floured board until dough becomes soft and pliable.
Run through a meat grinder or beat steadily with a wooden mallet for 30 minutes or until dough blisters, keeping edges turned in.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with biscuit cutter.
Prick with fork and bake in moderate (350°) oven for 30 minutes.
Should be a delicate ivory color.

title: rocky road pie
directions: Blend together graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar, butter or margarine and 1/2 cup nuts.
Press firmly against bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 8 minutes. Cool.

title: pecan delight pie
directions: Combine sugar and baking powder with stiffly beaten egg whites.
Fold in crushed crackers, pecans, dates and vanilla. Pour into greased 9-inch pie tin.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool.
Top with whipped cream and sprinkle with toasted pecans.

title: super seasoning salt
directions: Measure
all ingredients into blender and mix for about 30 seconds.
Store in tightly covered jar.
Use as an all-purpose seasoning.	Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: cocoa balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Bake on greased cookie sheet 10 minutes at 375°. Cool.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: low sugar pie
directions: Take 1 cup pineapple juice and the Jell-O and cook for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool, then add sweetener, cream cheese, pineapple and Cool Whip and mix together.
Pour into pie crusts and cool overnight in refrigerator.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients and set aside.
Beat eggs and add oil. Gradually add sugar, cocoa, melted butter and vanilla.
Add the flour mixture.
Fold in zucchini and nuts, if desired.
Divide into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350°
for 1 1/2 hours.

title: old-fashioned pickled okra
directions: Wash okra; pack into hot, clean jars.
Place 1 pepper pod and 1 clove garlic in each jar.
Heat vinegar, water and salt to boiling.
If desired, mustard seed and celery seed may be added to the vinegar mixture.
Pour hot vinegar over okra and seal.
Let stand 8 weeks before using. Makes 10 pints.

title: colorful cereal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar, margarine and eggs thoroughly.
Mix in flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt. Stir in cereal.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2-inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light browned.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: cinnamon waldorf salad
directions: Boil until melted, 1/4 cup of cinnamon candies and water.
Add apples to water mixture until pink (5 minutes).
Pour away water. Add to apples the rest of the ingredients; mix and chill.
Then serve.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add oil; mix very well with mixer.
Add eggs 1 at a time.
Beat thoroughly after each egg. Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) square pans.

title: german apple cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add sugar gradually until mixture is thick and creamy.
In small bowl, sift flour, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Add to other mixture and blend well, using a wooden spoon to blend.
Fold in apples and walnuts. Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake in 350° preheated oven for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: alma's cinnamon apples
directions: Boil together sugar, water, vinegar and candies until candies melt (keep stirring to prevent sticking).
Add peeled and quartered apples.
Use a variety that won't turn mushy when cooked.
Amount can vary, as long as liquid covers apples adequately.
Simmer until apples are tender and some are transparent appearing (usually 20 to 30 minutes).
Keep checking. Dip out into serving dish, adding some syrup.
Serve hot or cold.

title: baked chicken with chip beef and bacon
directions: Put chip beef on bottom of pan; wrap each piece of chicken with bacon.
Place on top of beef.
Pour sour cream mixed with the mushroom soup over chicken.
Bake at 325-350° for about 2 hours.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch glass casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
To prevent sticking, spray dish with Pam before baking.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook pepper and onion in butter until about done.
Add wieners; cook until done.
Add this to macaroni and cheese. Stir.
Very quick and easy dish when you don't have a lot of time.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs, whip.
Add zucchini and vanilla to mixture.
Then add dry ingredients.
Grease and flour two bread pans.
Pour mixture into both pans evenly.
Bake at 325 degrees for one hour.

title: holiday crackers
directions: Whisk together the first 5 ingredients.
Pour over crackers, stirring to coat.
Place in baking sheets and bake at 275° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 11 to 12 cups.

title: me-ma's picante sauce
directions: Mix tomatoes, peppers, onions and salt.
Let set 10 minutes. Mix all together and cook about 45 minutes.

title: skillet cabbage(contains 230 calories)
directions: Quarter the cabbage; trim off
and
discard
the core at the point of each quarter, then
cut the quarters into 1/8 inch thick slices; set aside.
Cook the
bacon
in
a
12 to 14-inch skillet over moderately high heat for 5 minutes or until crisp. Remove from
skillet
and drain
on
paper
towels.
To
bacon drippings in the skillet add
the
cabbage,
carrots, onion and the celery if used.
Cook uncovered, stirring occasionally over moderate heat for 5 to 7
minutes
or
until the vegetables are crisp-tender. Mix tomatoes; remove
the
skillet from the heat and season with sugar, salt and pepper.
Top with bacon.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Combine all ingredients, except eggs.
Simmer 8 minutes. Place the shelled eggs in a wide-mouthed 1 1/2-quart jar.
Strain in the hot vinegar.
Cover and chill in the refrigerator overnight before using.
The eggs will keep in the pickling solution for a week or more in the refrigerator.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix and pour into uncooked pie shell and cook at 300° until done.

title: orange muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine bread mix and next 5 ingredients. Stir 50 to 75 strokes by hand. Spoon into 12 large muffin cups that are sprayed with Pam or lined. Sprinkle with almonds and bake at 400° for 18 to 24 minutes or until golden brown and tested with toothpick for doneness.

title: fall apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in tube pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: sauteed cauliflower
directions: Break the cauliflower into small flowerets and cook or steam in unsalted water until just tender, 10 to 12 minutes; or cook frozen cauliflower according to directions on the package.
Drain. Combine and heat oil, thyme, vinegar and garlic in a large pan or skillet over moderate heat for 5 minutes.
Add drained cauliflower; sprinkle with pepper and stir gently.
Simmer until hot.
Sprinkle with parsley before serving.
Serves 4.

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain beets, add all ingredients.
Let set several hours or overnight.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze or chill in oblong pan.

title: sausage bread
directions: Let frozen bread thaw and raise.
Punch down and roll out very thin, no bubbles.
Meanwhile, cook sausage of your choice, breaking into small pieces and onion (diced).
Drain well.
Mix Cheddar cheese with sausage.
Spread over loaf.
Roll up jelly roll fashion and pinch together so it stays.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.
Brush top of roll with butter and a little garlic before baking.
Let partially cool before cutting.
Slice thin. Need to use large cookie sheet.
Good for card parties, etc.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Melt butter; pour it in the flour, baking soda and salt.
Pour into greased pan (butter bottom of pan).
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: round steak deluxe
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour over serving sized pieces of steak which have been browned.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons flour.
Bake covered in 350° oven for 2 hours.
Easy and delicious!

title: watermellon cake
directions: Soak raisins in boiling water for 15 minutes, then drain well. Dust with flour and set aside.
Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, water and vanilla.
Add flour and baking powder.
Add a few drops of coloring to make the mixture pink. Fold in raisins.
Pour the batter into greased floured pans.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Soak beans overnight (water to cover).
Boil beans until they are soft with the salt and butter (remove garlic).
Put beans in a baking dish with the remaining water.
Sprinkle with brown sugar; cover top with strips of bacon.
Bake in slow oven at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: father whitcombs mustard
directions: Mix together dry mustard and vinegar and let stand overnight in nonmetal container. Add remaining ingredients. Cook in nonmetal double boiler until thick, about the consistency of honey. Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soups, onion, green chilies and water chestnuts together.
Fry tortillas, 3 seconds per side, in hot oil.

title: chicken and dumplings(texas style)
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Remove from broth.
Add celery, onion, garlic, salt and pepper to broth.
Debone chicken; cut into pieces and return to broth.
Tear flour tortillas into pieces and drop into chicken and broth while cooking.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, egg, bread crumbs and 1 cup salsa.
Pat into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 45 minutes.
Spoon remaining salsa over loaf.
Continue baking for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over crumbs.
Top with chocolate chips, nuts and coconut.
Press down gently.

title: pine-ana torte(pineapple banana torte)
directions: Mix gingerbread mix according to directions.
Bake in a 9-inch spring-form pan; cool.
Split in half crosswise with thread. Place bottom half on cake plate.
Whip cream with vanilla and sugar.
Spread the bottom layer with half of whipped cream. Arrange banana slices around outside edge and fill center with 3/4 cup pineapple.
Put second layer; spread with rest of whipped cream.
Sprinkle nuts around outside edge and fill center with rest of pineapple.
Chill.

title: budget beef burgundy
directions: Cut roast into 1 1/2 to 2-inch cubes, trimming and discarding visible fat.
In brown paper or plastic bag, combine flour, garlic, salt (if desired) and pepper; add meat and shake to coat evenly. In heavy Dutch oven over medium-high heat, heat oil.
In batches, brown cubed beef on all sides.
As browned, remove meat and set aside.
Remove and discard all but 2 tablespoons pan drippings. Add mushrooms and onions; saute about 5 minutes.
Stir in wine, broth and herbs.
Return meat to pot; bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer until meat is fork-tender, about 2 hours. Stir in peas.
Delicious served with wide egg noodles or rice; sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 8 servings.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Make sauce from rhubarb and sugar.
Add jello and refrigerate. Keeps for a long time.
It is really good.

title: jumbo seafood shells
directions: Add shells gradually to 6 qt. boiling water, salted.
Cook until tender but firm.
Drain; rinse with cold water.
Drain again.
Place on a towel-lined plate to cool.
Combine crabmeat, shrimp, cheese, mayo, celery and onion in a medium bowl.
If the mixture is too dry, add more mayo.
Spoon mixture into cooled shells.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: "yum-yum" cake
directions: *Follow directions on box for mixing.

title: raw vegetable dip(this is especially good with raw zucchini)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let sit for 1 hour refrigerated before serving.

title: onion casserole(an onion lover's delight)
directions: Peel and slice onions into thirds.
Saute for 25 minutes in butter.
Cut Swiss cheese into cubes.
Add cheese, mushroom soup and soy sauce to onions.
Put into casserole dish.
Slice French bread thick; cut in halves.
Arrange on top of onions and sauce. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serves 6.

title: easy ice cream pie
directions: Mix milk and pudding; blend in softened ice cream.
Pour into crust; spread on whipped topping.
Refrigerate.
Sprinkle crushed Heath bar on top before serving.
Pies can be frozen.

title: quick lasagna toss
directions: Cook the noodles according to the package directions; drain. Meanwhile, in a soup pot, cook the sausage over medium-high heat for 6 to 8 minutes, or until no pink remains, stirring to crumble the sausage; drain.
Add the noodles and the remaining ingredients; mix well.
Reduce the heat to medium-low and cook for 6 to 8 minutes, or until heated through and the cheese is melted. Serve immediately.

title: candied yams
directions: Put margarine on bottom of heavy saucepan.
Cover with sliced yams; top with brown sugar.
Cover pan and bring ingredients to a slow boil.
Reduce heat to simmer until yams are soft.
Great for holiday dinners.

title: diabetic cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients together and blend well.
Pour ingredients in greased baking pan.
Place in 400° oven and bake approximately 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and enjoy.

title: swimmer's energy drink
directions: Mix milk, egg, honey and vanilla in blender until frothy.
Add banana and unthawed strawberries.
Mix until thick.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream the sugar, butter and eggs.
Heat applesauce.
Flour raisins and nuts in some of the flour before adding to cake.
Bake in a 350° oven.
This makes 2 large layers or 1 large Bundt cake.

title: fast fiesta shepherd's pie
directions: Cook beef in skillet until browned. Pour off fat. Stir in tomato soup, corn, picante sauce, cumin, basil and garlic. Heat to a boil. Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes. Mix cheese soup, milk and butter in saucepan. Heat to a boil. Remove from heat. Stir in potato flakes. Let stand 30 seconds. Mix with fork until evenly moistened. Drop potatoes by large spoonfuls onto beef mixture. Serves 4.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into ball.
Roll in crushed nuts.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken, pork, beef and potatoes.
Combine everything in large pot and simmer for 8 hours.

title: party ryes
directions: Mix mayonnaise, cheese, chopped onion and milk.
Spread on party rye slices.
Place under broiler until light gold in color. Serve.

title: baked swiss steak
directions: Trim fat from steak; cut into serving size pieces.
Pound flour into both sides of steak.
Heat fat in skillet; brown steak on both sides.
Season with 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Place a single layer in baking dish.
Cover with onion slices.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread uncooked ground beef in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut onion.
Place on hamburger.
Mix soups; spread on onion.
Place Tater Tots on top.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco with electric mixer.
Now add eggs one at a time.
You are to beat well after each egg (mix well).
Add flour, milk, salt, vanilla, coloring and baking powder.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.
Bake in cake pan.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat egg and sugar; add
oil,
soda, cinnamon, salt and baking powder.
Add flour, carrot,
pecan
and
raisins;	put pineapple with the juice.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 1 hour.

title: whit's beef jerky
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add meat.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Arrange beef strips on racks in dehydrator.
Dry on high for six to eight hours.
May arrange beef on foil covered oven racks.
Bake with oven door ajar at 200° for six or eight hours or until dry.
Store in tightly covered container.
This recipe will serve 6 people.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add beaten eggs, continue beating until creamy.
Crumble the mincemeat and mix until mincemeat is dissolved.
Add soda and salt; mix well.
Add flour; mix well. Add pecans.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen (3-inch) cookies.

title: sour cream lasagna
directions: Cook
noodles
and
drain.
Brown
meat, stir in tomato sauce, salt,
pepper
and
garlic
salt.	Simmer	5
minutes. Combine sour
cream, cottage cheese and chopped green onions. Layer noodles,
then meat mixture, then cheese mixture twice. Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 8.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar and water in large pan.
Bring to a boil and add milk.
Boil over low heat until mixture will form a firm ball when tested in cold water.
Stir mixture constantly to prevent burning. Remove from heat and add chocolate.
Beat until thick and creamy. Pour into buttered pan or dish to cool.

title: quick brownies
directions: Mix together butter, sugar, egg and cocoa.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add vanilla.
Grease 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: scallops with linguine
directions: Heat butter.
Saute scallops; remove from pan.
Add wine, broth and lemon juice.
Reduce to 1/2, then add parsley, dill and scallions.
Simmer 1 minute.
Add scallops; serve over cooked linguine.
Pass the grated cheese.

title: microwavable sloppy joes(serves 6; microwave time: 15 minutes)
directions: Place in a microwave-safe container the beef and onion; cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on High for 4 to 6 minutes; drain fat.
Place meat mixture in 2-quart casserole.
Add soup, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Microcook on High for 3 to 5 minutes; stir twice.
Serve on bread or buns of your choice.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add flour, eggs, milk and vanilla. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Preheat oven at 450°, then bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Combine ingredients for crust and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 5 minutes.
Let crust cool.

title: turtle cake
directions: Add 1/2 cup evaporated milk to the prepared cake mix.
Pour half of the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Microwave the package of caramels and the remainder of the milk in a small dish.
Pour over the baked cake; sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour remaining batter over all and bake 10 to 15 minutes.
No icing needed.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Reserve 1/3 cup of the Blue cheese.
In small mixer bowl, blend remaining Blue cheese and cream cheese on low speed.
Beat in mayonnaise and cream on medium speed until creamy.
Stir in reserved Blue cheese.
Cover; refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: chili beans
directions: Cut roast into small pieces.
Put all ingredients into crock-pot; cook all day or overnight.
After cooking for 3 hours, add 8 ounces of tomato sauce.

title: pot roast sandwiches
directions: Place all ingredients in roaster for 6 to 7 hours at 325° covered.
You may also use a crock-pot on low for 5 to 6 hours.

title: chili mac
directions: Saute
ground chuck, onions and green peppers over high heat until
light
brown.
Add water and seasonings in a large Dutch oven.
Boil
the macaroni for 6 minutes, then add to the pot and simmer
for 2 hours. Serve with crackers or cornbread and a green salad.

title: calzones(inside-out pizza)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Squeeze the insides out of sausage and brown.
Simmer tomato sauce, tomato paste, Italian seasoning and garlic while preparing rest.
Make dough mix and let rise.
Cut mushrooms, olives and onions.
Make 8-inch rounds with the dough. Put meat, sauce, vegetables and cheese on 1 side of round.
Fold over and press edges together.
Bake until golden brown.

title: chocolate pie filling
directions: Stir together sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Blend milk and egg yolks; stir into sugar mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla; stir. Immediately pour into baked pie shell.

title: spicy dog bites
directions: Cut each hot dog crosswise into 5 or 6 pieces.
Place a small saucepan on low heat and add jelly, chili sauce, mustard and onion.
Stir until jelly melts.
Put hot dogs in hot sauce and simmer approximately 1 hour.
Serve warm.
Makes 50 to 60 servings.

title: crab boil
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, seasoning packs, salt and pepper in large stock pot.
Fill the pot 2/3 full with water.
Cook on top of stove on medium-high until potatoes are nearly done.
Add live Blue crabs; cover and allow to boil for about 15 minutes.
Cut off heat and allow pot to steep for 15 minutes.
Serves up to 8 people.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt white chocolate and chocolate chips.
Add peanuts.
Drop by the teaspoonfuls onto wax paper or aluminum foil.
Let harden, then refrigerate.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Cool, then add the 7-Up.
Let set until slightly thickened.
Add the pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Let this set overnight in refrigerator.

title: easy lemon bars
directions: Combine cake mix, one egg and margarine.
Press into 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar, lemon extract and 3 eggs.
Beat well.
Pour over dough layer.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Cool overnight.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Melt
butter in heavy
saucepan.
Add
flour,
stirring until well blended.
Gradually add milk and cook over low heat until thickened.	Add salt and pepper.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together and put in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: rhubarb strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix with rhubarb and strawberries.
Put in a 9-inch crust.
Cover with top crust.
Cut slits in crust to let steam escape.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sugar and eggless fruit cake
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Put milk in top of double boiler; add marshmallows and heat until marshmallows are melted.
Drain cherries; cut in halves and add all the fruit and nuts to the crushed crackers.
Pour the milk and marshmallow mixture over the cracker mixture.
This is really an icebox cake but I baked mine one hour in a slow oven (250°) as it gives the nut meats a toasted flavor.
Be sure to mix well and bake in a greased, paper lined loaf pan.

title: ham and macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni following label directions; drain well.
Cool. Combine macaroni, ham, green peppers and onion in large bowl.
Add mayonnaise, salt and pepper; toss to mix.
Chill well.
