Just before serving, halve 1 cup cherry tomatoes.
Add to salad.
Toss lightly to mix.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Cut sirloin or round steak into 2 x 3/4 x 3/8-inch strips, cutting across the grain.
It is best to put meat in the freezer until firm before cutting.
Brown meat in large skillet in butter. Add onion.
Cook until limp.
Stir in gravy, red wine and tomato paste.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 10 to 20 minutes or until meat is tender.
Remove from heat and let stand for 10 minutes.
Slowly stir in sour cream.
Serve over hot noodles.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour in crust and chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: mushroom dip
directions: Let cream cheese sit out until softened (room temperature). In a medium size bowl, combine all ingredients.
Using a mixer, mix until creamy (it will have lumps from the mushrooms).
Chill in the refrigerator for 1 hour.
Good as vegetable or chip dip.

title: fudgy bonbons
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, combine chocolate chips and butter.
Cook and stir over very low heat until chips are melted and smooth.
Add sweetened condensed milk.
Mix well. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup and level off.
In medium bowl, combine flour, nuts, chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Mix well.
Shape 1 tablespoonful (use measuring spoon) of dough around each candy Kiss, covering completely.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes. Cookies will be soft and appear shiny, but become firm as they cool.
Do not overbake.
Remove from cookie sheets; cool.
In small saucepan, combine white baking bar and oil.
Cook and stir over low heat until melted and smooth.
Drizzle over cookies. Store in tightly covered container.
Yield:
5 dozen cookies.

title: oreo cookie ice cream dessert
directions: Crush cookies (save some to sprinkle on top). Mix remaining ingredients well with softened ice cream. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Freeze overnight. Sprinkle crushed cookies on top. Cut in squares and serve. May top each one with Cool Whip and a cherry.

title: mushroom sandwiches
directions: Put cheese through meat grinder.
Combine with mustard, Worcestershire sauce, eggs, salt and pepper.
Spread on bread slices and scatter diced bacon on top of spread.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes or until browned on under side.
Cut in halves or quarters, as desired and serve hot.
Yields 13 or more servings.

title: bacon deviled eggs
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain.
Crumble and return to same pan.
Add chili sauce and mix until warm.
Cut boiled eggs in half and spoon small amount of sauce on top of each egg.
Serve warm or cold.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour the boiling water over the bran cereal, margarine and sugar. Stir and cool. Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix and store in refrigerator in covered container until ready to bake.

title: thanksgiving salad
directions: Mix all the fruits together or layer them in a clear glass bowl.
Serve without dressing.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: sausage and eggs
directions: Brown and scramble sausage.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line bottom with trimmed bread slices.
Spoon sausage over bread. Sprinkle with grated onion and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings in blender.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour beef
directions: Brown meat in the oil in a Dutch oven.
Add the next six ingredients, plus 1/2 cup water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cover and cook over low heat until meat is tender (approximately 2 hours). Add cornstarch to 1/4 cup water.
Add to beef.
Stir and cook until thick and bubbly.
Serve over noodles.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Gather 6 to 10 beans in bundles; wrap 1/2 piece of bacon around center of each bundle. Place bundles in baking dish. Sprinkle bundles with garlic salt. Pour melted butter over bundles. Sprinkle with brown sugar. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bacon is done. Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Scald milk in double boiler.
Add sugar, salt and cocoa; blend well and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour a small amount over egg yolks, stirring constantly, then add to chocolate mixture.
Cook until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Place into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and brown.

title: french toast puffs
directions: Mix egg, sugar and vanilla in medium size bowl.
Add milk and blend until smooth.
Slowly add flour and baking powder until smooth.
Dip half slices of bread in batter.
Deep-fry in at least 2 inches of oil at 375° until brown on both sides.
Serve as you would pancakes or French toast.

title: brown rice with mushrooms
directions: Melt butter in a skillet.
Add onion and rice and brown.
Pour into a big casserole dish.
Add soup and bouillon.
Bake at 375° until done.
Cook for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk and bread crumbs to soften.
Add all other ingredients, except asparagus, to the bread mixture and mix well. Fold asparagus into bread mixture.
Bake in a greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish at 325° for 35 minutes, covered.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer until casserole begins to brown.

title: pea salad
directions: Make several hours ahead of time and refrigerate.

title: honey butter
directions: Mix butter and honey in small bowl until well blended.
Serve on toast.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until done, drain.
Saute hamburger, add all ingredients.
Stir.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: green chile cheese corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl and stir just until flour is moistened.
Batter should be lumpy.
Spread evenly in a loaf pan sprayed with nonfat cooking spray.
Bake 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Beat sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Melt margarine and chocolate over low heat.
Cool.
Stir in sugar and egg mixture.
Mix well. Add vanilla.
Put into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: best ever seafood paella
directions: Wash prawns, slit down back with scissors and remove sandy vein, set aside. Scrub and beard mussels, discard any that aren't firmly closed.
Put in pot with little water, steam for about 10 minutes.
Discard any which have not opened, set aside. Saute scallops in olive oil for 10-15 minutes, set aside.

title: jello salad
directions: Stir together water, crushed pineapple and jello.
Bring to a boil and boil 10 minutes.
Chill until firm.

title: sour cream pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Stir in sour cream.
Add syrup, vanilla and salt.
Mix sugar with cornstarch and add to rest of ingredients. Stir in pecans.
Put in uncooked pie shell and cook at 350° until crust is brown, about 35 minutes.

title: chicken a la king
directions: In saucepan, cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Blend in flour.
Cook, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat. Gradually stir in broth and milk.
Cook, stirring until thickened. Add remaining ingredients.
Heat; stir often.
Serve over toast.
Makes 3 cups.

title: weight watchers soup
directions: Combine all the ingredients and cook on medium heat for 1 hour, until all vegetables are done.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix pumpkin, eggs, milk, sugar and spices. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over top of pumpkin mixture.
Dribble melted margarine over cake mix. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Serve with whipped cream.

title: nonfat gazpacho dressing(oil-free and nondairy!)
directions: Place onion, potatoes, water and salt in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil; cover and simmer until the potatoes are tender. Remove from heat; add spinach and
garlic cloves and set aside.

title: unusual green pepper jelly
directions: Seed peppers and chop coarsely.
Place half of chopped peppers and 3/4 cups vinegar in container of electric blender.
Process on high speed until smooth.
Put remainder in (peppers and sugar). Put pureed peppers, red pepper, sugar and salt in a large Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Add pectin.
Cook, stirring often.
Cook 30 minutes or until it sheets from metal spoon.
Pour in jelly jar.
Pour 1/2 inch of paraffin.
Cover with metal lids.
Makes 6 pint jars.
Can tint red or green.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and Crisco.
Add sugar and eggs, one at a time.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add vanilla.
Add milk to creamed mixture.
Bake in 9 or 10-inch tube pan at 325° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips, butter and peanut butter together on low heat.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Stir until some of marshmallows have melted.
Pour into a buttered dish.
Let cool and cut into pieces.

title: pumpkin spice cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening. Gradually beat in sugar. Add eggs and pumpkin.
Mix well. Sift flour, baking powder, salt and spices together. Add to pumpkin mixture; mix well. Add nuts. Drop by teaspoonful onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake about 15 minutes or until firm to touch.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Thaw dough overnight.
Roll out dough on lightly floured board to 8-inches by 22 inches.
Place slices of pepperoni over dough. Put 1/2 inch chunks of cheese on top of pepperoni.

title: ham-broccoli bake
directions: Mix broccoli cuts, mushroom soup, cheese soup, milk, ham and onion powder together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Bisquick and milk and pour over mixture.
Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Other meat can be used such as chicken, turkey or beef.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix syrup, sugar and salt together.
Beat in whole eggs, one at a time.
Stir in melted butter, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pastry shells.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Do not overbake.
Cool 1 hour before serving.

title: corn bread
directions: In large iron skillet, melt 1 stick of margarine.
Mix together the rest of ingredients.
It should be soupy.
Pour into melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: deckel roast
directions: Brown roast with oil and garlic on all sides.
When done, remove from pot, empty remaining oil.
Put ketchup and horseradish in pot.
Fill each bottle with water and empty into pot.
Return meat and simmer approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Steam onion and garlic until onion is soft.
Add carrot, green pepper, bay leaf and herbs.
Stir well, then add the tomatoes, tomato paste and seasonings.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Melt and stir together over boiling water or in microwave oven.
Let harden and cut into bars.
Yield: About 3 1/2 dozen.

title: hungry boy cookies
directions: Cream sugars and margarine together.
Add eggs.
Beat until well mixed.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and salt which have been sifted together.
Mix well.
Add coconut, dates, pecans, chips, raisins, uncooked oatmeal and Rice Krispies.
Stir by hand until well mixed.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Melt butter in large skillet; add celery, green pepper and onion.
Saute.
Add salt, pepper, milk and soup.
Add rest of ingredients except cheese and almonds.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Add cheese and almonds.
tags: cream of celery soup/cream of mushroom soup

title: barbara's brownie cookie
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Beat in eggs.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Mix into creamed mixture to blend.
Add 2 cups of chocolate or chocolate raspberry chips. Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes.

title: broccoli with rice
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until clear.
Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain well.
Mix broccoli with soup and cheese and add to celery and onion.
Stir in cooked rice. Season and mix well.
Put into a greased casserole and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: saltine candy
directions: Line a cookie sheet with foil.
Lay out saltines, bumper to bumper.
Melt margarine.
Add sugar and boil for 3 minutes (medium heat).
Pour over crackers and spread to cover.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 7 minutes until light brown.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with peanut butter chips and chocolate chips.
Heat will melt chips.
Blend together by spreading with base of spoon. Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.
Break into bark.
Yummy!

title: poor man's lasagne
directions: Cook and drain hamburger with bell pepper, onion, garlic, mushrooms, Ragu sauce and tomato paste.
Cook and drain lasagne noodles.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan, then continue to layer meat, Parmesan cheese, cottage cheese, crushed olives, Mozzarella cheese and Sargento cheese.
Continue to layer until pan is nearly full. Last layer will be sauce (no meat), then cheese, Parmesan cheese, Mozzarella and Sargento cheeses.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 300° oven.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Melt butter, Saute garlic in butter slowly. Add lemon juice, wine, dillweed and salt.
Saute shrimp until pink.
Serve over angel hair pasta, rice or linguine.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Combine sour cream, cream cheese and potatoes, mixing well, until blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually.
Cream until smooth.
Add eggs.
Mix. Stir in dry ingredients.
Add fruit and nuts.
Drop with spoon.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon whipper snappers
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients by hand.
Drop by teaspoon onto powdered sugar.
Roll into a 1-inch ball.
Bake at 350° on a greased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: cheesy chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken with bouillon cubes, in about 1 1/2 quarts of water.
Save the broth and debone the chicken.
Cook spaghetti in the chicken broth and add tomatoes, beans and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add chicken and pour into a dish.
Cook at 375 degrees for about 30-45 minutes or until bubbly.
This is enough for two casserole dishes and freezes well.

title: brie in crescent roll
directions: Separate crescent dough into triangles.
Lay them on a cookie sheet in a circle with the fat ends towards the center leaving the points at the outer edge of the circle.
Roll together so there are no gaps in the center.
Place brie on crescent dough in center.
Poke a few times with a fork.
Sprinkle Tabasco sauce over the brie letting it soak into the holes.
Bring points of the triangles together at the center of the brie and seal.
Bake at 375 degrees for about 15 minutes.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Melt tomato soup and cream cheese over medium heat in a saucepan.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup boiling water; add to soup mixture.
Add onion and shrimp; blend well.
Add mayonnaise; blend well.
Pour into mold.
Refrigerate until set.

title: scalloped peaches
directions: Melt the butter in the top of a double boiler over boiling water; add the crumbled cereal. Stir until well blended.
Mix spices with sugar. Use a baking dish 7 x 3-inches deep.
Cover the bottom of the dish with buttered crumbs; add a layer of peaches and sprinkle with sugar mixture. Continue until peaches are used, leaving a layer of crumbs on top.
Add water mixed with lemon juice. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Use either canned or fresh peaches.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Cut cake in half.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Cover bottom half of cake with mixture.
Pour half the pie filling over this.
Add top layer of cake.
Cover top half of cake with remaining mixture.
Pour the rest of the pie filling over top of cake.

title: baked egg custard pie
directions: In a large bowl, place the egg mix.
Add water slowly, stirring constantly to avoid lumps.
Beat well until slightly fluffy.
Stir cinnamon and nutmeg into the eggs.
In another bowl, mix together the sugar and flour.
Stir into eggs.
Stir in evaporated milk, margarine and vanilla flavoring.

title: hudson's maurice dressing
directions: Blend together until smooth. Great with any salad.

title: plantation dinner casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain; add onion, soup, corn, pimiento, milk, salt and pepper.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Mix together ground meat mixture and noodles.
Put in a casserole dish and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle cheese on top, returning to oven just long enough to let the cheese melt.
Let set for 5 minutes before serving.

title: roasted vegetable couscous salad
directions: Prepare couscous according to package directions except omit butter or olive oil.
Allow to cool for 10 minutes.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Cream margarine and milk together.
Gradually add sugar.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Drop with spoon on cookie sheet and let stand overnight in freezer or refrigerator.

title: sugarplum frosting
directions: Cream butter thoroughly.
Add sugar slowly; continue beating until mixture is light and crumbly.
Add cream and vanilla; beat until completely blended.
For thinner frosting, use slightly more cream.
For thicker frosting, add extra sugar in small amounts.

title: apple spice everything nice cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar and shortening.
Add applesauce or water. Add flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Add apples, raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8-10 minutes at 400 degrees.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill overnight.
Use as a side dish or relish.

title: fruit squares(servings:  12)
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Stir in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour.
Add nuts.
Spread three-fourths of the batter 1/2-inch thick in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with filling.
Spoon remaining batter onto filling; spread over surface in patches.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool; cut in squares and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: spiedies marinade(for beef, lamb, pork, chicken)
directions: Mix all together.
Pour over chunks of meat.
Cover and marinate for 24 hours.
Place meat on skewers and grill or broil.

title: pork chops with sauce
directions: Roll pork chops in dry spaghetti sauce mix and brown in butter or oil.
Put soups in bowl and mix well.
Pour over chops and cook at 350° for 1 hour or until chops are tender.
Makes a delicious gravy.

title: health salad
directions: Mix well and let stand about 1 hour before eating.

title: aunt relda's apple salad
directions: Bring pineapple and sugar to a boil.
Boil about 5 minutes. Stir to dissolve sugar.
Remove from heat and add cream cheese and jello.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Cool.
Fold into cooled mixture the celery, nuts, apples and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: garlicky mashed potatoes
directions: Fill a 3-quart pan half full with water and bring to a boil. Peel potatoes, if desired.
Put potatoes, garlic and rosemary in water; return to a boil and cook until potatoes are tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain well, reserving 1/2 cup of cooking liquid.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in a large glass mixing bowl. Microwave for 4 minutes on Roast.
Stir well and continue cooking for 3 1/2 minutes on Roast, constantly stirring as mixture boils. Remove from microwave.
Stir in remaining ingredients until melted.
Pour in buttered 2-quart (8 x 8-inch) glass baking dish. Cool overnight.
Cut into squares.

title: bacon, cheddar and tomato sandwiches
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine all ingredients except hamburger buns.
Arrange buns, cut sides up, in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Spoon equal amount of bacon-cheese mixture onto each bun half.
Bake 15 minutes, until cheese is bubbling. Makes 4 servings (2 halves each).

title: pudding icing
directions: Whip pudding until it gets thick. Stir in Cool Whip. Spread on cake. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Combine sugar and butter and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each.
Add flour to mixture along with whipping cream.
Blend and mix well.
Add flavoring. Pour into tube pan that is well-greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until cake test is done.

title: burgundy chili
directions: Cook onion, garlic and beef in heated oil until lightly browned.
Stir hot water into chili powder; add to meat mixture along with tomatoes, salt and herbs.
Cover and simmer over very low heat 45 to 50 minutes.
Stir in wine and simmer, uncovered, about 20 minutes longer.
Add beans and heat.
Serve over hot polenta, rice or squares of corn bread.
Serves 8.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Combine peanut butter and softened ice cream; mix well. Pour into pie crust; freeze.

title: apple relish
directions: Cut peppers, onions and celery into small pieces.
Add sugar and cover with vinegar.
Cook until mixture is half done, then add apples and finish cooking until mixture turns brown.
Put in hot jars.
Process 15 minutes in hot water bath at simmering.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Put coarsely chopped peppers and vinegar in blender.
Blend until finely chopped.
Add sugar and bring mixture to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add pectin.
Boil 3 minutes longer. Add food coloring a drop at a time until color desired.
Stir and seal in jar (hot sterilized).
Will make 6 or 7 half-pint jars of jelly.

title: tomato-asparagus salad
directions: Snap off tough ends of asparagus.
Remove scales from stalks with a knife or vegetable peeler, if desired.
Cook asparagus, covered, in a small amount of boiling water 6 to 8 minutes or until crisp-tender; drain.
Plunge asparagus into ice water to stop the cooking process.
Drain and set aside.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and 1 teaspoon salt.
Pour off excess grease.
Add sauce and cottage cheese to beef.
Cook noodles in boiling water with 1 teaspoon salt for 7 minutes.

title: cream of carrot soup
directions: Heat butter in large soup pot.
Add onion and celery and saute for 5 minutes or until limp.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add chicken stock, stirring thoroughly after each addition.
Stir in carrots.
Bring mixture to a low boil.
Reduce heat and continue to simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until carrots are tender. Remove from heat.
Puree soup in a blender in small batches. Return soup to soup pot and stir in the cream.
Add salt and pepper and continue to heat until soup is hot and ready to serve. Sprinkle with dill just before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Mix, following directions on the box with the exception of substituting the water for pineapple juice.
Set aside.
In skillet or cake pan, melt margarine.
Be sure to coat the sides good. After margarine is melted, sprinkle with brown sugar, enough to absorb the butter.
Sprinkle with pieces of walnuts or pecans. Place pineapple rings on top of that with maraschino cherries in the middle of the pineapple.
Put cake mix on top of that and bake in a 350° oven for the time specified on the box.
Time may be a little longer.
Will have to go by smell and toothpick check. Remove from oven when baked and let cool for approximately 30 minutes in pan.
Take a wet knife and go around the edges and then invert onto cake plate or foil covered cardboard.
Whatever works best for you.
Let cool completely before service.
Enjoy.

title: chicken-stuffed shells
directions: Mix the first five ingredients very well.
Cook jumbo shells according to package directions.
Stuff shells with mixture.

title: sinfully rich low-fat fudge sauce
directions: In small saucepan, stir together sugar, cocoa and cornstarch. Stir in evaporated milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly with wire whip until mixture boils; continue cooking and stirring until thickened and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla. Serve sauce warm or cold with fresh fruits and cake.
Refrigerate leftover sauce.

title: souper scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine soup, milk, onion, salt and pepper and mix well. Place 1/2 of the potatoes in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with 1/2 of the soup mixture.
Repeat layers.

title: christmas cinnamon ornaments
directions: Mix applesauce and ground cloves or ground cinnamon in a bowl until a stiff dough forms.
Dough should be stiff enough to roll out 1/4-inch thick.
If dough is sticky, you may sprinkle in more cloves or cinnamon.
After dough is pressed out, cut with cookie cutters.
Make hole with toothpick.
Carefully put on rack to dry. Let air dry several days, turning occasionally.
These ornaments smell wonderful on your Christmas tree.
Makes 12 ornaments.

title: rock candy
directions: Stir sugar, corn syrup and water over low heat until dissolved.
Cook without stirring over high heat to the hard crack stage, 310°.
Remove mixture from heat; add coloring and flavor. Pour mixture onto greased cookie sheet.
When cold, break into pieces.

title: spinach salad
directions: Layer spinach, onion, mushrooms, bacon and eggs on salad plate.
Pour dressing over all.

title: microwave sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if skin is tough, otherwise just scrub and rinse well.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through. Use handle of wooden spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way through.
Place potatoes in micro-safe dish or pan.
Sprinkle with melted butter and chopped parsley, chives or thyme.
Microwave on High power for 10 minutes, rearranging the potatoes after 5 minutes.
Let rest for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Work the grated cheese into the slices.
Micro for another 4 to 6 minutes at High power until cheese is melted and potatoes are soft.
Serves 4.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tomato-s0up spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sift flour with soda, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
In a large bowl, with electric mixer at high speed, cream butter until light. Gradually add brown sugar, beating until light.
Add eggs, beating until fluffy.

Combine soup with enough water to measure 2 cups. At low speed, add flour mixture (in fourths) to sugar mixture, alternately with soup mixture (thirds), beginning and ending with flour mixture; beat until just combined.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Turn into prepared pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool completely before frosting.
Use Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: strawberry sauce
directions: Drain strawberries, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to measure 1 cup.
In a small saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch. Gradually add strawberry syrup, stirring until smooth.
Over low heat, slowly bring to boiling, stirring until mixture is thickened and translucent.
Remove from heat.
Stir in strawberries. Refrigerate until cold.

title: chicken rice-a-roni
directions: Brown Rice-A-Roni and seasoning in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add mushrooms, mushroom soup and boiling water.
Place chicken in oiled 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour Rice-A-Roni mixture over the chicken. Sprinkle onion soup on top. Seal well with foil and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Do not add salt.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In a saucepan mix both pudding and pie filling with milk, adding a cap of vanilla flavoring.
Cook according to directions on package.
Pour into pie crust.
Let cool before serving.
Can be garnished with whipped cream.

title: apple crisp
directions: Pour pie filling into shallow baking dish.
Top with the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix together; crumble topping evenly over potato mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: funny face chocolate chip pancakes
directions: Beat the first 3 ingredients with whisk until well blended. Add chocolate chips (keeping 1/4 cup for later).
Mix well. Spray griddle with nonstick spray.
Pour by 1/4 cupfuls onto hot griddle.
Cook until bubbles form in middle.
Turn and cook until golden.

title: plain muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in 1/4 cup shortening.
In separate bowl, beat together milk and egg.
Add this to flour mixture.
Do not beat.
Mixture will be lumpy.
Grease muffin tin.
Fill 2/3 full and bake for 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: banana bread or muffins
directions: Mix shortening and sugar until creamed.
Add egg and cream. Add bananas and mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Put into muffin or loaf pan that has been greased.
Bake muffins at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Bake loaf at 350° for about 60 minutes.
The riper the bananas, the better the muffins.

title: toffee bars
directions: Mix ingredients and spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and spread on bars while still warm.

title: touch downs
directions: Mix all together.
Spread between bread.
Butter each side. Toast in frying pan until brown and cheese is melted.

title: swiss cheese and broccoli quiche
directions: Wash broccoli; chop into flowerets, excluding most of stems. Saute onion and broccoli in butter until tender, not soft.
Put cooked broccoli and onion in bottom of pie crust.
Mix the eggs, cream, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables and top with cheese.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 375° or until knife inserted in center comes out dry.
Cool for 10 minutes before serving or serve at room temperature.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Peel potatoes and cut in half, into a 4-quart pot.
Chop remaining vegetables and add the water and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil, then simmer until cooked, occasionally mashing.
Potatoes should be only slightly chunky.
Sprinkle each serving with Cheddar cheese.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook each kind of pasta separately until done but still firm. Rinse and drain well.
Mix two pastas together.
Add Zesty Italian dressing.
Toss and refrigerate overnight.
If excess dressing remains in bowl next morning, drain off and reserve for additional recipes.
Next day, add remaining ingredients.
Yields 14 to 15 servings.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, celery and pepper until done.
Drain off fat.
Add tomatoes and macaroni.
Simmer on low until done. Pour into baking dish and cover with Velveeta cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix margarine and sugar together, adding eggs.
Add flour and sour cream and flavorings.
Bake at 300° or 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes to 2 hours.

title: bark candy
directions: Melt bark in microwave or over hot water in double boiler. Put remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour bark over; mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper-lined cookie sheet.

title: hamburger, herbs and rice
directions: Saute the hamburger in the butter until well separated and slightly browned.
Add onion, celery and parsley; cook for 5 minutes longer.
Add salt, pepper and chicken broth.
Stir in rice and herbs.
Cook over very low heat, covered, for 15 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: chicken casserole(serves 8 to 12)
directions: Mix stuffing, sage, melted butter and onion together. Put 1/2 on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch buttered baking dish. Mix together soups (undiluted), pepper, mustard, lemon juice, peas and sour cream. Add chicken. Place on top of stuffing in casserole and put remaining stuffing on top. Sprinkle with almonds. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Must bubble. Watch for browning too quickly. Enjoy!

title: cheesy beef enchiladas
directions: Prepare hamburger with taco seasoning according to package directions.
Heat refried beans.

Mix together cottage cheese, Monterey Jack cheese, chopped chiles, egg and seasonings. Microwave tortillas on HIGH for 30 to 45 seconds or until pliable. Place refried beans evenly on each tortilla; next place hamburger mixture on each tortilla, then Monterey Jack cheese filling on each tortilla.
Roll the tortillas up in jellyroll fashion; place seam side down in an 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4 inch baking dish. Cover with enchilada sauce.
Microwave on HIGH for 10 to 12 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Sprinkle with cheddar cheese; microwave for an additional 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Garnish with sour cream and green onions.

title: mm mm roast
directions: Mix Coke, chili sauce and soup mix.
Place roast and cubed potatoes and carrots in roaster.
Pour sauce mix over meat and vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until done.

title: butter dip bread sticks
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan in the oven.
Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt and combine these dry ingredients.
Stir in milk with a fork, stirring just until dough clings together.
(May not need complete cup.) Knead dough on floured board about 10 times.
Roll dough into an 8 x 12-inch rectangle.
With a floured knife, cut dough in half lengthwise, then cut dough into 16 strips from each half (total 32 strips).
Dip each strip into melted butter in the 9 x 13-inch pan, coating all sides and lay strips close together in 2 rows in pan. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onions and carrots in salted water.
Cover until tender.
Drain well.
Add soup and sour cream.
Melt butter and stir in dressing mix.
Spread half of dressing mix in greased dish.
Pour in squash mixture.
Cover with remaining dressing mix. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook on top of stove.
Mix butter, sugar and milk.
Cook 5 minutes at boiling.
Take off stove.
Mix vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop on wax paper, one tablespoon at a time.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: chicken yummy
directions: Cut cutlets into bite size pieces (easier if still partially frozen).
Dip into beaten eggs.
Shake cutlets in an equal crumb-cheese mixture (in a plastic bag).
Pepper is optional. Saute coated cutlets in plenty of butter until golden brown. Remove chicken to casserole dish.
Saute any and all vegetables in amount you desire in the same pan (I prefer just broccoli).
Keep scraping bottom of pan.
Add vegetables to chicken.
Add 1/4 to 1/2 cup broth to chicken mixture.
Stir everything together.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until bubbly and golden brown. Serve with rice.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin with 1 cup of hot water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: coconut and pecan vanilla wafer cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers in a food processor

or in a bag and roll a rolling pin over the pan until wafers are crushed. Cream margarine and sugar together. Add eggs, 2 at a time. Add milk gradually and mix well. Place crushed wafers in a round or flat dish with sides, then stir in pecans and coconut in cream mixture and mix well, then pour on wafer crust. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done. Serve warm with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: rhubarb sponge pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, save for later.
Beat egg yolks and sugar together.
Add melted butter and flour.
Stir in milk and lemon juice.
Cut rhubarb and place in the bottom of unbaked pie shell. Fold egg whites that have been beaten stiff into above mixture.
Pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes and then at 350° for 25 minutes more.
Use a 9-inch pan.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Grease baking dish with about 1 tablespoon butter.
Put in 1/2 cup bread crumbs.
Slice 4 apples on this.
Cover with 1/2 cup bread crumbs, 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, 3/4 cup sugar, 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg and dot with 1 tablespoon of butter.
Repeat with 4 apples, 1/2 cup bread crumbs, 3/4 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1 teaspoon nutmeg and dot with 1 tablespoon butter. Pour cup of water on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: best ever cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients
until	well
blended.	Fold in carefully remaining ingredients.
Spoon
by
teaspoonful
onto cookie sheet and then press
down with fork.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool
and
store
in an airtight container. Put piece of crumpled foil on top to keep cookies crispy.

title: genevieve bender's pizzelles
directions: Cream sugar and melted oleo.
Beat in eggs, adding them one at a time.
Stir in anise oil, lemon extract, vanilla and cinnamon. Add flour, one cup at a time. Stir in whiskey.
Drop tablespoonful on hot pizzelle iron and cook for 30 to 40 seconds.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat. Drain; add peppers, onions and mushrooms. Mix. Pour into large casserole dish. Top with pizza sauce. Top with Mozzarella.

title: picadillo
directions: Brown beef in skillet; drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce and remaining ingredients.
Simmer for a few minutes until heated through.
Serve with rice.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Fill quart jars with chopped cabbage, then add salt, vinegar and sugar.
Pour enough boiling water to completely cover contents in the jar.
Seal tightly.

title: golden cream potato soup
directions: Cover and simmer first 9 ingredients until tender, then add remaining ingredients.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown meats.
Drain.
Cut Velveeta into small chunks and add to meat.
Stir until melted.
Add soups.
Mix well. Add picante sauce; stir.
Can be put in crock-pot to keep warm.

title: pasta with eggplant and tomatoes
directions: Sprinkle cut side of eggplant with salt.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Rinse under cold water.
Dry and peel. Dice flesh and set aside.

title: chicken for 6
directions: Flatten chicken breasts.
Spread 1/4 cup butter on each side; salt and pepper.
Roll up and wrap with slice of cheese.
Coat lightly with flour; dip in egg.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Secure with toothpicks.
Arrange in a shallow pan.
Melt remaining butter; add herbs.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Baste. Pour wine over.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Baste.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, bell pepper and onion; mix.
Heat remaining ingredients and pour over cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate.
Good as long as it lasts.

title: raspberry champagne punch
directions: In blender, puree raspberries.
In a punch bowl, combine raspberries, lemon concentrate, sugar and wine.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Just before serving, scoop sherbet into punch bowl. Add champagne.
Stir gently.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: thanksgiving dinner rice
directions: Prepare rice however is says on package, plus 1 1/2 cups of water.
Saute the onion and celery in 2 tablespoons of oil until transparent.
Add mushrooms, parsley and nuts; saute 1 to 2 minutes.
Add this to rice and water.
Cook until all water is absorbed (approximately 20 to 30 minutes).

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Place in bottom of 3-quart casserole. Top with sauce and cheese.
Combine Bisquick, milk and eggs.
Pour over sauce and cheese evenly.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cut in squares and serve.

title: grandma's chili
directions: Cook in a large pan for 30 minutes.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Mix everything together.
Pour into buttered cake pan and bake about 25 minutes at 375°.
Serve warm with milk.

title: sweet and spicy dip
directions: In medium saucepan, over medium-high heat, using wire whisk, combine all ingredients.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens and boils.
Serve warm with chicken nuggets, wontons, cocktail franks or vegetables for dipping.
Makes 3 cups.
May be refrigerated in covered nonmetal container for up to one week.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheet with Crisco.
Combine Crisco, light brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in large bowl. Beat at medium speed of mixer until well blended.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed just until blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 2 inches apart onto baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet.
Remove to foil on countertop.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: sweet and sour stir-fry chicken
directions: Coat chicken with cornstarch.
Heat oil on medium-high heat in skillet.
Add chicken; cook for 3 to 4 minutes, until golden brown. Set aside in a bowl.
Add bell pepper, snap peas and water chestnuts to skillet.
Stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes, until just tender. Add to this the stir-fry sauce and chicken.
Serve over rice; garnish with sliced scallions.

title: english pea salad
directions: Drain peas and add onions, peppers, cheese, celery and pickle relish.
Mix well and then toss gently with mayonnaise and egg. Chill.

title: hot apple cider drink
directions: Mix all ingredients except oranges in large saucepan.
Cut ends off the 3 oranges and place in mixture.
Simmer over medium heat to low heat for 30 minutes to 1 hour and serve.
Can be refrigerated, then reheat and serve hot.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Add eggs to first three ingredients.
Add pumpkin, nutmeg, cloves and soda.
Mix.
Slowly add flour.
Stir in dates and nuts. Drop by spoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: creme puff dessert
directions: Combine 1 cup water and 1 stick butter and bring to boil. Stir in 1 cup flour and mix until blended.
Remove from burner. Beat in 4 eggs, one at a time, until blended.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Let fall and cool. Then beat 1 large vanilla instant pudding with 3 cups milk and 1 large 8 ounce package of cream cheese.
Refrigerate 15 minutes. Spread Cool Whip on top.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.
Cut into squares.
Serves 8 to 10 persons.

title: crinkled cookies
directions: Cream shortening in large bowl of electric mixer.
Add 1 1/2 cups sugar gradually and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after the addition of each egg.
Add sifted dry ingredients (flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt).

title: sour cream cucumbers
directions: Pare cucumbers; slice and sprinkle with salt.
Chill 30 minutes.
Press out excess liquid in folds of paper towels. Combine other ingredients and toss with cucumbers.
Chill 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Remove fat and gristle.
Cut into narrow strips 2 1/2-inches long, 3/4-inch wide and 1/4-inch thick.
Dust strips with salt and pepper.
Leave at room temperature at least 2 hours.

title: ranch mashed potatoes
directions: Add you do is add salad dressing mix to potatoes.
Mix well. Add butter or margarine if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla until creamy.
Add combined remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: french-fried cauliflower
directions: Prepare the cauliflower according to package directions and drain.
Season with salt.
Blend milk with the egg, then dip the cauliflower into the mixture.
Roll in the bread crumbs.
Drop into hot oil and cook until golden brown.

title: chicken burgers
directions: Mix hamburger, soup and egg, salt and pepper.
Crumble the crackers into the meat mixture.
Make into patties.
Roll in cracker crumbs.
Fry in hot shortening.
They are very moist and good.
Taste between chicken and hamburger.

title: piccadillo
directions: Saute onions & peppers in olive oil, then meat. Drain. Add rest of ingredients & cook 1 hour over slow heat, covered. Serve over yellow rice.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare pudding in separate bowl.
Crush candy in wrappers; put in another bowl.
Crush 2/3 package of chocolate wafers in another bowl.
Defrost Cool Whip.
In a clear bowl, place in layers:
pudding, sprinkle candy bars, Cool Whip and sprinkle wafers.
Enough ingredients to repeat 3 times.

title: taco bake
directions: Brown ground beef and onion over medium heat and drain.
Add water, taco seasoning and tomato sauce; mix well.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion well done; drain.
Add soup and sour cream.
Melt stick of butter in skillet.
Add seasoning packet and bread crumbs to butter and brown.
Layer 1/2 bread crumbs on bottom of casserole.
Pour mixture in and top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: grandma's chili
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Add sauce, beans and chili powder.
Cook slowly for 1 hour.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar together.
Then add eggs and mix well.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan, mix chocolate chips, 1/2 cup of the whipping cream and sugar.
Stirring frequently over low heat, cook until mixture is smooth.

title: fudge cake
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together.
Add the eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Melt and add the chocolate.
Blend into mixture. Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together alternately with ice water to creamed mixture.
Grease three 8-inch layer cake pans and line with waxed paper.
Pour in batter.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 to 35 minutes, or 9 x 13-inch pan for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together and press into an 11 x 14-inch pan.
Bake 5 minutes in 350° oven.

title: baked pork chops on the grill
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a non-metal dish.
Turn heat on grill to medium.
Place chops on opposite burner from heat. Bake for 30 minutes (don't look) and turn over and bake for 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: egg casserole
directions: Cook sausage.
Crumble and drain real well.
Beat eggs, milk, mustard and salt together. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Add cubed bread on top.
Sprinkle sausage on top.
Sprinkle cheese on top and soak overnight or 6 hours.
Cover dish with foil.
Leave one corner of foil slightly lifted for steam to get out.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes.
Eggs shouldn't be runny (bake 5 minutes longer if necessary).
Cut in squares for serving. Leftovers are excellent.

title: chocolate oat chip cookies
directions: Beat
butter,
shortening and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs, milk
and
vanilla;
beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate morsels and nuts. Mix well. Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Cool on a cookie sheet for 1 minute, then remove to wire rack to cool completely.

title: chicken 'n rice dinner
directions: Heat oil in large nonstick skillet on medium-high heat.
Add chicken; cover.
Cook 5 minutes on each side or until cooked through.
Remove chicken from skillet.
Add water, soup and seasonings; stir.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice and broccoli.
Top with chicken.
Cover.
Cook on low heat 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of chicken soup

title: oriental rice with vegetables
directions: Saute mushrooms in margarine in medium saucepan.
Add chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
Add vegetables and soy sauce.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes or until all liquid is absorbed.
Serves 4.
Each serving equals 1 bread, 1 vegetable, 1/2 fat, 19 optional calories on most diet exchange programs.

title: cinnamon breakfast rolls
directions: Grease a Bundt pan with oleo.
Put dinner rolls in and sprinkle dry pudding mix over the rolls.
Pour in the melted butter, brown sugar and pecans.
Put towel over pan and let the rolls rise overnight.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool for 5 minutes.
Throw onto plate! Excellent and easy!

title: carrots elegante(microwave)
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe dish, microwave carrots with water, covered, until tender, 7 to 8 minutes, stirring once. Drain.
Immediately stir in remaining ingredients.
Yields 4 servings.

title: baked hash romanoff
directions: Refrigerate corned beef hash until cold.
Open both ends of can in order to push out into a roll of corned beef hash.
Cut into approximately 3/4 inch slices and place in shallow baking dish, overlapping slices.
Top with sauce; tomato sauce, garlic powder and oregano; then, top with shredded cheese.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 25 minutes or until very hot!
Serves 4.

title: zucchini puff
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix zucchini, onion, oil and Bisquick. Beat eggs; add to mix.
Add cheese, salt and parsley.
Mix well. Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: apple butter
directions: Place apple pieces and apple juice, cider and lemon juice in a large non-aluminum kettle.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until volume is reduced by half (the consistency of applesauce).
Add spices; mix well and heat a few more minutes. Remove from heat and pack into hot, clean jars, leaving 1/2-inch space at the top.
Cap with hot lid.
Process 10 minutes in boiling water.
Freeze after jars reach room temperature.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Make paste of coloring and cocoa.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix salt with vanilla and milk. Add alternately with flour.
Mix soda with vinegar; fold into mixture.
Bake in two layers of 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: simple pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta al dente.
Combine pasta with remaining ingredients.
Serve as a main dish on a hot summer evening with large slices of fresh French bread and an iced beverage.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until done.
Cool. Punch holes all over cake with a straw.
Spread milk over top and in holes. Cool 30 minutes in refrigerator. Spread pineapple over cake, then spread Cool Whip over the whole cake.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine melted butter, brown sugar and spices.
Pour over fruit.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: x-tra fancy pound cake
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, salt and mace.
Cream butter thoroughly.
Gradually add 10x sugar, creaming well.
Continue beating until light and fluffy.
Blend in extracts and add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Begin and end with dry ingredients.
Blend thoroughly on low speed after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Turn into well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cool and frost, if desired.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Heat water, jello, cheese and marshmallows until dissolved. Cool slightly; add nuts, 7-Up and well drained pineapple.
Chill.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Crumble sausage in frypan and brown.
Combine eggs, milk and Bisquick; pour into oblong glass dish.
Add fried sausage and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mrs. mae bell morgan's hominy
directions: Boil for 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil water and sugar for 3 minutes and cool.
Mix lemon juice, water and pineapple juice.
Cut bananas lengthwise; remove seeds. Crush and pour 1/2 lemon juice mixture over bananas.
Add orange juice and 1 can water.
Mix altogether; add to cooled syrup.
Place in wide mouth jars and freeze.
Remove from freezer 2 hours before serving; add ginger ale.
Add pint of sherbet.

title: vegetable salad
directions: In bowl, combine first seven ingredients.
In 10-cup clear bowl, layer cabbage, mushrooms, spinach, onion and peas.
Spread on dressing; top with cheese and bacon.
May be refrigerated up to 8 hours.

title: blueberry crumb pudding
directions: Thaw berries.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 1-quart casserole or baking dish.
Roll zwieback into fine crumbs and mix with sugar, cinnamon and melted butter.
Arrange 1 layer of blueberries on bottom of pan, cover with crumbs, alternating, ending up with crumbs on top.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.

title: tiger butter cups
directions: Melt white chocolate and peanut butter chips in double boiler. Add peanut butter.
Stir until mixed.
Spoon into mini muffin cups.
Makes about 100.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and one egg and press into bottom of 9 x 11-inch pan.

title: shrimp in green peppers
directions: Cut slice off bottom of peppers; clean insides.
Blanch peppers in scalding water for 3 minutes; drain.
Add seasonings to melted butter.
Combine with bread crumbs.
Add egg and then add shrimp.
Stuff peppers.
Set each pepper in a paper frill in a muffin tin.
Sprinkle tops with grated Parmesan cheese (paprika also, optional).
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift the 3 cups of flour, cinnamon, soda, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs well.
Gradually add sugar and oil, mixing well. Add vanilla and dry ingredients; mixing well.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients; blend well.
Stir in zucchini.
Mix nuts with 1 teaspoon of flour; stir into batter.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cool in pans on rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Bake in 350° oven until lightly browned.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind together the tomatoes, peppers and onions.
Mix all ingredients
together good and cook for 10 minutes.
Can hot.

title: cheesy cauliflower casserole
directions: Rinse cauliflower.
Separate into flowerets.
Cook cauliflower until tender-crisp and drain.
Place in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Heat oven to 400°.
Beat soup and milk with hand beater until smooth.
Pour over cauliflower.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: kugel
directions: Cook noodles per package directions.
While noodles cook, drain canned fruit.
Put rest of ingredients (except cherries) in bowl and mix together.
Drain noodles and add to fruit.
Add that to mixture in bowl.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch Pyrex pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Put on cherries (in decorative pattern). Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Serve hot or warm; may be reheated.
(Great with turkey or chicken.)

title: stromboli
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook the sausage.
Keep in small pieces. Mix together all the ingredients in a bowl except the frozen bread dough or olive oil.
Defrost frozen loaves of bread dough in microwave until soft or put it in the oven at 200° with a pan of water on shelf under the loaf; leave it there until soft.
On a cookie sheet, spray nonstick spray.
Spread soft bread dough until flat.
Put 1/4 ingredients on dough.
Wrap dough around it and pinch shut.
Turn it over so crease is on the bottom.
Cut 3 small holes in top of dough.
Brush with olive oil and sprinkle with oregano.
Bake until golden.
Repeat with other dough.

title: creole green beans
directions: Fry bacon; drain on paper towel.
Pour off all but 3 tablespoons of drippings.
Empty beans into skillet; add soup mix and heat thoroughly.
Break bacon into small pieces; add half to beans, along with tomatoes and sugar.
Heat to serve.
Top with remaining bacon.
Serves 8.

title: popsicles
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze in paper cups until thick enough to hold wooden stick, then cover with foil.
Freeze until hard.

title: drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening, vanilla and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Continue creaming while adding well beaten eggs slowly. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Drop small portions of mixture on greased baking sheet; in 400° oven, bake for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 72 cookies.

title: open face blueberry pie
directions: In a saucepan, put 1 cup blueberries, sugar and water.
Bring to a boil; make a paste combining flour, salt and water.
Add to the blueberry mixture, stirring until thickened.
Remove from heat and add hot mixture to uncooked reserved 3 cups blueberries.
Fold well and pour all into the baked pie shell.
Chill for at least 3 hours.
Serve topped with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: ritz cracker snack
directions: Cook milk and dates until thick.
Add chopped nuts.
Spread on crackers.
Bake at 250° for 10 minutes.
After baked, mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread on top of crackers.

title: banana split cake
directions: The crust:
Pour crushed graham crackers into pan (so that it covers the bottom of the pan) and add 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup softened butter and blend.
Mash into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix powdered sugar, 1 cup softened butter, eggs and vanilla.
Pour on top of crust.
Next, layer the sliced bananas, then the crushed pineapple, Cool Whip; top with strawberries and pecans. Refrigerate overnight.

title: prune cupcakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs 1 at a time and beat well.
Add sifted flour, salt, soda and cinnamon alternately with sour milk.
Add prunes, raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in muffin tins with liners.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: hot spread for split french rolls
directions: Soak garlic in oil for 1 hour.
Combine all ingredients and spread mixture on split rolls and put in broiler about 15 minutes. Serve piping hot.

title: ozark burgers
directions: Combine beef, onions, potatoes, salt and pepper; make into patties.
Roll patties in flour.
Brown in hot oil in skillet then place in baking pan.
Make sauce by combining the steak sauce, tomato sauce and water; stir well.
Pour sauce over patties and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecued short ribs
directions: Cut short ribs into serving pieces.
Brown with onions in hot fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake at 350°
until tender, or cook over very low heat 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: rhubarb pudding
directions: *Use miniature or cut up big ones.

title: cake mix cookie sandwiches
directions: Mix all together.
Make little balls and press down a little then bake at 350°F for 8-10 min.
Let cool and put Cool Whip in between cookies.
Excellent for freezing.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, stirring until blended.
Divide mixture in half.
Roll into two cheese balls.
Wrap with plastic wrap and chill for 5 hours or until ready to serve.
Pull a vegetable peeler down long edge of candy bar, letting chocolate curl up on vegetable peeler.
Press pecans around sides and sprinkle chocolate curls on top.
Serve with gingersnaps.

title: speedy baked beans
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir bacon and onion until bacon is crisp. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly in 300° to 350° oven.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; beat well.
Add eggs; beat again. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop small balls of dough on cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375° and decorate with colored sugar.
Or, chill dough and use in cookie press.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and chop apples.
Combine apples, sugar and flour in large bowl.
Drop by rounded spoon into hot grease.
When brown, take out to drain.
Combine powdered sugar and cinnamon in large Ziploc bag.
After crisps have cooled, put in Ziploc bag and shake.
Place in airtight container.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Pat out in bottom of cake pan and prick with fork 1-inch apart. Bake at 250° for 1 hour. Dust with powdered sugar and cut while hot.

title: tomato soup salad
directions: Bring tomato juice to a boil.
Add Jell-O.
When cool, add vegetables and 1/2 cup grated Longhorn cheese.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch square pan and chill.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Add orange slices and mix by hand.
Makes 3 layers.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook celery and onions in butter until tender; add stock and seasoning.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add slowly to mushroom soup.
Add cheese.
Boil and rinse spaghetti; add to stock.
Let stand one hour.
Add chicken, olives, sherry.
Place in 9x13-inch greased casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and broken pecans, if desired. 350 degree oven, about 45 minutes.
Serves 10-12.

title: apple-cranberry punch
directions: Combine cider and fruit juices.
Chill in refrigerator.
Add chilled ginger ale just before serving.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Melt margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Stir in all but 1/4 cup of cookie crumbs.
Press flat and refrigerate until margarine has hardened.

title: super submarine sandwiches
directions: Cut bread loaves horizontally in half.
Spread cut sides with margarine.
Dip lettuce leaves into salad dressing.
On bottom halves of loaves, layer lettuce, salami, American cheese, ham, Mozzarella cheese, tomato and onion.
Top with top halves of loaves.
Secure with wooden picks.
Makes 4 sandwiches.
Perfect for a summertime picnic!

title: meat balls barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients; make into balls.
Bake in oven until done.
Put in casserole dish.
Pour barbecue sauce over and bake about 10 minutes.

title: german apple pancake
directions: Beat egg yolks; mix in flour, butter, milk and salt.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Heat 2 tablespoons butter in a large skillet. Pour in batter; top with apple slices.
Cook over medium heat for about 5 minutes.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes, until golden brown.
Top with sugar and cinnamon.

title: rice consomme
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: miraculous vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Drain liquid.
Add chili powder.
Add V-8 and bring to gentle boil.
Add bouillon and water, then vegetables and pepper.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: mississippi party shrimp
directions: Bring tomato soup and water to a boil.
Add cream cheese and stir until dissolved.
Add gelatin, which has been dissolved in cold water.
Mix in celery, onion, green pepper, and shrimp. Chill until ready to serve.
Add mayonnaise and spread on thinly sliced bread with crust removed or place in decorative mold or bowl and serve with crackers.

title: lacy french fried onion rings
directions: Blend the first three ingredients and set aside.
Combine the egg, milk and oil in a bowl and beat until thoroughly blended. Beat in the dry ingredients until batter is smooth.
Cover and set aside while preparing onions.
Peel and slice 1/4-inch thick and separate into rings.

title: dill pickles ii
directions: Put
ingredients
in
jars
(quart).
Boil
together:
1 quart vinegar, 3 quarts water and 1/2
cup salt.
Pour over pickles and seal. Place cans in boiling water and let stand 10 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: In frying pan, saute onion in butter.
Stir in remaining ingredients, using heavy cream, until desired consistency.
Fill mushroom caps with mixture and place in single layer in baking dish or 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Can bake mushrooms in 3 tablespoons garlic butter (optional).

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut hard-boiled eggs in halves.
Remove yolks and mash with fork.
Mix in other ingredients, using enough mayo to moisten well.
Refill egg whites with yolk mixture, heaping it up.
Chill until served.

title: speedy spinach lasagne
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Add Ricotta cheese, spinach, salt and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese. Lightly grease bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with a little sauce.
Layer 1/2 of the noodles, 1/2 the cheese-spinach mixture, 1/2 the Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 the spaghetti sauce.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Cover dish with a lightly greased sheet of foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting into squares and serving.
Serves 8.

title: polish sausage-sauerkraut bake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except sausage.
Spoon into 2-quart baking dish.
Saute sausage in skillet until brown on all sides. Arrange on kraut mixture.
Bake at 375° until hot through, about 30 minutes.

title: date orange salad
directions: Mix above ingredients in bowl and marinate 1/2 hour.
Add to 6 cups greens just before serving.
Serves 6.

title: asparagus vinaigrette
directions: Trim asparagus; cover with water and add 1 teaspoon Beau Monde.
Cook until tender.
Combine in bowl 1 teaspoon Beau Monde, pepper, garlic powder, mustard, vinegar, olive oil and sour cream. Beat well.
Stir in chopped egg and parsley.
Drain asparagus and cover with sauce.
Heat thoroughly and serve at once.

title: fried green beans
directions: Cook green beans and drain.
Set aside.
Fry 3 slices of bacon until crisp.
Pour in green beans and stir every few minutes until bacon flavor has saturated green beans.

title: smokie link sausages and mushrooms
directions: Cut smokies into small slices and saute in butter for 15 minutes, then add mushroom buttons and juice.
Simmer for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.
Serve hot in chafing dish.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in skins until tender; while hot, peel and slice into 1/4-inch pieces.
In a skillet, cook bacon until crispy. Remove from pan and crumble into potatoes.
Combine remaining ingredients, except parsley, and heat to boiling point.
After mixture thickens and boils, pour over potatoes.
Mix lightly. Place in 3-quart casserole.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine sweet potatoes, sugar, salt, egg, 1/4 cup butter, vanilla and milk.
Place in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish (greased).
In small bowl, combine brown sugar, flour, pecans and remaining butter.
Top sweet potatoes with crumbled mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: creamy potato bake
directions: Prepare instant mashed potatoes omitting butter. Add cream cheese and beat well. Stir in egg, onion and parsley; blend thoroughly. Transfer to greased 1-quart baking dish. Dot with butter. Bake in hot oven (400°) for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar, vanilla and lemon extract until fluffy. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour and baking soda.
Combine jam and sour cream.
Add jam mixture alternately with dry mixture, beating until well combined.
Divide among 5 greased and floured 4 1/2 x 2 3/4 x 2 1/4-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes in pans.
Remove and cool completely on wire rack.
Freezes well.

title: playground barbecue
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in medium saucepan.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add meat and simmer for 1/2 hour.
This is also good using cooked turkey.
Makes 8 sandwiches.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops in oil in an electric skillet.
Top with cooked rice.
Add tomatoes.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ranch chicken
directions: Place thawed chicken into regular size baking bag.
Slit bag about 2-inches on the top.
Add 2 packages of Ranch dressing mix per 3 pounds of chicken; shake well.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour.
Baking times may vary according to the oven.

title: mini pizzas
directions: *Any number of toppings may be used:
chopped pepperoni, diced peppers, chopped sausage, etc.

title: creamed chicken and biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease the bottoms and sides of an 11 x 7 baking dish.
Chop the onion.
Heat butter in a small non-stick skillet over medium-high heat until melted.
Stir in onion and saute until tender.

title: eggplant cheese bake
directions: Cube eggplant.
Place in a small pan.
Cover with boiling water and boil for 5 minutes.
Drain. Add half of the cheese, gently stirring until cheese melts.
Mix in bread crumbs.
In a separate bowl, beat eggs slightly with milk, onion, parsley, salt and pepper. Stir into eggplant mixture.
Spoon into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese, bread crumbs and sesame seed.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set and golden brown.

title: spinach dip #1
directions: Drain spinach well.
Mix all ingredients and chill at least 2 hours.
Serve with "dippers" of choice.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Melt butter and saute onions, shallots and parsley.
Add cream cheese and mushroom soup.
Cover, stir until smooth.
Stir in crab meat.
Cook on low fire for about 1/2 hour.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix well and serve with raw veggies.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: May be used in pita sandwiches with garbanzo beans over pasta, or as cocktail meatballs, like Swedish meatballs.
Low cholesterol and low-fat.

title: baked salmon with capers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse and dry salmon fillet.
Place on large piece of aluminum foil, skin side down.
Squeeze 1/2 lemon juice over fish.
Sprinkle onions and capers along top of fish. Season with fresh grated pepper.
Wrap foil to seal edges.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
The fish should be just firm when pressed lightly with finger.
Garnish with 1/2 lemon, sliced.
Serves 3 to 4. Excellent served with pasta marinara and Caesar salad.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Combine partially frozen broccoli, onion, celery, cold water and butter. Boil 5 minutes. Combine rice, soup and Cheez Whiz. Fold into the vegetable mixture. Turn into shallow baking pan (10 x 8-inches).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: wee bran muffins
directions: In large pan, toss all dry ingredients together; set aside. In large bowl mix eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Pour this mixture over dry ingredients and stir until well blended.
(No electric mixer.)
Pour batter into tiny muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Makes 144 tiny muffins that can be kept in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.

title: orange jello mold
directions: Mix jello, hot water and cheese in blender.
Add fruits and stir.
Add marshmallows.

title: butterscotch yams
directions: Arrange yams in a single layer in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake in a 325° oven for 15 minutes.

title: spiced cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Refrigerate, covered, for several hours.
Just before serving, reheat slowly.
Strain to remove spices.
Serve hot in mugs or punch cups along with cookies.
Makes 8 servings.

title: oyster fritters
directions: Add enough pancake flour to egg and salt and pepper to make a thick batter.
Fry in enough hot oil to come about halfway up on fritter.
Brown on one side, turn and brown on other side.

title: waffles supreme
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt together, then add milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix oil, egg yolks and milk together.
Stir into flour mixture.
Carefully fold in egg whites (don't stir).
Heat griddle and bake for only a few minutes. Serve with your favorite syrup.

title: (hot) jalapeno relish
directions: Chop jalapeno peppers, bell peppers, onions and green tomatoes very coarse.
Sprinkle canning salt and pepper; soak overnight. Drain juice, then mix.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Melt margarine, add stuffing mix.
Mix and reserve 1/4 cup of mixture.
Cook zucchini until tender; drain.
Add everything together and mix.
Put in a greased casserole, bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Put reserved mixture on top of casserole and enjoy.

title: mocha icing
directions: Beat shortening until fluffy.
Add egg, coffee, salt and vanilla.
Add sugar and milk.
More milk may be needed.

title: squash cake
directions: Cook squash, covered, in a small amount of boiling water for 15 minutes, or until tender.
Drain.
Mash and drain again.
Set aside 1 cup squash.
Combine sugar and oil in a mixing bowl; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs; beat until well blended.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg; blend well.
Add to egg mixture. Stir in squash, orange rind, pineapple, pecans, coconut and vanilla; blend well.
Spoon into a greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes to 1 hour.
Let cake cool in pan for 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Let cool completely on a wire rack.
Place on serving plate.
Spoon Glaze over top of cake. Yields one 10-inch cake.

title: beef 'n tater bake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put meat into an 8-inch square baking dish.
Then bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
After that, remove from oven; drain excess fat.
Combine 3 cups hot mashed potatoes and 3/4 cup shredded American cheese.
Spread over meat. Top with 1/4 cup shredded American cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: pork with orange rice
directions: Brown pork in olive oil in a skillet; season with salt and pepper.
Put rice in an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Pour orange juice over rice.
Arrange pork on rice and pour condensed chicken soup over all.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake an additional 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients until creamy.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes two (2) small pies.

title: quick butterscotch sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small saucepan; bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Sauce will thicken as it cools.
Serve cold over ice cream or pudding.

title: marinated peas
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except the oil, vinegar and sugar.
Mix the oil, vinegar and sugar together before pouring over rest of ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: caramel nut pop corn
directions: Pop the corn. Put in big tupperware bowl. Shake bowl to get unpopped kernels at bottom of bowl. Lift pop corn into buttered turkey pan.

title: souper roast
directions: Mix soups together and pour over roast.
Cook in oven on 350° for about 2 1/2 hours or until done, or cook in crock-pot.

title: ever ready frozen waldorf salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve 3/4 cup juice.
Combine lemon and pineapple juice.
Add eggs, sugar and salt.
Cook over low heat, constantly stirring until thick.
Cool.
After cooled, add pineapple, celery, apples and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Freeze. Lasts indefinitely.

title: hearty vegetable beef soup
directions: Place roast, Bloody Mary mix, tomatoes and potatoes in crock-pot.
Cook on high 4 to 6 hours.
Add frozen vegetables and cook on high another 30 minutes to 1 hour or until vegetables are cooked and meat is tender.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Beat eggs, add oil, sugar and berries.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
Sprinkle with sugar. Divide mixture in half.
Bake at 350° for 70 to 75 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix well first 3 ingredients.
Add nuts, pineapple and coconut.
Mix well and pour into 2 graham cracker pie shells. Chill.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add onion, beaten egg and milk to dry ingredients, stirring slightly.
Drop teaspoon of batter into deep, hot fat.
Cook until brown.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on package.
Mix onions, celery, cheese and mayonnaise.
Spread over vegetables.
Melt butter and mix with cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken wings(appetizer)
directions: Mix melted butter and minced garlic in one bowl.
Mix crackers, cheese, parsley, pepper and paprika in another bowl. Dip chicken wings in butter bowl, then in cracker mixture.
Bake in a shallow greased pan for 35 to 45 minutes or until tender.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix eggs, corn, milk, oil, onion and green chilies.
Mix together corn meal, soda and salt; combine with liquid mixture. Add cheese.
Preheat oven to 375°, put well greased pans in oven to preheat and pour batter into warmed pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 - 60 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: chocolate kiss cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for kisses.
Roll dough into balls.
If dough is too sticky to work with, dip fingers into powdered sugar.
Place balls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
When almost cool, press kisses into center.

title: tuna cakes
directions: Lightly grease skillet. Mix all ingredients; form into patties. Brown on both sides.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: peach freezer jams
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Let stand 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: meat loaf superb
directions: Saute in large skillet over medium heat for 5 minutes the butter and onion.
Add and saute 8 to 10 minutes the tofu pieces and add tamari.
Add and stir until wilted, 5 to 8 minutes, the spinach and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Serve over steamed rice and enjoy.

title: chicken bundles
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: hot fruit
directions: Put fruit in large baking dish.
Heat brown sugar, pineapple juice, butter and ginger.
Pour over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet and hot mustard
directions: Combine mustard and vinegar and let sit overnight.
Beat eggs and sugar; add to mustard and vinegar and cook, stirring frequently, in double boiler until it starts to get thick (20 to 25 minutes).
Store in refrigerator.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef, onion and green pepper.
In a bowl, combine the soup or pizza sauce, tomato paste, soup, water, mushrooms, oregano and garlic salt.
Cook the noodles as directed. In a greased casserole, place a layer of noodles, ground beef and soup.
Repeat layers.
Place sliced pepperoni and cheese over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix well.
Store in a tight container.
To use, mix 2 heaping tablespoonfuls of tea with 1 cup of hot water.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Line a 9-inch deep-dish pie plate with one unbaked crust. Drain vegetables, chicken and mushrooms.
Mix all ingredients and season lightly with salt, pepper or any favorite seasonings.
Pour into pie pan and top with remaining pie crust.
Pinch edges together.
Slit the top crust in a few places and bake at 375° for about 45 minutes or until golden brown and bubbling.

title: banana cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle on cookies 1/2 cup brown sugar mixed with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pork and bean salad
directions: Drain beans; add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill. Serve with charcoaled mullets or any seafood.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Cut meat into pieces; brown well on both sides in oil.
Add mushrooms and onions.
Cook until lightly browned.
Blend in remaining ingredients; cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until meat is tender; stir often.
Remove bay leaf before serving. Serve on rice or noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter-chocolate candy
directions: Mix the first 3 items.
Add pecans, graham cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Roll into balls; dip in dark almond chocolate.

title: mama blanche's zucchini cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a mixer.
Add zucchini last; blend in lightly.
Bake in greased oblong pan on bottom rack. Cook for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Cool before cutting.

title: apple crisp
