directions: Mix butter, sugar and flour. Place apple slices in a 8x8 pan. Sprinkle butter topping over apples. Bake at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: frozen passion ice cream
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Freeze in ice cream freezer according to manufacturer's instructions.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Melt soup, cheese and milk (or water) on stove top in saucepan or in microwave in a large casserole dish.
Pour over cooked noodles, tuna and peas.
Stir.
Cook until bubbly in a 350° oven. Let cool for 10 to 15 minutes so sauce can thicken.
Serve over toast, if desired.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine in saucepan and boil sugar, cocoa, margarine, salt, and milk for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop onto waxed paper 1 tablespoon at a time.

title: mile high pie
directions: Add all ingredients together except pie shells and mix well. Pour into the pie shells and chill.

title: barley salad
directions: Heat 2 quarts water to boiling.
Add barley; bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer 40 minutes or until barley is tender. Rinse with cold water; drain.
Place vegetables and barley in large bowl.
Cut onions into 2-inch pieces.
Brown in hot salad oil.
Discard green onion.
Add oil to barley mixture, tossing to coat.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate two hours.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, butter and 1 egg.
Spread in bottom of glass dish.
Pour in pineapple.
Blend remaining ingredients and pour over crust and pineapple.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: curry dip
directions: Refrigerate before using to allow dip to flavor more. Excellent dip for fresh vegetables.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let sit overnight.
Add shredded Cheddar cheese, 2 to 3 chopped avocados and 2 to 3 chopped tomatoes.
Drain excess dressing and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Add flour, soda and salt; mix well. Stir in 1/2 cup M&M'S; reserve the rest for decoration. Drop by spoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Decorate tops with M&M'S. Bake at 375° for
to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: beef stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes, cool and slice in halves lengthwise.
Brown beef and diced onions; drain.
Scoop centers from baked potatoes, mash and add mayonnaise, milk and Cheddar cheese.
Mix beef with mashed potato mixture.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Spoon into shells of baked potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with butter.

title: candy apple walnut pie
directions: In large bowl, toss together apples, nuts, candies, 1/3 cup sugar and flour.
Pour into one crust.

title: mexicali casserole
directions: Remove wrappers from 1 can of tamales.
Cut tamales in thirds. Combine the cut tamales, hominy, sausage and soup.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven 30 or 40 minutes.
Remove wrappers from second can of tamales.
Cut tamales diagonally in halves.
Garnish top of casserole with cut tamales. Sprinkle with cheese atop.
Return to oven to melt cheese and heat top of tamales.

title: three bean salad
directions: Combine ingredients and let stand 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: dilly bread
directions: Mix all together and let rise 4 hours.
Work down using 1/2 cup flour.
Divide in loaves.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: poor man's punch
directions: Combine Kool-Aid with exact amount of water (follow package directions).
Add lemonade and pineapple juice.
Stir well and chill.
When serving, add ginger ale.
Yield: 4 ounce cups punch.

title: aunt gin's peanut brittle
directions: Melt sugar at 400°.
Stir until melted.
Add salted peanuts and baking soda.
Mix well.
Work fast.
Pour onto large buttered baking sheet.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Saute butter, celery and onion.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Place ribs, meat side up, in baking dish.
Place slices of onions and lemon on top of ribs.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan and cook over low heat for 30 minutes.
Bake ribs at 450° for 30 minutes.
Pour sauce over ribs and reduce heat to 350°. Cook for 1 hour.
Baste with sauce every 15 minutes.

title: quick punch
directions: Scoop sherbet into punch bowl.
Add lemon-lime carbonated beverages to sherbet.
Makes 25 to 30 (4 ounce) servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies ii
directions: Cream Crisco and brown sugar.
Add vanilla.
Beat in eggs. Mix flour, soda and salt.
Mix into sugar mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Remove to cooling racks.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: chicken-apple salad
directions: Separate meat from skin and bones; cut chicken into bite-sized pieces.
Mix chicken, apple and celery.
Mix salad dressing, cinnamon and salt.
Stir into chicken mixture.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: snowballs
directions: Melt chips and milk in a double boiler.
Stir constantly.
Add confectioners sugar and nuts.
Roll into balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat cheese and milk until fluffy.
Add lemon and vanilla and mix well.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours.
Top with cherry pie filling just before serving.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Bring butter, cocoa and milk to a boil.
Pour over sugar and mix well.
Then add vanilla and nuts.
Pour over cake while it's hot.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Prick dough and line with foil.
Fill with dried beans, uncooked rice or pie weights, bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool completely on wire rack.
In 2-quart saucepan, stir with wire whisk until well blended.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Continue cooking and stirring for 2 minutes or until thick.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients, except oleo and crackers, thoroughly.
Put in an 8 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Crush crackers and mix with the melted oleo; put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes with oleo.

title: traditional christmas eggnog
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar until thick and light.
Beat in cream, milk, salt and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until they hold stiff peaks; fold into egg yolk mixture.
Serve in chilled punch bowl; sprinkle with nutmeg. Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: lemon ice box pie
directions: Beat together, then pour one little bottle, about 3-5 oz,
of lemon juice in and mix. Pour into vanilla wafer crust and chill. Top with cool whip.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift the dry ingredients into a bowl.
Add wet ingredients all at once and stir just until moistened.
Bake in greased 8-inch square pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Add water to make 3 1/4 cups. Saute onions in shortening until tender.
Add 1 1/4 cups water, carrots, celery and bouillon.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Combine sugar, cornstarch, catsup, vinegar and soy sauce.
Stir into vegetable mixture.
Cook until clear and thickened.
Add chicken, green pepper and pineapple.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Make rice with measured liquid, salt and margarine.

title: texas caviar
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in medium saucepan.
Simmer on medium heat until hot.
Add cheese and stir until cheese melts. Mash mixture slightly.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: any bean salad
directions: Drain the beans; combine the beans, green pepper, pimiento and onion in a bowl.
Mix together oil, vinegar, oregano, parsley and pepper.
Pour over the vegetables and mix well.
Marinate in the refrigerator at least 3 hours.

title: spinach salad
directions: Shake well and refrigerate.

title: herb grilled chicken breast
directions: In blender or food processor, combine all ingredients except chicken.
Process until mixture is pureed.
Spread mixture on all sides of breast pieces.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator overnight (or at least 15 minutes).
Before grilling, scrape off excess marinade.
Grill or broil 6 to 8 inches from heat source for 5 to 10 minutes per side until cooked through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: curry herring(karrysild)
directions: Cut herring into small pieces.
Slice eggs.
Layer herring and eggs in bowl.
Put chopped onion on top.
Mix mayonnaise with cream and curry powder.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour dressing over herring and decorate with sliced hard-boiled eggs and chopped parsley.
This can be artfully arranged in a clear glass bowl to show the layers.

title: grandma b's chicken
directions: Mix ingredients together and spread on chicken.
This is enough for 2 chickens, cut up.
Add enough water to cover bottom of pan.
Cover loosely and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
You can also place approximately 8 large or 10 to 12 small pieces of chicken, skin side down, in pan; this is instead of cutting up 2 chickens.

title: crowd pleasing potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with bay leaf until barely tender.
Peel and grate potatoes.
In a pot, add butter to soup.
Stir until smooth. Blend in sour cream, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle in onion salt and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Blend well.

title: chocolate raspberry ice cream
directions: Heat whipping cream.
Beat yolks and sugar together.
Gradually add hot cream to yolks mixture, whisking constantly.
Cook mixture in top of double boiler over hot water stirring constantly until mixture thickens, about 8 minutes.
Do not let mixture boil. Remove from heat.
Strain mixture into bowl.
Add chocolate and vanilla stirring occasionally until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth.
Cool completely.
Stir raspberries with juice into cool mixture.
Freeze in ice cream freezer according to manufacturer's instructions.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: custard pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt and cinnamon; beat lightly.
Heat milk until just beginning to scald.
Beat milk into egg mixture; pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until table knife comes out clean when inserted in center.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Mix all together with mixer for 3 minutes.
Put in floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in water; stir in Eagle Brand milk and egg yolks.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat; add margarine and vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Slice 2 bananas and dip in lemon juice; drain.
Arrange on bottom of baked pie shell.
Pour pudding over all and chill until set, about 4 hours.

title: cucumber soup(guatemala)
directions: In a large saucepan, warn the oil over medium heat.
Add the cucumbers, onion and red pepper.
Cook until the vegetables are tender, about 15 minutes.
Stir in the chicken broth and simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
In a blender or food processor, puree the soup until very smooth and return it to the sauce pan.
Bring to a simmer and season to taste with salt and pepper.
You can serve hot with a tablespoon of yogurt and rice.

title: rum balls
directions: Combine crumbs, powdered sugar, 1 cup of pecans and cocoa. Add corn syrup and rum and mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Roll in sugar or pecans.
Store in airtight container.
Improves with age!

title: hot reuben dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Dip with rye bread or rye Triscuits.

title: chocolate chip zucchini cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and oil together. Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk. beat with mixer. Mix together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Beat well. Stir in zucchini. Pour batter into greased and floured cake pan. Sprinkle top with chocolate chips. Bake at 350 degrees for 40-45 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients and add water until mixture is thick. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Drop into hot deep fat 1 teaspoonful at a time.
Turn several times until golden brown.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients.
Mix the remaining ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Blend together.
Put into a 2-quart buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.
Serves 8.

title: fruit punch
directions: Blend together and enjoy.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Mix all ingredients. Put in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Crush and sprinkle potato chips over hot casserole.
Return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: milky way energizer
directions: Combine Milky Way bars, milk and peach in a 5-cup blender container.
Process at high speed until smooth, about 45 seconds. Gradually add ice and process until ice is melted.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour in a small bowl.
Set aside.
Mix eggs, melted butter and buttermilk; stir in flour and sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla and lemon juice if desired.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes until set.

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix together, adding a few drops of food coloring.
Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie crust, top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini crescent pie
directions: Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles.
Place on an ungreased 10-inch pie pan.
Press over the bottom and sides of pan to form crust.
Cook onion and zucchini in butter.
Stir in parsley, salt, pepper, garlic, basil and oregano.
Beat eggs and combine with cheese.
Pour vegetable mix into crust, then pour egg mixture over all.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 18 to 20 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
If browns too fast, cover crust with foil during last 10 minutes of baking.

title: salmon squares
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Drain salmon liquid into measuring cup and add to milk.
Add with cracker crumbs and wheat germ to eggs; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pan which has been oiled and sprinkled with wheat germ.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash and eggs well.
Add butter, onion, crumbs and pepper.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: pecan cheese wafers
directions: Cream margarine while grating cheese.
Add cheese and mix well. Mix together dry ingredients and add to cheese mixture.
Blend in well.
Shape into small balls and place on ungreased baking sheet. Press a pecan half into each ball.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes being careful not to overbake.
(These will keep several days in a tightly covered tin and also freeze well.)

title: oreo dessert
directions: Cut candy bars into small pieces.
Crush Oreo cookies with rolling pin.
Mix it all together. Spread half in 9 x 13-inch pan, then spread 1/2 gallon softened vanilla ice cream on top and cover with remaining cookie/candy bar mixture.
Freeze.

title: cheese log
directions: In mixer bowl, beat together butter and seasonings at medium speed until fluffy, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Blend cheese and lemon juice into butter mixture.
Form into log shape on wax paper and chill for a few hours.

title: caramel corn(cracker jacks)
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan.
Add brown sugar and Karo syrup, stirring constantly.
Let boil 1 minute.
Add soda and stir well.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and add vanilla and peanut butter.
Spoon onto waxed paper.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken pieces in hot olive oil until lightly colored. Add onion, garlic, basil and parsley.
Brown along with chicken until chicken is golden brown and vegetables are soft and slightly colored.
Wet with sherry or wine and allow to evaporate.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add tomatoes and their juices. Cover and simmer for about 20 to 30 minutes or until chicken is tender and sauce has thickened a little.
Serve over spaghetti and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: green beans with cashews
directions: In large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add onion and garlic; cook, stirring for 2 minutes.
Add beans, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring 3 minutes.
Add cashews and cook 1 minute. Contains 210 calories per serving.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Put macaroni, diced ham and cheese mixture into a casserole dish.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter and add to Ritz crackers.
Spread cracker mixture on top.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: carrots au gratin
directions: Combine crumbs and 2 tablespoons of the margarine; set aside. Add onion to remaining margarine.
Saute over low heat.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in milk.
Increase heat to medium; cook until bubbly and thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cheese; stir until smooth.
Stir in carrots and parsley flakes.
Spread in shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with crumb mixture. Bake in a 350° oven about 20 minutes or until bubbly and crumbs are golden brown.
Yields 8 servings.
Contains 220 calories per serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil onions, squash, salt and pepper in cooker until tender; drain.
Put squash in casserole dish.
Now put 1 to 2 layers of squash, butter, cream of mushroom soup, cheese and bread stuffing.
Top with bread stuffing and then cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbling and golden brown.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom

title: cheese cake
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften at room temperature.
Add one egg at a time.
Gradually add sugar.
Add vanilla.
Fold in sour cream.
Pour in crust.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Turn oven off and leave for 1 hour.
Refrigerate cake after it cools.

title: doughnut balls
directions: Mix together sugar, milk and eggs.
Melt Crisco; add to the first.
Add flour, salt, baking powder and nutmeg.
Combine the liquid and dry mix.
Stir until smooth.
Drop by teaspoon in fryer; fry until brown at 365° for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: cocktail hot dogs
directions: Mix catsup, sugar and bourbon.
Put in the wieners, and simmer several hours.
This is ideal for a crock pot.
Serve hot.

title: talarina
directions: Cook noodles until done.
Drain.
In skillet, brown meat and add onion and pepper and cook until done.
In a large baking dish, add noodles, meat mixture and remaining ingredients, reserving 1 cup cheese for top.
Mix well.
Add cheese on top and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Recipe may be halved.

title: light and airy pancakes
directions: Barely
blend the ingredients.
Do not overmix!
That's the secret to these pancakes.
Cook on griddle around 400°.

title: great grandmother phillips' chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together.
Add eggs and pinch of salt. Mix well.
Add margarine and milk.
Pour into uncooked pie shell. Start oven at 425°.
Bake 10 minutes.
Turn oven down to 400° and bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt, cloves, cinnamon and red pepper. Stir with fork to mix.
Coat 1/3 of tomato slices at a time with the sugar mixture.
Spread slices evenly over dough in pie pan. Sprinkle with raisins and top with remaining sugar mixture. Drizzle with vinegar and dot with butter.
Roll out remaining dough; cover filling with pastry.
Crimp edges and cut 2 or 3 small vents in top crust.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes or until crust is golden and juices bubble around edges.

title: mexican breakfast
directions: Brown hot sausage with the chopped garlic or garlic powder, chopped onion and chopped bell pepper.
Add 2 cups hash browns. Season with 1 teaspoon cumin and salt and pepper to taste.
Add dashes of hot sauce.
Simmer.
Beat together the eggs, scrambled with 1/4 cup of water, salt and pepper.
Just before done, add 1 cup or more of cheese.
Stuff hot flour tortillas.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° on a cookie sheet pan.
Ice while warm.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: molded cheese and pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve lemon gelatin in 1 cup boiling water. Chill until slightly thickened. Beat until light and fluffy. Fold in whipped cream. Add cottage cheese. Pour into 10 individual molds to partly fill them. Dissolve lime flavored gelatin in boiling
water. Add pineapple juice. Chill until slightly thickened. Add pineapple. Pour onto lemon layer, filling molds. Chill until firm. Makes 8-10 servings.

title: concho bars
directions: Mix cake mix, brown sugar, melted oleo, eggs and water.
Add pecans and chocolate chips.
Mix all and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix together.
Roll out.
Use cookie cutters.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Mix lemon juice with
milk.
Add pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Pour into crust and chill.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Combine pudding and milk and beat until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers. Add layer of pudding mix.
Continue adding layers of graham crackers and pudding mix, but stop with graham crackers on top. Bring cocoa, evaporated milk and sugar to a boil, stirring constantly.
Let cool for 1 minute, then add margarine and vanilla flavoring.
Pour over cake.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: "tamale pie"
directions: In large skillet, brown beef, breaking up with spoon.
Drain off fat.
Add onion and green pepper, saute until tender.
Stir in tomatoes (chopped if necessary), corn, chili powder, salt, pepper and cumin.
Simmer, uncovered 15 minutes, until thickened.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat; drain and add soup and water.
Put into baking dish deep pie pan.
Cover with biscuits and bake in hot oven at 350° until biscuits are done.

title: creole salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
In large bowl, add macaroni, chopped tomatoes and olives.
In separate bowl, put mayonnaise.
Here's the secret: Grate on small side of cheese grater, juice from one onion into mayonnaise.
Add garlic and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix dressing with macaroni, tomato and olive mixture.
Top with grated cheese and chill.

title: beef pot roast(4 or 5 pounds)
directions: Cook roast, salt and pepper in water, covering meat, about 1/2 hour.
Add potatoes, onions and carrots.
Cook another 15 minutes. Add mushroom soup and onion soup.
Cook about 30 minutes or until juices are thick.

title: beef noodle dish
directions: Cook until meat is not red and onion and pepper are soft.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add olives (with juice) and tomatoes.
Cook noodles according to directions.
Mix and put into casserole.
When ready to use, top with soup and grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 325° until bubbly and cheese slightly browned.
This freezes well before adding soup.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Put in 4 cups of sliced apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, salt and water.
Rub together the flour, sugar and butter.
Drop mixture over apples.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with cream, if desired.

title: herbed stuffing mix
directions: Dry bread in slow oven for about 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Stir in seasonings and oil.
Lightly toss the cubes.
Store in airtight container. Label and store in cool, dry place.
Use within 4 months.
Makes 12 cups.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in cool whip and pineapple.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.

title: pignoli cookies
directions: Whip egg whites; add sugar.
Break up almond paste and add to egg mixture.
Beat well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Grease and flour cookie sheets.
Make small balls; roll in nuts (do not flatten). Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Stir in strawberries, pineapple and nuts.
Place 1/2 Jell-O mixture in a baking dish and let set until firm.
Mix sour cream and bananas and spread over firm mixture. Gently spoon the remaining Jell-O evenly over smoothed sour cream mixture and let set until firm.
To serve, cut into squares and place on lettuce.

title: roast buffet ham
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut the ham into slices.
Distribute the ham in a roasting pan.
Mix the rest of the ingredients in a bowl and pour over the ham.
Cover the roasting pan and heat in the oven for 40 minutes.
Rotate the ham slices and heat for 35 more minutes.
Serve hot in the pan with juices.

title: skyline dip
directions: Press cream cheese in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Skyline chili, followed by cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Dip with tortilla chips.

title: polish sausage skillet supper
directions: In a large skillet, brown sausage on all sides.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat 20 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Makes 4 servings.
Has 680 calories per serving.

title: poor man's lobster
directions: Place fish in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread soup over fish. Melt oleo and add crushed crackers and clams with juice.
Spread over fish and soup mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chili con carne(6 servings)
directions: Brown onion and garlic.
Remove garlic before adding other ingredients.
Add meat and brown slightly.
Add beans, tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer on top of stove until thickened.

title: golden punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ginger ale.
Chill by adding plastic bag filled with ice cubes.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Serves 30 to 35.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Put sugar, Karo, milk, salt and chocolate in saucepan; stir to dissolve.
Bring slowly to the boiling point, stirring occasionally.
Cook, after it boils, without stirring to a soft ball stage when tried in cold water.
Add butter, vanilla and nuts (pecans or almonds).
Cool slightly.
Beat until candy begins to lose its gloss.
Pour into a buttered sheet pan; cool and cut in squares.

title: rice and beans(20 minutes)
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add onion and garlic; cook and stir until tender but not browned.
Stir in beans, tomatoes, water and oregano.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice; return to boil. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cole slaw
directions: Place grated cabbage in mixing bowl; sprinkle sugar over top. Cover bowl and place in refrigerator for at least 1 hour before serving.
When ready to serve, take from refrigerator and mix in mayonnaise, stirring well to mix sugar and mayonnaise.
Place in serving dish and serve.

title: peanut butter marshmallow fudge
directions: Cook the sugar and milk to the soft ball stage (236°).
Add the marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla; mix well.
If big marshmallows are used, mix until dissolved.
Pour into a buttered pan (9-inch square).
Cool and cut in about 40 pieces.
Makes about 1 1/2 pounds.

title: spiced apples
directions: In medium skillet, combine the first 6 spiced apple ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, until slightly thickened.
Add apples.
Simmer, uncovered, until apples are just tender, stirring gently.
Serve with sliced pork roast.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: ranch oyster crackers
directions: Mix Ranch dressing packet, oil, garlic salt and dill weed in large bowl.
Add crackers and mix until mostly absorbed.
Pour onto cookie sheet and bake in 250° oven for 5 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Mix together and pack in loaf pan. Store in airtight container.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Boil slowly sugar, water and milk.
After it starts to boil real hard when stirring, add the pecans.
Cook until soft ball stage.
Add vanilla or almond flavoring and remove from heat. Stir for a few minutes and then drop by spoonful on wax paper.

title: brownie cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients in order given. Place by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 9 to 10 minutes.

title: crab or shrimp jambalaya
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Add onion and pepper; cook until tender.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add tomatoes and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add rice and shrimp or crabmeat.
Serves 6.

title: connie's cheese ball
directions: Mix together; form roll and chill.
Can be rolled with pecans.

title: cheddar crown loaf(makes 1 large loaf)
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly mix 2 1/2 cups flour with the sugar, salt and undissolved dry yeast.
Combine milk, water and 3 tablespoons margarine in a saucepan.
Heat over low heat until liquids are very warm; the margarine does not need to melt. Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in cheese and enough additional flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk, about 45 minutes.

title: noodle salad
directions: Break up broccoli and cauliflower into a large bowl. Cut up carrots, cucumbers and olives into small pieces and add to bowl. Cut up cheeses into small blocks and add to bowl. Refrigerate mixture.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Fry bacon in six quart pan.
Remove bacon (set aside) and pour chopped onion and garlic into hot grease.
Cook until onion is clear.
Sprinkle flour into grease and stir until mixture is brown.
Pour in peas and add the bacon.
Give it a dash of salt and pepper and cook on low heat for about 1 hour.
Season to taste.

title: cupcakes
directions: Stir shortening to soften.
Gradually add sugar and cream thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating after each addition.
Pour into paper bake cups in muffin pans (1/2 full).
Bake at 375° about 20 minutes or until done.

title: sour cream jalapeno corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease muffin cups or use paper or foil baking cups.
Thoroughly mix corn meal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a large bowl.
Beat eggs and sour cream with whisk or fork in a small bowl.
When smooth, stir in jalapeno. Pour over flour mixture.
Fold in with a rubber spatula until well mixed.
Batter will be very stiff.
Scoop batter into muffin cups. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until firm to the touch in the center.
Let cool 5 minutes in pan before turning onto a rack to cool.
Serve at any temperature.
Makes 12 regular muffins.

title: halupki
directions: Core head of cabbage well. Parboil in large pot of water. Separate leaves. Remove hard vein without cutting through the leaf. Cabbage leaves should be flimsy (cooked enough) so that when filled, they do not crack.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Mix in rest of ingredients.
Drop onto waxed paper with teaspoon.
Makes 30 cookies.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread in ungreased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Cook in 375° oven until done, about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: easy meat and potato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown beef and drain.
In ungreased 12 x 8-inch baking dish, evenly layer potatoes.
Spoon ground beef over potatoes.
Spoon vegetable soup evenly over top.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover; sprinkle with cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix until crumbly the peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Save some of this mixture for the top of the pie.
Sprinkle crumb mixture in bottom of crust.
Cover with cooled vanilla pudding. Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle rest of crumb mixture on top, and chill.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix with hands.
Shape into small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cool boiled chicken.
Pull meat from bones.
Put meat back into broth.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook 45 minutes, then add bag of noodles.
Cook until done.
Serve.

title: mom's oatmeal cake
directions: In large bowl, put oats and stick of butter. Do not melt butter. Pour boiling water over and let stand for 20 minutes. Mix remaining ingredients with oat mixture. Mix well with mixer on medium speed. Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Pour batter into pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine pineapple with juice, pudding mix, Jell-O and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture starts to boil.
Remove from heat; cool completely.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for 2 hours, covered.
Stir again before serving.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the shortening and butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool completely on a rack.
Yields one 10-inch cake.

title: date and nut fruit cake("christmas goody")
directions: Cut dates in small chunks.
Mix with boiling water and baking soda.
Let cool and set aside.
Cream the sugar, Crisco, egg yolks, walnuts, raisins, candied fruit mix and add date mixture. Sift together flour and baking powder and add to date mixture. Add vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whits and add to date mixture.
Spread on greased cookie sheet or loaf pans.
Bake at 350° approximately 40 to 45 minutes. Cool
and cut into squares or slices.

title: apple strudel baklava
directions: Keep unused phyllo dough covered with damp towel while working.
Lay 6 sheets of phyllo in bottom of a buttered 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan, brushing each sheet with some margarine. Combine apples, nuts, sugar, raisins, lemon peel, lemon juice and cinnamon.
Sprinkle half the nut mixture over the phyllo in pan. Top with 6 more sheets of phyllo brushed with margarine.
Add remaining nut mixture.
Top with remaining phyllo brushed with margarine.
Trim phyllo even with edges of pan.
Score into diamonds. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes. Warm honey; drizzle over diamonds. Cool.

title: mustard sauce for ham
directions: Combine
ingredients and bring to boil.
Serve with ham hot or on sandwiches.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let set overnight to blend.

title: chocolate chip cheese cake
directions: First, you beat your cream cheese until smooth and gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Stir in whipped topping, then stir in chocolate chips.
Spoon
mixture into your crust.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: ski stew
directions: Heat oil in 2-quart saucepan.
When hot, add onion and celery. Cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally with wooden spoon, until onions are tender, not brown.
This will take 5 minutes. Add hot dogs and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine sour cream, dressing mix and 1/2 of the cheese. Reserve about 1/3 of this mixture.
Add cut up chicken and olives and mix.
Spoon chicken mixture onto tortilla shell.
Roll up and place seam side down on a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Spoon reserved sour cream mixture over tortillas.
Serve with medium salsa spooned on top.
Serves 6.

title: kentucky bourbon balls
directions: Mix chocolate wafers, pecans, cocoa powder and sugar.
Stir in corn syrup and bourbon.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls and roll in chocolate sprinkles.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Mix together all ingredients and place in baking pan.
